<TITLE>No-vote reasons removed by one who still votes</TITLE>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<!--Connections 32 Template - Features Menu Page--><!--Use the Headline for HTML Page TITLE>--><!--Headline-->
<p align="center"><a href="/"><img src="../../images/flag.gif"
alt="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border="0"
width="595" height="176"></a><br clear="all">
</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top" width="150"><i>November 05, 1996</i></td>
        <td width="470"><!--FIRST STORY TEMPLATE-->
				<FONT SIZE="+3"><B>No-vote reasons removed by one who still votes</B></FONT><BR><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
				<FONT size="-1"><I>By Sam Venable, Columnist</I></FONT><P>
				<FONT SIZE="-1"><!--dateline--></FONT></DIV></B><BR>
				<FONT SIZE="+2">I</FONT>n the entrepreneurial spirit of the 1990s, I officially claim, as personal and exclusive property, the following 25 excuses for not voting today:
<P>   1. One vote won&#39;t make any difference.
<P>   2. All the candidates are basically alike.
<P>   3. All politicians are crooked, so why bother giving them another opportunity to rip me off?
<P>   4. The weather is going to be bad, and I don&#39;t want to get (fill in blank) wet, cold, windblown.
<P>   5. The weather is going to be good, and I want to (fill in blank) go fishing, work in the yard, wash the car, play golf.
<P>   6. There&#39;s a lot of road construction between my house and the polls.
<P>   7. There&#39;s going to be a crowd.
<P>   8. I meant to vote early but forgot.
<P>   9. My bum (fill in blank) knee, back, neck, leg is starting to hurt, and it&#39;ll only get worse if I have to wait in line.
<P>   10. All those goofs handing out campaign material will be outside the place, and I don&#39;t want to have to fool with them.
<P>   11. Whether unification passes or fails, the fat cats will still be in charge.
<P>   12. Nobody is telling the whole truth on (name of issue) so who can you believe?
<P>   13. (Name of issue) is too complicated, so why not leave it up to someone who understands it better?
<P>   14. My (fill in blank) wife, husband, brother, sister, mother, father, friend will simply cancel out my vote anyway.
<P>   15. The flu is going around, and sure as the world somebody&#39;ll cough or sneeze and I&#39;ll catch it.
<P>   16. Everybody knows that (fill in blank) the media, major political parties, big corporations, labor unions, organized crime bosses control the outcome in the first place.
<P>   17. The only things politicians really care about is getting re-elected.
<P>   18. I knew (name of candidate) when we were in high school, and (he/she) was always such a holier-than-thou, know-it-all jerk; I wouldn&#39;t give (him/her) air in a jug.
<P>   19. I&#39;ve got too much work to do.
<P>   20. I&#39;ve got to run out of town this morning, and it&#39;ll be a pain to get back before the polls close.
<P>   21. The traffic&#39;s bad enough around a school to begin with, let alone with all this election mess.
<P>   22. (Name of candidate) is a shoo-in already.
<P>   23. (Name of candidate) doesn&#39;t have a prayer of a chance of winning.
<P>   24. My car&#39;s in the shop and I don&#39;t want to bother asking my neighbor for a ride.
<P>   25. I want to catch up on my (fill in blank) reading, TV watching, sleep, housework.
<P>   There. If you can think up any other excuses, fine. But as far as these particular ones are concerned, hands off.
<P>   Like any good rich, conservative Republican, I have laid claim to them all. They are mine and mine alone, to use or not use as I see fit. You can&#39;t have any of them.
<P>   What if you do? Well, like any good bleeding-heart, liberal Democrat, I&#39;ll sue the pants off you.
<P>   See you at the polls.
<P>
<P><font size=2><strong>Sam Venable&#39;s column appears in The News-Sentinel on Sunday, Tuesday, Thursday and Friday. His column also is available on our Web site at www.knoxnews.com. His latest book, &#39;&#39;I&#39;d Rather Be Ugly Than Stuppid,&#39;&#39; is now available from The News-Sentinel and area bookstores.</strong></font>
<P>

        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

<hr size="5">

