<P><B>MARLOWE, WADE ELVIN - </B>58, of White Oak, Tenn., passed away Saturday, January 18, 1997, at the Jellico Community Hospital. He was a heavy equipment operator and a veteran of the Korean War. Preceded in death by his father, Floyd Marlowe. Survived by: wife, Wanda West Marlowe of White Oak, Tenn.; sons, Mike Marlowe and wife, Niobie of Smyrna, Tenn., Aaron Marlowe, White Oak, Tenn.; two grandchildren, Erica and Kimber Marlowe; mother, Alta Marlowe of White Oak, Tenn.; brothers and sisters-in-law, Robert and Jeanette Marlowe of Oak Ridge, Tenn., Curtis and Genevee Marlowe of White Oak, Tenn., Malcolm and Deloris Marlowe of Canton, Mich., David and Beth Marlowe of White Oak, Tenn.; sisters and brothers-in-law, Joyce and Chuck Gentry of Knoxville, Tenn., Alma and Cordell Bragg of Harrodsburg, Ky.; several nieces and nephews; and a host of friends. The family will receive friends Monday from 5-8 p.m. at the Cox and Son Funeral Home Chapel with funeral service to follow at 8 p.m. with Rev. William Floyd officiating. Family and friends will meet at 11 a.m. Tuesday, January 21, 1997, at the Campbell Memorial Gardens, LaFollette, Tenn. for graveside service and interment. Cox and Son Funeral Home, in charge.
<P>
<P><B>MARTIN, MR. KEVIN PENN - </B>age 46, of Sevierville, formerly of Newport, died Saturday evening, January 18, 1997, at Fort Sanders Sevier Medical Center. Mr. Martin had worked as a social worker for Holston Home of the United Methodist Church and previously for the State of Tennessee. He was of the Catholic faith. He was preceded in death by: his mother, Mary Ann Martin; and foster father, James Huff Clark. Survivors include: his father, George P. Martin of Kingsport; foster family, Ann M. Clark of Sweetwater, Marti Steffen of Knoxville, and Penny Ervin of Newport; brother, Steve Martin of Kingsport; sister, Patrica Edens of Gray; and special friend, Anna Kate Walker of Sevierville. Graveside services will be held at 11 a.m. Tuesday at the Huff Family Cemetery in Bridgeport with Rev. Charles Starks officiating. Family and friends will meet at 10:45 a.m. for the 11 a.m. service at the Huff Cemetery. The family will receive friends from 6 until 8 p.m. Monday evening at Costner-Maloy Funeral Home. The family requests that memorials be made to the National Kidney Foundation East Tennessee, Walkers Springs Blvd., Knoxville, TN 37917. Costner-Maloy Funearl Home, Newport, is in charge of arrangements.
