<P><B>MCCLURE, PAUL W. - </B>age 82, of Maryville, died Saturday, January 18, 1997, at his home. He was a member of Clarks Grove Cumberland Presbyterian Church, was retired from ALCOA with 42 years of service and was a member of the ALCOA 25 Year Service Club. He was a veteran of WWII, serving in the U.S. Army Air Corps and was a member of the VFW. He was preceded in death by: brothers, Charlie, Willie, Frank, and Raymond McClure; sisters, Lucy Hitch, Bertha Horton, and Mildred Carroll Smith. Survivors include: his wife, Sylvia Lorene McClure of Maryville; son and daughter-in-law, James and Dorothy McClure; daughters and sons-in-law, Paula and Larry Wolfe, Sara and Ted Sowders; grandchildren, Brooke McClure, Justin McClure, Gene Wolfe, Lisa and Brad Hutsell, Kami Wolfe, Tom, Jeff, Monica, and Susan Sowders; two great-grandchildren; sisters, Elizabeth Vandaveer, Katie Anderson, and Kathleen Foster; several nieces and nephews; special friends, Patsy and Ernest Jones, and Joyce Lucas. Funeral services will be 7 p.m. Monday in McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home Chapel with Rev. Gale Keown officiating. Family and friends will meet 10 a.m., Tuesday in Clarks Grove Cemetery for the interment service. The family will receive friends Monday from 6-7 p.m. at McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home, Maryville.
