<P><B>MILLER, OPAL SAMSEL - </B>age 66, of Rt. #2, Bean Station, passed away January 18, at U.T. Medical Center in Knoxville. She was a member of Central United Methodist Church, Tate Spring #425 Order of Eastern Star, secretary of the Grainger County Senior Citizens, and member of the Women&#39;s Club of Grainger County. She was preceded in death by: her parents, Tom and Alice Samsel; and a brother, Gale Samsel. Survivors include: husband of 51 years, Fred Miller, Bean Station; daughter and son-in-law, Rhonda and Harold Reagan, Rutledge; daughter, Donna Winstead, Morristown; grandchildren, Richard and Melissa Reagan, Matt and Mindy Winstead; brother, Wavy Samsel, Bean Station; five nephews; and one niece. Funeral services will be conducted 8:30 p.m. Tuesday evening at Mayes Mortuary with Rev. Jeff Wright officiating. Prior to funeral services, Eastern Star services will be held on Tuesday evening. Graveside services will be held Wednesday, January 22, 11 a.m. at Hamblen Memory Gardens. The family will receive friends Tuesday evening, 6 p.m. until time of services at Mayes Mortuary in Morristown.
