<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 19, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>2 get promotions at Home & Garden TV</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">T</FONT>wo women have been promoted at the Knoxville-based Home & Garden Television.
<P>   Pamela Cannella Treacy has been named vice president of new business. She formerly was senior director of new business.
<P>   In the new position, Treacy will continue the sales and management of the network&#39;s alternative technologies. Her new responsibilities will include oversight of HGTV&#39;s local ad sales department and coordination of administration functions of the affiliate sales department.
<P>   She joined HGTV in 1994 and has also been senior director for the Southeast region&#39;s affiliate sales. Prior to joining HGTV, she worked at ESPN for eight years, most recently as the director of the Central region&#39;s affiliate sales and marketing.
<P>   Also at HGTV, Orlinda Gray has been named the network&#39;s facilities manager.
<P>   Her responsibilities will include building repair and maintenance, grounds upkeep, mail delivery service, security system, phone system administration and vehicle and office equipment maintenance.
<P>   Gray has been employed in facilities management for more than a decade. She most recently worked for IT Corp. in Knoxville, where she gained more than 20 years experience in office environment management.
<P>   More than 200 employees work in the 90,000-square-foot HGTV/Cinetel Productions/Cinetel Studios facility. 
<P>   &#39;&#39;Orlinda brings to our organization a depth of experience that meets these challenges,&#39;&#39; said Mark Hale, executive vice president of Cinetel Studios. &#39;&#39;Her leadership skills are crucial as we continue to grow our companies and expand our operations.&#39;&#39;
<P>
