<P><B>MURPHY, ADA RAMSEY INGLE - </B>73, of Fountain City, died Friday, January 17, 1997, at her home. Member of Church Street United Methodist Church and was active in the Achievement Sunday School as well as many other community affairs and projects. She served as first president of the Knoxville Homebuilders Auxiliary and was named in 1976 as the Secretary of the Year by the Knoxville Legal Secretary Assoc. Preceded in death by her first husband, Ernest W. Ingle. Survivors: husband, Col. Robert M. Murphy; daughter and son-in-law, Janie and David Pollard; son and daughter-in-law, David and Gail Ingle; sister, Mary Carringer, all of Knoxville; grandchildren, Ernie Ingle and his wife, Brooke of Knoxville, Laura Beth Ingle of Knoxville and David Pollard, Jr. of Nashville; also several nieces. Funeral service 2 p.m. Monday in Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel with Rev. William Fowler and Dr. D.L. Hammer officiating. Interment will follow at Lynnhurst Cemetery. Pallbearers: David Pollard, Jr., Ernie Ingle, Richie and Doug Sexton, Edward Ingle and Eric New. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Church St. United Methodist Church, 900 Henley Street, Knoxville, Tenn. 37902 or American Cancer Society. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Sunday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
