<P>h3816_0122
<P><B>SMITH, BISHOP CECIL JAMES - </B>was born, January 3, 1918, in Knoxville, Tenn. He departed this life Thursday, January 16, 1997, at Brakebill Nursing Home. A Bishop of the Church of God and a member of Cherry Street Church of God. He pastored churches in Maryville, Tenn. and for 30 years he faithfully served the Church of God Sanctified in Springfield, Ohio. A veteran of World War II. Survivors: wife, Lucille Smith; sister, Hortense B. Arnold; brother, Oliver V. (Blanche Mae) Hemphill, Hollywood, Calif.; four nephews, Leon, Ronald, Robert, and Allen Hemphill; six nieces, Yvonne, Gloria, and Gayle, all of California, Earnestine Pennex, Annie (Charlie) Whitman, and Della (William) Oliver, of Knoxville; devoted cousin, Janice (Jesse) DeBro; loving friend, Mrs. Annie Moore of Springfield, Ohio; other family members, the Rogers, Harris, Perry, and Armstrong families; devoted friends, Bishop and Mrs. John Batts, Wilbur Burris, Mr. and Mrs. Robert L. Patton, Mr. and Mrs. John Morgan; and a host of other relatives and friends. The family will receive friends Tuesday, January 21, 1997, at Cherry Street Church of God from 6:30-7 p.m. with funeral to follow. Bishop John W. Batts officiating, assisted by other ministers. Interment Wednesday, January 22, 1997, at Tennessee State Veterans Cemetery at 10 a.m. The family will be at the home of his sister, Hortense Arnold, 2233 Dandridge Ave. Arrangements by Unity Mortuary.
