<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top" width="150"><i>January 19, 1997</i> </td>
        <td width="470"><font size="6"><b>Business group taps Top
        Ten Web sites<!--SUBHEAD--></b></font><p><br>
        <font size="5">H</font>ere is the 1996 list of Top Ten
        World Wide Web sites for small business, as compiled by
        First American Group Purchasing Association, a New
        Orleans purchasing and information resource for small
        business: </p>
        <p>1. <b>Net Marquee Family Business Center NetCenter</b>
        -- Articles, papers, newsletters and other small business
        information for owners and executives of family owned
        companies. (<a href="http://www.nmq.com/">http://www.nmq.com/</a>).
        </p>
        <p>2. <strong>Smart Business Supersite </strong>-- How-to
        business information, articles and newsletters. (<a
        href="http://www.smartbiz.com/">http://www.smartbiz.com</a>).
        </p>
        <p>3. <b>SCOR-Net</b> -- A Small Corporate Offering
        Registration network featuring service providers
        knowledgeable about raising capital for small business,
        including direct public offerings market space. (<a
        href="http://www.scor-net.com/">http://www.scor-net.com</a>)
        </p>
        <p>4. <b>Let's Talk Business Network</b> -- Online radio
        program focused on entrepreneurship, small business and
        franchising. A mentoring area includes interviews with
        successful entrepreneurs and top resources. (<a
        href="http://www.ltbn.com/">http://www.ltbn.com</a>). </p>
        <p>5. <b>SBA Women in Business </b>-- Resources, funding,
        technology, forums and mentoring programs for women-owned
        businesses. (<a
        href="http://www.sbaonline.sba.gov/womeninbusiness/">http://www.sbaonline.sba.gov/womeninbusiness</a>).
        </p>
        <p>6. <b>Export USA</b> -- Includes the ''Bible'' of U.S.
        exporting, John R. Jegoe's export advice book. (<a
        href="http://www.exportusa.com/">http://www.
        exportusa.com</a>). </p>
        <p>7. <b>Committee on Small Business</b> -- The U.S.
        Senate's schedule of committee meetings concerning small
        business and government publications about small
        business. (<a href="http://www.senate.gov/tsbc/">http://www.senate.gov/tsbc/</a>).
        </p>
        <p>8.<b> CNN Financial Network </b>-- Financial news and
        an open forum for users. (http://www.cnnfn.com). </p>
        <p>9.<b> Franchise Handbook On Line</b> -- A franchise
        directory and help in evaluating fanchises. (<a
        href="http://franchise1.com/">http://franchise1.com</a>).
        </p>
        <p>10. <b>Secret Source</b> -- How to stay on top in the
        latest professions, including legal and finance. (<a
        href="http://www.secretsource.com/">http://www.secretsource.com/</a>).
        </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
