<html>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<head>
	<title>Realtors honor Jim Simpson, install Dick Scarborough as &#39;97 president</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper Business News">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<a href="/"><img src="../../images/flag.gif" alt="Knoxville News-Sentinel Online -- Business News" align=bottom border=0 width=595 height=176></a><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td align=left valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 19, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Realtors honor Jim Simpson, install Dick Scarborough as &#39;97 president</B></font><basefont size=6><!--SUBHEAD--></basefont></FONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I>By Jerry Dean, News-Sentinel business writer</I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		<FONT SIZE="+2">J</FONT>im Simpson of Volunteer Realty&#39;s commercial division was named by the Knoxville Association of Realtors as the 1996 Realtor of the Year at KAR&#39;s annual banquet, held Friday, Jan. 17, at the Hyatt Regency.
<P>   A committee of past award recipients chose Simpson, based on active participation in KAR, the Tennessee and National Associations of Realtors; his community service record; and the quality of his business relationships with clients and fellow KAR members.
<P>   Realtors also installed Dick Scarborough of Farragut as KAR&#39;s 1997 president and recognized 224 area Realtors for posting &#39;&#39;outstanding years&#39;&#39; with sales exceeding $1 million. 
<P>   Scarborough reported 6,946 Knoxville area homes were sold during 1996 at an average price of $117,113. That exceeds the average 1995 price of $110,718 for the 6,536 homes sold that year.
<P>   Scarborough, owner and president of AAIM Century 21 Real Estate Co. in Farragut, said lower interest rates helped boost 1996 home sales. Average home prices have risen steadily from $70,012 in 1986 and $94,786 in 1991, Scarborough said.
<P>   Simpson, a 1975 real-estate graduate of the University of Tennessee, has been active in both committee work and leadership positions within the association, and he was KAR&#39;s 1994 president. 
<P>   He served eight years on KAR&#39;s board of directors and six years on the Tennessee Association of Realtors board.
<P>   Simpson, 1996 president of the Tennessee Commercial and Investment Realtors, was elected 1997 vice president of the Tennessee Association of Realtors. 
<P>   A specialist in selling commercial and investment real estate, Simpson is a certified commercial investment member as designated by NAR&#39;s Commercial Investment Real Estate Institute.
<P>   Scarborough, president of AAIM Century 21 for 30 years, is a Niles, Ohio, native who was reared in Harriman, Tenn. 
<P>   Scarborough has served on the KAR Board, has chaired its committees, has served as three-term president of the East Tennessee Real Estate Brokers Council and has served on the National Brokers Communication Congress.
<P>   Other KAR officers installed Friday were B.J. Swinehart of RE/MAX Preferred Properties, president-elect; Rod Ferguson of RE/MAX Preferred Properties, vice president; and George Wallace of Coldwell Banker Wallace & Wallace, treasurer. Installed as directors were Jim Ford of Volunteer Realty, Al Gibson of Realty Executives and Michael Wood of Wood Realtors.
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<hr size=5>

