		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Women&#39;s expo set April 4-6</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">T</FONT>he 1997 Women Today Expo will bring more than 300 exhibitors, speakers, and food and fashion professionals to the Knoxville Convention/Exhibition Center April 4-6.
<P>   The show, geared to the interests and lifestyles of 1990s women, will feature a fashion and entertainment stage, a cooking school with hourly demonstrations, seminars and workshops on a wide range of topics, and exhibitors offering items for sale.
<P>   The Women Today Expo is sponsored by The News-Sentinel, Scripps Howard Cable TV Co. and WBIR-TV, Channel 10. For more information or to purchase booth space, call Lisa Duncan, 521-1885.
<P>
