<P><B>ALEXANDER, JACK ROY - </B>age 62, of LaFollette, passed away Thursday, January 16, 1997, at the University of Tennessee Medical Center, Knoxville. He was a member of the LaFollette Church of God, LaFollette Masonic Lodge #623, and Campbell County Shrine Club. Mr. Alexander was a 32nd Degree Mason and Shriner. He served 22 years as County Judge/Executive and was currently serving as County Commissioner. He was a graduate of LMU and received his master in finance at the University of Tennessee. Preceded in death by parents, James Roy and Minnie Pierce Alexander. Survivors: wife, Kathy Alexander, LaFollette; daughters and sons-in-law, Sheila and Steve Lawson, Knoxville, Jackie and Raymond Jackson, Jacksboro, Angie Alexander, LaFollette; grandchildren, Rachel and Samanatha Jackson. Funeral service 8 p.m. Sunday, January 19, at LaFollette Church of God, Rev. Kenneth Stephens officiating. Interment 10 a.m. Monday, January 20. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Sunday at LaFollette Church of God. Nephews and Commissioners will be pallbearers. Arrangements by Cross Funeral Home.
<P>
<P><B>BAYLESS, MARTHA EMMA - </B>age 80, of Halls, passed away January 16, 1997, at St. Mary&#39;s Medical Center. Member of Beaver Dam Baptist Church. Preceded in death by: husband, Charles A. Bayless. Survivors: daughter and son-in-law, Charlsie and Ronnie Hall; grandchildren, Kim and Kip Huston of Elliott City, Md., Rhonda and Herbert Holcomb of Rogersville and Michael Hall of Dunbarton, N.H.; five grandchildren; sisters, Leatha Wilkins of Knoxville and Retha Hankins of Knoxville. Family and friends will meet at Greenwood Cemetery, 2 p.m. Sunday for graveside service, Rev. Ralph Cox officiating. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Saturday at Mynatt&#39;s.
<P>
<P><B>BROWN, HELEN STARKEY - </B>passed away Thursday, January 16, 1997, at her West Knoxville home. Survived by: husband of 55 years, Joseph M. Brown, Sr.; son and daughter-in-law, Joseph M. and Jewel Brown, Jr., Knoxville; brother and sister-in-law, James Harry and Margaret Starkey; grandson, Jason Brown; several nieces and nephews. Private graveside service will be held Saturday, 2 p.m. at Highland Memorial Cemetery, R. David Lancaster officiating of First Cumberland Presbyteriand Church. Memorials may be made to the Med Centers Home Care Hospice Program. Arrangements by Highland Memorial Funeral Home, 5313 Kingston Pike, 588-0567.
<P>
<P>
<P><B>COLLINS, JAMES R. - </B>age 71, of Lenoir City, passed away early Friday morning, January 17, 1997, at the Loudon Health Care Center. He was a member of Central United Methodist Church. Retired from T.V.A. and O.R.N.L. He was a veteran of World War II, serving with the Marines. He was preceded in death by: sisters, Ruby Orr and Sue Miller. Survivors: wife, Mary Corum Collins; daughters and sons-in-law, Debbie and Tom Hackler of Ten Mile, Robyn and Jeff Longest of Clinton; stepdaughters, Libby Purdy of Lenoir City, Debbie Lankford of Chattanooga; grandchildren, Jennifer and Mary Beth Purdy of Lenoir City; brother, L.F. Collins of Kingsport; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 2 p.m. Sunday, Click Funeral Home Chapel, Rev. C. Mark Gooden officiating. Interment Lake View Cemetery with full military honors conducted by the U.S. Marine Corp. Pallbearers: Jackie Morton, Jim Monger, Ralph Fitzgerald, Dr. Walter Shea, Joe Malone, and Jim Finn. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Central United Methodist Church Memorial Fund, 201 B. Street, Lenoir City, TN 37771. The family will receive friends from 5-7 p.m. Saturday at Click Funeral Home, Lenoir City.
<P>
<P><B>COCHRAN, ANNA MAE &#39;&#39;GRANNY&#39;&#39; - </B>age 86, of Rockford died Friday, January 17, 1997, at Blount Memorial Hospital. She was a member of Lakeview Baptist Church, was preceded in death by her husband, Robert C. Cochran; sister, Mattie Weaver. Survivors include: her son, Bob Cochran; daughter Norma Payne; grandchildren, Ty Cochran and wife, Tami Cochran Rhines and husband, Fanny Clark and husband; great-grandchildren, Annette Rhines, Eric Rhines, and Derick Rhines; sisters, Eva Newberry and family, Sophia Norris and family; special friends, Wallace and Jean Thurman and family. Funeral service will be held at 2 p.m. Sunday in McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home Chapel with Rev. Gary Simerly and Rev. Tommy LeQuire officiating. The interment will follow in Sherwood Memorial Gardens. The family will receive friends from 1-2 p.m. Sunday at McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home.
