<P>h3804_0119
<P><B>BALLEW, BETTY J. ARNOLD - </B>age 69, went to be with the Heavenly Father on Thursday, January 16, 1997, after living over 21/2  years with lung and brain cancer. Mrs. Ballew worked as a cashier for Ramsey&#39;s Cafeteria until retiring approximately 31/2 years ago. Prior to that, she worked many years as cashier at the old &#39;&#39;Weaver&#39;s Cafeteria&#39;&#39; on North Broadway. She was a member of Lincoln Park Baptist Church and was an Eastern Star. Preceded in death by infant sister, Peggy Joyce Arnold; and sister, Carol Sue Arnold Strange; and father, Rufus Madison Arnold. She was also preceded in recent death of brother-in-law, Walter A. Horne of Whiting, Ind. Mrs. Ballew is survived by her mother, Ruby Giles Arnold; and she is survived by her two adult children, her son, Fred Kenneth (Ken) Ballew, Jr., and daughter-in-law, Patsy C. Pate Ballew; and her daughter, Patricia (Pat) Ballew Shackelford Mortorano and son-in-law, Patrick J. Mortorano. There are seven grandchildren: Scott Shackelford, Chance Ballew, Chase Ballew, Kelley Shackelford, Robert Mortorano, Karen Mortorano and Janelle Mortorano. Mrs. Ballew was divorced from Fred &#39;&#39;Kenneth&#39;&#39; Ballew, Sr. many years ago. Mrs. Ballew is survived by three sisters and one brother: brother, James Arnold and sister-in-law, Dorothy Padgett Arnold of Knoxville; surviving sisters are Mrs. W.A. (Jean &#39;&#39;Dude&#39;&#39; Arnold) Horne of Whiting, Ind., Mrs. Joan Arnold Hagan Bush (&#39;&#39;very close&#39;&#39; brother-in-law) O.D. &#39;&#39;Bubby&#39;&#39; Bush of Chattanooga, Tenn., Mrs. Mary Lou Arnold McGhee and brother-in-law, Dr. Jerry R. McGhee of Birmingham, Ala. Mrs. Ballew remained close friends with her &#39;&#39;sister-in-law,&#39;&#39; Mrs. John Barton (Viola) Clifton of Knoxville; favorite niece, Vicki Hagan of Chattanooga; many, many nieces and nephews. She will be sadly missed, but we are comforted knowing God needed another angel and she is now &#39;&#39;pain free&#39;&#39; and in a glorious place. Funeral service 10 a.m. Saturday at Stevens Chapel, Pastor Ted J. Ingram officiating. Interment Sherwood Memorial Gardens. Arrangements by Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
