<P>h3808_0121
<P><B>COLQUITT, FRANK - </B>born November 8, 1939 in Opelika, Ala. to the late Joe Nathan and Mae Fannie Golden Colquitt. He departed this life Wednesday, January 15, 1997, at Blount Memorial Hospital. Preceded in death by parents; brothers, Rev. J.L. and Carter Colquitt; sisters, Elvira Kennedy, Mary Butler, Annie Sheadrick and Daisy C. Burnett. Survivors: Lelia Colquitt; son,  Bradford (Brad) Davenport; several stepchildren, the Robinson, Jackson, Russell and Adamson Families; sisters, Pearl (David) Marion, Jewel Equhart, Detroit, Mich.; sister-in-law, Essie M. Colquitt; brothers, Willie (Dorothy) Colquitt, Lover Joe Colquitt of Toledo, Ohio; brothers-in-law, Jessie Sheadrick, Robert Butler, Gad Kelly; 20 grandchildren; six great-grandchildren; a host of nieces, nephews, cousins, aunts and friends. The family will receive friends on Sunday, January 19, 1997, at Unity Mortuary Chapel from 3-3:30 p.m. with funeral to follow. Rev. James Davis  officiating. Interment on Tuesday, January 21, 1997, at 11 a.m. at New Gray Cemetery. The family will be at the home of Mrs. Betty Robinson, 2323 Parkview Ave. Arrangements by Unity Mortuary.
