	<title>Symposium kicks off weekend&#39;s King celebration</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 17, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Symposium kicks off weekend&#39;s King celebration</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">A</FONT> youth symposium Saturday at Austin-East High School is part of this weekend&#39;s celebration of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.&#39;s birthday.
<P>   &#39;&#39;Pride and Peace: Positive Pathways to Community&#39;&#39; is the focus of the annual Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. Youth Symposium, to be held from 8:30 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. Saturday at Austin-East.
<P>   The symposium is free, and lunch will be provided. Sam Kirk, CEO of CES Associates in Nashville, will be the keynote speaker.
<P>   Other activities planned:
<P>   * The local King Commemoration Commission&#39;s annual parade will begin at 4:30 p.m. Sunday, Jan. 19 at Tabernacle Baptist Church, 2137 Martin Luther King Jr. Ave.
<P>   The parade will proceed along MLK to the Five Points intersection and down to the Burlington Community.
<P>   A memorial service will follow the parade at 6 p.m. at Greater Warner Tabernacle AME Zion Church, 3800 Martin Luther King Jr. Ave.
<P>   * WSJK/WKOP-TV will present a tribute to Dr. King from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. Monday, Jan. 20.
<P>   Benjamin Hooks, retired executive director of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People, will be the keynote speaker.
<P>   * The University of Tennessee&#39;s Black Cultural Programming Committee will sponsor a unity march and program highlighting the works of Dr. King on Monday, Jan. 20.
<P>   The march will begin at the Torchbearer statue on the corner of Yale Avenue and Volunteer Boulevard on the UT campus. The following program will be held in the University Center auditorium.
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
