	<title>Knoxville back on annexation track</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 16, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Knoxville back on annexation track</B></font><FONT SIZE="-1"><BR> Unity vote moratorium over; council OKs bids to add 14 tracts</FONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I>By Jim Balloch, News-Sentinel staff writer</I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">K</FONT>noxville is back in the annexation business.
<P>   In its first such action in more than a year, City Council on Tuesday gave unanimous first reading approval to the annexation of 13 parcels of county property whose owners requested to be taken into the city.
<P>   Council also approved the annexation of a 14th tract -- the Maxey&#39;s Boat Dock property on Maloney and Ginn roads in South Knox County -- whose owners have since withdrawn their annexation request.
<P>    Mayor Victor Ashe said Wednesday the parcel remains targeted and will be on the Jan. 28 council agenda for second reading.
<P>    The parcel &#39;&#39;is at the end of an existing street that is in the city, and it is off Alcoa Highway, (all of which) is within the city,&#39;&#39; he said.
<P>   Bill Maxey, who owns one-third of the six-acre tract, said the annexation was requested when a sale of the land to a developer was pending. The sale fell through. Maxey said he and his two sisters are reconsidering the annexation.
<P>   &#39;&#39;We&#39;ve been talking it over,&#39;&#39; he said. &#39;&#39;We feel like maybe it&#39;s not the right thing to do, but we have not made a final decision yet.&#39;&#39;
<P>  Maxey&#39;s Boat Dock was once a popular docking and concessions area. There are no longer gasoline or concession sales, but boats are still docked there.
<P>    At a hearing Wednesday, some county residents who live near the site expressed concern or opposition.
<P>    There were no annexations during 1996 because of a moratorium established by Ashe, at the request of County Executive Tommy Schumpert, to minimize the impact of annexation issues on the proposal to merge city and county governments.
<P>   Now that unification failed, the city &#39;&#39;will be pursuing growth through annexation,&#39;&#39; Ashe said. &#39;&#39;The annexations will be at the owner&#39;s request by and large, but that is not an iron-clad rule.&#39;&#39;
<P>   Schumpert said his office will try to learn from people who are requesting annexation &#39;&#39;the exact reasons they want to be in the city, what services we&#39;re not offering that they would prefer.&#39;&#39;
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<hr size=5>

