<P><B>BAILEY, ROBERT A. - </B>of Fountain City, passed away Tuesday afternoon at St. Mary&#39;s Medical Center. Member of Arlington Church of Christ where he was a deacon, secretary and treasurer. Retired after 37 years as supervisor of K.U.B. Power Division. Was a major in the Army Corps of Engineers during World War II, serving in Africa and Europe. Survived by wife of 55 years, Rubye B. Bailey of Fountain City; daughter and son-in-law, Nancy and Jim Loy of Pensacola, Fla.; son and daughter-in-law, Michael and Beth Bailey of Senatobia, Miss.; grandchildren, Mary and Meg Bailey, Jamie and Bryan Loy; sisters, Fayren Pitts, Neva Harvey, Jane Morris and Charlotte Joyner, all of Henderson, Tenn.; brother, Lance Bailey of Henderson, Tenn.; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 3 p.m. Thursday at Gentry-Griffey Chapel, Mr. Dana Slingluff officiating, assisted by Dr. Tom Drinnen and Mr. Harold Scott. Interment will follow in Lynnhurst Cemetery. Pallbearers: Lyle Randall, Aubrey Cowan, Gene Majors, Charlie Shipe, Frank Reagan, Jerry Fitto, John Ramsey, David Tiller. Honorary pallbearers: Warren Hancock, Truett Lindner, Bill McQuaig, Dan Trent, Rasho Winget, Owen Hornby, Charles Owens and Fred Gilliam. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the Arlington Church of Christ, 2206 Tecoa, Knoxville, TN 37917. Arrangements by Gentry-Griffey Chapel.
