<P><B>TUCKER, JENNIE FAYE - </B>age 77, of Clinton, Tenn., passed away Tuesday, January 14, 1997, at Methodist Medical Center. She was preceded in death by parents, Ed and Lottie Brummett; husband, Earvin Tucker; daughter, Emma Jean Longmire; brothers, Millard and Paul Brummett. She is survived by grandchildren, Brenda and husband, Clifford Early of Kodak, Tenn., Angela and husband, Tim Sheffler of Oak Ridge, Tenn., Michael and wife, Phyllis Longmire of Clinton, Tenn. and Dean and wife, Beverly Longmire of Bono, Arkansas; 11 great-grandchildren; special nephew, George Brummett of Clinton, Tenn. Funeral services will be conducted at 2 p.m. Friday, January 17, 1997, at the Holley-Gamble Funeral Home Chapel. Rev. Anna Mae Denton and Rev. Dennis Shipley officiating. Interment will be at Robbins Cemetery, Clinton, Tenn. The family will receive friends from 7 to 9 p.m. Thursday, January 16, 1997, at Holley-Gamble Funeral Home Chapel, Clinton.
<P>
<P><B>WADE, DOROTHY ANN (LLOYD) - </B>age 75, of Powell, went home to be with Jesus on Monday, January 13, 1997. She was a member of First Baptist Church of Powell. Preceded in death by her husband, William E. Wade. Survived by daughter and son-in-law, Susan L. and Rev. Kenneth Byrd of Clinton; sons and daughters-in-law, William Barry and Judy Wade, Knoxville, Rev. David L. and Shannon Wade of Elizabethton; brother and sister-in-law, (Ret. Col.) E.A. and Wynn Lloyd, Canton, Conn.; sister and brother-in-law, Jeanne and Hugh Holt, Rome, Ga.; grandchildren, Don Wade, Cheryl Murphy, DeAnna Wade, Mariah Byrd, Micah Wade, Matthew Wade, Bethany Wade; great-granddaughter, Ashlee Murphy; aunt and uncle, Bertha and R.S. McEver of Greenville, S.C.; several cousins, nieces and nephews. Funeral service 1 p.m. Thursday at Gentry-Griffey Chapel with interment to follow at Lynnhurst Cemetery, Rev. Phil Jones officiating. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the American Cancer Society or the Gideons. Arrangements by Gentry-Griffey Chapel.
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
