<head>
	<title>Townsend man pleads guilty to federal witness tampering</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 15, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Townsend man pleads guilty to federal witness tampering</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I>By Randy Kenner, News-Sentinel staff writer</I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">A</FONT> Townsend man pleaded guilty Tuesday to federal witness tampering in connection with the 1996 beating of the brother of a government informant in Sevier County.
<P>   Ronald Edward Buchanan, 45, also pleaded guilty to using a firearm during a crime of violence in connection with the June 10 incident and to a count of distributing cocaine in 1994.
<P>   Three other charges were dropped as part of a plea agreement between Buchanan and federal authorities.
<P>   U.S. District Judge James Jarvis asked Buchanan, also known as Eddie Buck, if he understood and agreed with the plea agreement and the factual basis describing the offenses.
<P>   &#39;&#39;Yeah, I understand it, your honor,&#39;&#39; Buchanan told Jarvis before adding, &#39;&#39;My lawyer&#39;s gone over it with me, too.&#39;&#39;
<P>   Buchanan and Randy Alan McClure, 27, of Sevierville allegedly broke into the Sevier County home of Joel and Agnes McCarter at gunpoint on June 10 because McCarter&#39;s brother, Johnny, was testifying against at least McClure.
<P>   Johnny McCarter cooperated with authorities in a 1994 drug investigation involving McClure and had testified against him in Sevier County and was going to testify before a federal grand jury.
<P>   According to testimony by Joel McCarter, he was beaten by McClure while Buchanan held a shotgun on him and his wife. He said he was subsequently  dragged from the house to McClure&#39;s truck.
<P>   &#39;&#39;The defendant (and his co-defendant, Randy McClure) forced Joel McCarter into a vehicle and threatened to kill him since they could not find his brother, Johnny McCarter,&#39;&#39; states a factual basis prepared by Assistant U.S. Attorney Mary Aubry and signed by Buchanan.
<P>   According to the document, Buchanan repeatedly struck Joel McCarter with the butt of a 12-gauge shotgun while the three men drove about a mile from the McCarter residence.
<P>   At that point McCarter was pushed from the truck and struck several more times by Buchanan before being left on the road, according to court documents and the testimony of McCarter.
<P>   In addition to pleading guilty to conspiring to use intimidation and physical force to delay or prevent Johnny McCarter&#39;s testimony, Buchanan also pleaded guilty to selling Johnny McCarter about a gram of cocaine on Aug. 22, 1994.
<P>   According to court statements, he faces a sentencing range of 71/2 to 81/3 years in prison.
<P>   McClure&#39;s case is still pending.
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
