<head>
	<title>Suspect in burglary ring captured</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 15, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Suspect in burglary ring captured</B></font><FONT SIZE="-1"><BR> 3 others caught earlier; string of break-ins covers wide area</FONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">C</FONT>LINTON -- An Anderson County man alleged to be a member of a gang that has committed burglaries in at least 10 East Tennessee counties was arrested early Tuesday after eluding officers since Saturday.
<P>   Johnnie Mack Wilson, 30, of Briceville was arrested at a mobile home near Oliver Springs about 3 a.m., according to Mark Whaley, information officer for the Anderson County Sheriff&#39;s Department. 
<P>   Wilson, Charles R. &#39;&#39;Chucky&#39;&#39; Daugherty, 24; Chris &#39;&#39;Skeeter Bill&#39;&#39; Moser, 19, and Deena Leinart, 22, are charged with breaking into two houses in Meigs County and two in Roane County on Saturday. 
<P>   All four are suspects in at least two and possibly more burglaries in Claiborne County, including a Jan. 2 break-in at the home of a Tennessee Highway Patrol trooper in the Lone Mountain community, officials said.
<P>   Claiborne County Chief Deputy Kelly Anders said police initially suspected the trooper&#39;s home, which was &#39;&#39;severely trashed&#39;&#39; in the burglary, had been targeted because it is an officer&#39;s. 
<P>   Interviews with the suspects revealed however, that the break-in was random, Anders said.
<P>   &#39;&#39;It was after they got inside and saw pictures and other things to indicate they were in a trooper&#39;s house that they apparently decided to trash it because it was a cop&#39;s,&#39;&#39; Anders said.
<P>   The three men are all from Briceville. Leinart is from Halls.
<P>   A Meigs County man saw the three running from his home Saturday afternoon. They fled into some woods, but Leinart was arrested when she came to the residence to pick up the three men.
<P>   Officers said the three stole a church van and drove it to Briceville where it was found and a search started. Daughtery and Moser were arrested Monday afternoon. Wilson fled from officers on an all-terrain vehicle and fled along mining roads in the mountains.
<P>   Whaley said officers got an anonymous telephone call that Wilson was at the mobile home. He said officers surrounded the home, and Wilson surrendered without incident.
<P> 
<P>   
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
