<P><B>ATCHLEY, DALE FRED (TODY), JR. - </B>age 49, of Knoxville, passed away Tuesday, January 14, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Hospital. He was preceded in death by his father, Dale Fred Atchley, Sr.; mother, Nora Nuchols Atchley; and sister, Joyce Green. Survived by wife, Sue Hayes Atchley; daughter, Elizabeth Atchley; step-daughters, Faye, Teresa and Kelly; step-sons, Jimmy, Gary, Sam and Patrick Hayes; step-daughter, Linda Tipes, all of Portland, Ind.; sisters, Vickie Bell, Charlotte Cinnamon and Sharon Atkins; special grandchildren and several special aunts and uncles. Family and friends will meet 9:45 a.m. Thursday at Holly Hills Memorial Park for 10 a.m. graveside service, Rev. Hubert Troutman officiating. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Wednesday at Holly Hills South Funeral Home, 573-7300.
<P>
<P><B>BAILEY, ROBERT A. - </B>of Fountain City, passed away Tuesday afternoon at St. Mary&#39;s Medical Center. Member of Arlington Church of Christ where he was a deacon, secretary and treasurer. Retired after 37 years as supervisor of K.U.B. Power Division. Was a major in the Army Corps of Engineers during World War II, serving in Africa and Europe. Survived by wife of 55 years, Rubye B. Bailey of Fountain City; daughter and son-in-law, Nancy and Jim Loy of Pensacola, Fla.; son and daughter-in-law, Michael and Beth Bailey of Senatobia, Miss.; grandchildren, Mary and Meg Bailey, Jamie and Bryan Loy; sisters, Fayren Pitts, Neva Harvey, Jane Morris and Charlotte Joyner, all of Henderson, Tenn.; brother, Lance Bailey of Henderson, Tenn.; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 3 p.m. Thursday at Gentry-Griffey Chapel, Mr. Dana Slingluff officiating, assisted by Dr. Tom Drinnen and Mr. Harold Scott. Interment will follow in Lynnhurst Cemetery. Pallbearers: Lyle Randall, Aubrey Cowan, Gene Majors, Charlie Shipe, Frank Reagan, Jerry Fitto, John Ramsey, David Tiller. Honorary pallbearers: Warren Hancock, Truett Lindner, Bill McQuaig, Dan Trent, Rasho Winget, Owen Hornby, Charles Owens and Fred Gilliam. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the Arlington Church of Christ, 2206 Tecoa, Knoxville, TN 37917. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at Gentry-Griffey Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>BARNARD, EDNA DEATHERAGE - </B>age 95, of Kingston, died Monday, January 13, 1997. The body is at Kyker Funeral Home, Kingston, where the family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Thursday. Funeral 8 p.m. Thursday in Kyker Chapel with the Rev. John Rhodes officiating. Burial 11 a.m. Friday at Bethel Cemetery at Fairview.
<P>
<P><B>FOUST, CONNIE CAROL (WILSON) MASSENGILL -</B> age 49, of Clinton, passed away January 13, 1997, at the Methodist Medical Center. She was a life long resident of Lake City area. She was a faithful member of the Lake City Church of Christ. She was preceded in death by: mother, Barbara A. (Braden) Wilson; brother, Ellis Eugene Wilson; two sisters, Joyce Wilson and Francis Wilson. She is survived by father and stepmother, Gilbert E. and Winnie Wilson of Briceville; four sons, James Edward Massengill, Jr. of Illinois, Andrew M.  Massengill of Illinois, Louie A. Massengill of Clinton, Tenn. and Danny Jason Foust of Clinton, Tenn.; daughter, Deborah Sue Massengill of Clinton, Tenn.; brothers, Eddie Braden of Loudon, Bobby Braden of Indiana; sisters, Linda Lydick of Lake City, Jamie Braden of Georgia, Julie M. House and Lillian McClain, both of Knoxville; stepsister, Lorene Mullins of Knoxville; three grandchildren; three great-grandchildren; several nieces and nephews and a host of other relatives and friends. Funeral services will be Thursday, January 16, 1997, at the Lake City Church of Christ with Minister Tim Medford officiating. The family will receive friends from 1 until 8 p.m. in the chapel of Martin Funeral Home of Lake City, Wednesday, January 15, 1997. Interment to follow the service on Thursday in the Oak Grove Cemetery in Lake City. Martin Funeral Home of Lake City in charge of arrangements.
<P>
<P><B>GALYON, RALPH E. - </B>age 69, of Halls, died 3:19 a.m. Tuesday, January 14, 1997, at St. Mary&#39;s Medical Center. He was a member of Salem Baptist Church. Retired from T.V.A. after 18 years of service. Preceded in death by parents, Clarence E. and Jerushia Galyon. Survivors: wife, Betty R. Galyon, Halls; son and daughter-in-law, Stanley D. and Geneva Galyon, Knoxville; son, Terry L. Galyon, Halls; sister and brother-in-law, Sarah and Marvin Jortner, Memphis; numerous nieces, nephews and close friends. Family and friends will meet 12:45 p.m. Thursday at McCloud Family Cemetery for a 1 p.m. graveside service, Rev. John Holland officiating. Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway, in charge.
