<P><B>GARDNER, HENRY L. &#39;&#39;HANK&#39;&#39; - </B>age 62, of 269 County Rd. 285, Niota, passed away Monday, January 13, 1997, at the family home. He was preceded in death by his parents, Albert and Opal Gardner; brother, Leroy Gardner and wife, Lida Lee Murray Gardner. He was retired from the U.S. Air Force as a Tec. Sgt. having served from 1951-1971. He also worked almost 20 years for Hay-Morris and Sutton Construction Co. Survivors: daughters and sons-in-law, Diane and Joe Trotter of Sweetwater, Denise and Tommy Powell, Debbie and Joel Lewis, all of Niota; son, Ken Gardner of San Antonio, Texas; sister, Alberta Von Der Lieth of Sioux City, Iowa; nine grandchildren; four great-grandchildren; several nieces and nephews; special friend, W.B. Martin of Sweetwater. The body is at Kyker Funeral Home, Sweetwater, where the family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Thursday. Graveside service and interment 10 a.m. Friday in the Midway Church of God Cemetery with Rev. Clayton Dunsmore officiating. Military honors will be provided by the Sweetwater VFW Gold Post 5156.
