<P><B>GRAHAM, TRULA M. - </B>age 87, of Knoxville, passed away January 13, 1997, at Baptist Hospital. Born in Union County, Tenn. on September 14, 1909. Member of Sevier Heights Baptist Church. Preceded in death by: her husband, Charles E. Graham; sister, Queener Coppock, Maynardville; and brother, Trola Graham of Michigan. Survivors: children and spouses, Floyd and Sharon Kay Graham of Weldon, Calif., Lloyd and Angela Graham, Knoxville, and Daisy Graham of Knoxville; grandchildren and spouses, Mike and Sheree Graham, Knoxville, Billy and Tammy Graham of Fairfield, Calif., Shawn and Tammy Graham, Gray, Tenn., David and Yvette Anderson, Powell; great-grandchildren, Michael Graham, Meridieth Graham of Knoxville, Hannah Graham and Fairfield, Calif., Danielle Anderson, and Adam Crabtree of Powell; sisters and brothers, Lillie Summers, Iowa, Lasco &#39;&#39;Doc&#39;&#39; Coppock, Maynardville, and Arzo Coppock of Knoxville; several nieces and nephews. Family and friends will meet at Weaver&#39;s at 9:45 a.m. Wednesday to proceed to New Loyston Memorial Gardens, for an 11 a.m. graveside service, The Rev. Lester Mullins officiating. Arrangements by Weaver Funeral Home.
