<P><B>GRUBB, EDNA C. - </B>age 81, of Corryton, died 1:34 p.m. Sunday, January 12, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Regional Medical Center. Member of Corryton Baptist Church. Retired from the Standard Knitting Mills. Preceded in death by brothers, Earl, Bill and Clifton Cooper; half brother, Bob McKelvey. Survivors: husband of 63 years, Ross Grubb, Corryton; daughter and son-in-law, Ann and Paul Pierce, Knoxville; grandchildren, Ronald and Steve Atkins, Kathy Thornhill; great-grandchildren, Chris and Jonathan Atkins, Tonya and Nicole Thornhill; great-great-grandchildren, Timothy and Sera Atkins, all of Knoxville; sisters, Katherine Harris, Richmond, Va., Vivian Cantrell, Los Angeles, Calif.; sister-in-law, Margaret E. Cooper, Knoxville; half-brothers and sisters-in-laws, Reed and Gerry McKelvey, Corryton, Charles and Frankie McKelvey, Nashville; half sisters and brothers-in-law, Jeanette and James Golden, Corryton, Sammy and Gene Black, Knoxville; half sister, Dorothy Howard, Las Vegas, Nev.; several nieces and nephews. Family and friends will meet 12:45 p.m. Friday at the entrance to Lynnhurst Cemetery for a 1 p.m. graveside service, Rev. Doyle Davis officiating. Pallbearers: Julian Weaver, Berlye Clapp, Clun Longmire, Claxton Zachary, Joe Longmire, George Cantrell and Chris Atkins. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Thursday at Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
