<P><B>HARBIN, MRS. RUTH E. - </B>age 79,  of Knoxville, died 1:55 a.m. Tuesday, January 14, 1997, at Fort Sanders Regional Medical Center. Member of First Baptist Church. Survivors: husband, Henry P. (Cotton) Harbin; daughter, Judy Dodge, both of Knoxville; son and daughter-in-law, Steven and Marie Harbin, Fort Lauderdale, Fla.; son, Dennis Harbin, Tampa, Fla.; eight grandchildren; eight great-grandchildren. Funeral service 8 p.m. Wednesday at Stevens Chapel, Dr. David Hull, Dr. Jerry Seale, Rev. Dave Ward and Rev. Bob Money officiating. Family and friends will meet at Tennessee Veterans&#39; Cemetery, Lyons View Pike at 11:45 a.m. Thursday for a 12 noon graveside service and interment. Pallbearers: Greg Dodge, Herb Dodge, John Cate, Steve Williams, Steven Harbin, Jr., Larry Harbin and Ellis Cameron. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to First Baptist Church, 510 W. Main St., Knoxville, TN 37902. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
