<P><B>HENSLEY, ROBERT LEROY - </B>age 83, of Knoxville, went to be with the Lord Monday, January 13, 1997, at U.T. Hospital. He attended Knoxville Baptist Tabernacle, veteran of World War II, serving in the U.S. Army. He retired from Lakeshore Hospital. Preceded in death by wife, Goldie Fraker Hensley; mother and sister and grandson, Jacky Hensley. Survivors: daughters and sons-in-law, Patsy and Cleo Todd, Bobbie and Ed Brown, Debbie and Ernest Underwood, Linda Stevens Drake; sons and daughters-in-law, Jack and Joann Hensley, Don and Marie Hensley, Larry and Darlene Hensley, Gary and Peggy Hensley, David Hensley, Steve Hensley; 24 grandchildren; ten great-grandchildren. Funeral service 10 a.m. Thursday, Rose Chapel, Dr. Bob Bevington and Rev. Albert Barlow officiating. Interment in Lynnhurst Cemetery. Pallbearers: Don Mullins, Bill Russell, Jim Crowley, Jake Huffaker, Ray Wise. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Wednesday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>HICKS, GARNETTE JEWEL - </B>age 79, of Sweetwater, passed away Tuesday, January 14, 1997, at 1:20 a.m. at the Fort Sanders Park West Medical Center, Knoxville, after a brief illness. She was preceded in death by her parents, Haywood L. and Elizbeth Bright Hicks; brother, Frances Hicks; and a sister, Helen Hicks. She was a member of the First Baptist Church of Sweetwater. She was retired from Sweetwater Hosiery Mill. Survivors: sisters and brothers-in-law, Kathleen Clayton, Margie and Ernest McAmis; brother-in-law, James W. Hicks, all of Sweetwater; several nieces and nephews. The body is at Kyker Funeral Home, Sweetwater, where the family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday. Graveside service and interment 11 a.m. Thursday in the West View Cemetery with Rev. Gary Baker officiating.
<P>
<P><B>HOWARD, TERRI DENISE - </B>age 40, of Maryville, passed away Tuesday morning, January 14, 1997, at U.T. Medical Center. Survivors: husband, Edward L. Howard; daughter, Sydney Howard; son, Austin Howard, all of Maryville; mother and step-father, Dorothy and Bobby Roach of Ohio; brother, Charles Derifield of Indiana; grandparents, Divers and Ema Gene Dray of Ohio; several cousins, nieces and nephews. Family and friends will meet at Clark&#39;s Grove Cemetery at 3 p.m. Thursday for graveside service and interment, Rev. Charlie Allmon officiating. Friends may call at their convenience from 10 a.m. to 2:30 p.m. Thursday at Miller Funeral Home, Maryville.
