<P>
<P><B>HURT, CHARLES DAVID - </B>passed away Monday, January 13, 1997, at his home in Pittman Center. He was born in Paris, Tenn. and was a resident of Rogersville and Johnson City, Tenn. prior to moving to the Pittman Center area. Mr. Hurt was retired from First National Bank of Gatlinburg and was a member of Hills Creek Baptist Church. He was preceded in death by his parents, Walter and Nellie Bishop Hurt of Paris, Tenn.; brothers, Hugh and Bishop Hurt. Survivors: wife, Faye Hurt; daughter and son-in-law, Lois and Bill Fortenberry of Kingsport; son and daughter-in-law, Dan and Nancy Hurt of Toana, Va.; grandchildren, Amy, Susan and Kathryn Fortenberry, Christina Hurt; sisters, Elizabeth Parrish, Mary Ruth Perry, Paris, Tenn.; brothers,  Gilbert Hurt of Chattanooga, Paul Hurt of Daytona Beach, Fla. The family will receive friends 6-7 Wednesday in the East Chapel of Atchley Funeral Home with funeral service to follow at 7 p.m. Rev. Melvin Carr and Rev. Jim White officiating. Interment 10 a.m. Thursday at Smoky Mountain Memory Gardens. Atchley Funeral Home in charge.
<P>
<P><B>MABRY, DR. RONALD H. - </B>age 51, of Knoxville, died 10:45 p.m. Sunday at UT Medical Center. He was owner of Garden Chiropractic Center. He was of the Presbyterian faith. Preceded in death by father, William Mabry. Survivors: wife (whom he loved more than life its self) Vickie S. Mabry; sons, Kent Mabry, Lance Mabry; granddaughter, Jordan McKenzie Anderson; mother, Bobbie Mabry; brother, Gary Mabry, all of Knoxville. Dr. Mabry&#39;s family wished to thank his many friends and patients over the past 27 years for their concern and many prayers. Family and friends will meet at the entrance to Greenwood Cemetery at 10:45 a.m. Wednesday for a 11 a.m. committal service and entombment. Rev. Mark Kitts and Rev. Leonard Turner officiating. Pallbearers: Dr. Ron Turner, Marty Bass, Ed Bailey, Harold Elkins, Dr. John McLaughlin, Dr. Larry Wolfe. Honorary pallbearers: Dr. Bill Cawrse, Roger Mink, Dudley Taylor, David Jones, Lori Fleishman, Jess Campbell, Dr. Carl Don Mabry, Dr. Gary Spiegleman, Bob Holt, P.G. Hibben, B.J. Harris. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the American Cancer Society, 871 Weisgarber Road, Knoxville, Tenn. 37909 or to the Retarded Citizen&#39;s Association of Knox County, 3000 N. Central, Knoxville, Tennessee 37917. Arrangements by Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
