<head>
	<title>Buffett tickets to be rationed</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 14, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Buffett tickets to be rationed</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><B>Jimmy Buffett </B>fans won&#39;t need to camp out in freezing weather to get good tickets for Buffett&#39;s March 1 concert at Thompson-Boling Arena. The tickets will go on sale at 9 a.m. Saturday at the arena and at most Tickets Unlimited outlets.
<P>   However, as has become the arena&#39;s custom for fast-selling concerts, a lottery will be held for the first 300 spaces in the ticket line. To qualify for one of those spaces, fans must go to the arena between noon and 7 p.m. Thursday or 8 a.m. and 7 p.m. Friday to get a wristband numbered 1 to 300.
<P>   Each participant must have valid I.D.; there is a limit of one wristband per person. Those with wristbands should be at Thompson-Boling by 7:30 a.m. Saturday, when a number will be drawn at random. The person with that wristband number will be first in line; all those with numbers greater than the drawn number will line up in sequence. The person bearing the number 1 will take a place in line behind number 300, and those with numbers higher than 1 will line up in sequence.
<P>    Participants must show the same identification on Saturday as they had shown when they received the wristband.
<P>    The lottery will be held only at Thompson-Boling Arena. Phone sales and on-site sales at other Tickets Unlimited outlets will also begin at 9 a.m. Tickets are $38.50 down to $16, and a limit of 10 tickets per person is expected.
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
