<P><B>BEBERGAL, DAVID - </B>age 79, of Knoxville, passed away at approximately 9:15 a.m. Sunday morning at Ft. Sanders Park West Regional Medical Center after a lengthy battle with cancer. He was born in 1917, in Charleston, S.C., where he lived before moving to Knoxville in the early &#39;40s. He was a longstanding member of Heska Amuna Synagogue and a member in good standing for 50 years in the Scottish Rite. Mr. Bebergal was a past general manager of the original General Products Corp. on Gay St. He later worked with Carlyle and Co. and Jewelry Box in Maryville and West Town Mall as manager. Preceded in death by parents, Esther and Samuel Bebergal. Survivors: wife of 50 years, Reva Jane Gurwin Bebergal; son, Steven Jay; daughter and son-in-law, Helene and Jay Markus of Memphis; grandchildren, Aaron Ross and Joshua Ben; several nieces and nephews including Pessa Brody and Esther Webster of Knoxville, and Harry Goldberg of Roanoke Island; several nieces and cousins from Columbus, Ohio; and special sister-in-law, Gladys Caller of Florida. Family and friends will meet for graveside services 2 p.m. Tuesday, January 14, 1997, at New Jewish Cemetery on Keith and Glenn Sts., Rabbi Shlomo Levine officiating. Active pallbearers: Bart Brody, Jerry Miller, Harold Shersky, Norbert Slovis, Gilbert Levinson, Zeke Freemin, Richard Keen, Jerome Salomone. Honorary pallbearers: Harold Brown, Monte Abrams, Monte Miller, Isadore Abrams, Dr. Haraf, Barry Wolf, Al Merlin, Sam Abrams, Lawrence Abrams, Irv Russoto, Charles Coffin, Leonard Shersky, Bill Noelton, Jeff Siegel, Phil Gurwin and Doug Binkley. In lieu of flowers, please make donations to Heska Amuna Synagogue or Knoxville Cancer Society. Arrangements by Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>BINGHAM, GLEN F. - </B>age 80, of Knoxville, formerly of Dandridge, passed away Sunday afternoon, January 12, 1997, at U.T. Medical Center, Knoxville. He was a retired farmer and was of the Baptist faith. Funeral service 11 a.m. Wednesday at Farrar Dandridge Chapel with Rev. Ernest Condee and Rev. Mike Seager officiating. Interment in Piedmont Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Tuesday evening at Farrar Funeral Home, Dandridge.
