<P><B>BOGGS, RUTH BRIDGES - </B>age 56, formerly of Elk Valley, Tenn., 815 Mariner Cove, Eaton, Ohio, passed away on January 12, 1997, at Fort Hamilton Hospital in Hamilton, Ohio, after a short battle with lung cancer. She was a member of Sugar Valley Methodist Church. After 31 years of dedicated service she retired as an Avon District Manager from Avon Products, Inc. She was the daughter of the late Everett and Ella Bridges. She is survived by her loving husband, Tinsley (Lee) Boggs of Eaton, Ohio; two loving and adoring daughters, Joy Snyder and husband, Wayne of Fairfield, Ohio, Kathy Clapp and husband, Steve of Eaton, Ohio; one step-daughter, Annette Ballard and husband, Randy of Indianapolis, Ind.; three grandchildren, Jessica Snyder, Morgan and Jordan Clapp; one step-grandchild, Gabriel Ballard; two brothers, James B. Bridges and wife, Mary of Virginia Beach, Va. and Everette Bridges, Jr. and wife, Elizabeth of Morristown, Tenn.; one sister, Mary Kathern (Kitty) Miller and husband, Richard of Oneida, Tenn.; mother-in-law, Mae Boggs of Eaton, Ohio and several nieces, nephews, aunts, uncles and cousins; also many loving and supportive friends. The family will receive friends at Girton-Schmidt and Boucher Funeral Home, Eaton, Ohio, on January 14, 1997, from 6 p.m. until 9 p.m. Funeral services will be at the Girton Funeral Home,  January 15, 1997 at 2 p.m. with Rev. Randy Ballard and Pastor Ken Barton officiating. The body will lie in state one hour from 10 a.m. to 11 a.m. at Elk Fork Baptist Church in Elk Valley, Tenn. on January 16, 1997, with a brief memorial service followed by burial in the Valley View Cemetery in Elk Valley, Tenn., in Campbell County. West-Murley Funeral Home, Oneida, Tenn., in charge of local arrangements.
