<P><B>BRYANT, CHARLES ARTHUR - </B>age 71, of Gatlinburg, died Monday, January 6, 1997, at the Baptist Hospital of East Tennessee, after an extended illness. He was a Navy Veteran of World War II, and of the Baptist faith. He was preceded in death by: his father, George Ward Bryant; and son, Scott Ward Bryant. Survivors: wife, Julia Bryant; stepmother, Mary Bryant; sons, Mark Bryant, Darrell Beaman; daughter, Judy Webb; beloved grandchildren, Danielle Bryant, Taylor Bryant, Christopher Beaman, Jarrod Webb; son-in-law, Wyatt Webb; daughters-in-law, Dyan Bryant, Paula Beaman; niece, Tracy Schaefer; nephew, Bret Schaefer; brother-in-law, Don Schaefer. Graveside service and interment was Wednesday, January 8, 1997, in Glades Cemetery, Rev. Ben Whitted officiated. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the American Diabetes Association. Arrangements by Atchley Funeral Home, Sevierville.
