<html>
<head>
	<title>ET Briefs</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 13, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>ET Briefs</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><h3>Several departments join search for three suspects </h3>
<P>
<P>
<P>   Three Anderson County men wanted in connection with a rash of burglaries may have stolen a church van Sunday as they continued to elude capture, Roane County officials said.
<P>   According to authorities, the suspects, all of Briceville, are Johnnie Mack Wilson, 30, described as a white male, 6-feet 1-inch tall, 180 pounds, with brown hair and blue eyes; Charles R. &#39;&#39;Chucky&#39;&#39; Daugherty, 24, a white male, 5-feet 10-inches, 190 pounds, brown hair and blue eyes; and Chris &#39;&#39;Skeeter Bill&#39;&#39; Moser, 19.
<P>   Roane County authorities believe the men may be in Anderson County, though a multicounty search continues.
<P>   Following a burglary at a Roane County residence Saturday, the three suspects fled into the woods near the Meigs and Roane county line, according to a report from Roane County Sheriff David Haggard. Their alleged accomplice, Deena Leinart, was arrested Saturday after she attempted to flee in a car. She is being held in the Anderson County Jail.
<P>   RCSD dispatcher Doug Cook said the men stole a van from Shiloh Baptist Church early Sunday morning. Authorities discovered the van later that morning near Briceville.
<P>   Haggard said officials from Roane, Meigs, Anderson and Morgan counties have joined the search.
<P>    RCSD Det. Linda Booth said the men may also be responsible for several recent home burglaries in Anderson, Claiborne, Grainger, Morgan and Roane counties.
<P>
<P>
<P><h3>Unidentified body found in Campbell house fire ruins</h3> 
<P>
<P>
<P>   CARYVILLE -- Campbell County Sheriff&#39;s Department detectives struggled Sunday to determine the identity and cause of death for a body discovered in the charred remains of a Caryville house.
<P>   Authorities were alerted about a house on Lawson Lane at 12:25 p.m. Sunday, according to a sheriff&#39;s department report.
<P>   Det. Scott Smith said a witness saw flames coming from the home around 6 a.m., but the witness failed to call because he thought the home was abandoned, the report stated. The home had no electricity.
<P>   Authorities said an autopsy will be performed today to establish the cause of death and make a positive identification.
<P>   Ken Russell, an investigator with the state fire marshal&#39;s office, is working with the sheriff&#39;s department to determine the cause of the fire.
<P>
<P>
<P><h3>E. Knoxville teen faces felony drug, gun charges </h3>
<P>
<P>
<P>   A 17-year-old boy faces felony charges after police found 19 &#39;&#39;rocks&#39;&#39; of crack cocaine, $320 in cash and a loaded gun in his pocket, records show.
<P>   Nathaniel Bomdiley Adebayo, who gave police a Barker Avenue address, was arrested Saturday after he allegedly ran from officers in East Knoxville. He was charged with aggravated robbery, carrying a weapon with the intent to go armed, possession of cocaine and possession of a firearm with an altered serial number, according to a Knoxville Police Department report.
<P>   Adebayo, an Austin-East High School student, allegedly had crack cocaine, cash and a loaded gun in his pocket when he was captured by Officers Mike Bates and Steve Still on S. Olive Street around 3:30 p.m.
<P>   The officers began chasing Adebayo because he matched the description of a man accused of robbing a 30-year-old East Knoxvillian minutes before, the report stated. The alleged victim told police he and a friend gave Adebayo a ride.
<P>   The alleged victim claimed Adebayo robbed him of $25 after he declined to buy &#39;&#39;some dope&#39;&#39; from Adebayo, the report stated. A rock of crack cocaine generally costs $25.
<P>
<P>
