<P><B>BRUCE, ZELLA LOVE HALL - </B>age 93, of Speedwell, passed away Friday, Jan. 10 at the LaFollette Medical Center. She was a member of Cawood United Methodist Church of Speedwell, Cumberland Mountain Chapter #137 Order of the Eastern  Star, Campbell County Teachers Association and the Retired Teachers Association. Mrs. Bruce was a graduate of Lincoln Memorial University and taught at various schools in Claiborne and Campbell counties for several years. Preceded in death by her parents, George and Lula Proffitt Hall; husband, Charles Patton Bruce; brother, Charles Denzil Hall; sisters, Verdie Carr, Ruby Hall and Alma Smith; daughter-in-law, Margueritte Maire Bruce; grandson, James Tupper; great-grandchildren, Misty Carol Simpson, Karen Jean and Sharon Jane Simpson and Thomas Ray Tupper. Survivors: son, Charles Ray Bruce of Clinton; sons and daughters-in-law, Roy Eugene and Florine Taylor Bruce of Speedwell, Boyd and Flossie Smith Bruce of Gainesville, Fla.; daughters and sons-in-law, Lula Mae and Tommy Tupper of Clinton, Charlene Balliet Donahee and Mel Donahee of Barefoot Bay, Fla.; 13 grandchildren; 16 great-grandchildren; brother, Allison Hall, Blountville, Tenn.; sister, Carrie Claiborne, LaFollette. Funeral services 8 p.m. Monday, Jan. 13, at Cross Funeral Home, Rev. Bill Hill officiating. Interment 2 p.m. Tuesday, Jan. 14 at Alexander Cemetery, Speedwell. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Monday at Cross Chapel. Arrangements by Cross Funeral Home.
