<P><B>COULTER, HUBERT DUGGAN - </B>age 85, of Maryville, died Saturday, January 11, 1997, at Fairpark Nursing Center. He was a member of Pleasant Grove Baptist Church, was retired from ALCOA, and was a member of the ALCOA 25 Year Service Club, was a lifelong resident of the Hubbard Community. He was preceded in death by his parents, Samuel H. and Ida Duggan Coulter; brothers, Edgar, Eugene and Joe Coulter; sisters, Jennie and Nina Belle Coulter. Survivors include his wife of 60 years, Ruby L. Coulter; sons and daughters-in-law, David and Mary Coulter of Riceville, Tom and Pat Coulter of Knoxville; daughters and sons-in-law, JoAnn and Eldon Black of Verbena, Ala., Martha and Tony Abbott of Maryville; grandchildren, Mark Black, Melba Gabriel, Martha Doyle, Michael Black, Randy Coulter, Timothy Coulter, Susan Millsaps, Nina Abbott and Tyler Abbott; seven great-grandchildren. Funeral services will be 6:30 p.m. Monday in McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home Chapel with Rev. Greg L. Long officiating. Friends will meet 11 a.m. Tuesday at Pleasant Grove Cemetery for the interment service with members of the Senior Men&#39;s Sunday School Class serving as honorary pallbearers. The family will receive friends immediately following the service at the funeral home. The family suggests memorials be made to Pleasant Grove Baptist Church, 3736 Tuckaleechee Pike, Maryville, TN 37804. McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home, Maryville.
