<P><B>CROSWELL, HARRY BENNETT - </B>age 68, of Sevierville, died Friday, January 10, 1997. He was a resident of Sevierville for 22 years and retired from Colonial Industries, where he was manager for the Sevier Industries Plant. He was of the Catholic faith. Survivors: wife, June Croswell; son, Bennett Croswell and wife, Stephanie of Palm City, Fla.; step-son, Thomas Hardy and wife, Fran of Summerfield, N.C.; grandchildren, Jody, Megan and Amanda Hardy, Caitlin, Hannah and Michael Croswell. Memorial service 4 p.m. Tuesday, January 14, 1997, in the East Chapel of Atchley Funeral Home, Father Jay Flaherty and Rev. Leroy Parton officiating. Family requests no flowers. Contributions may be made to the charity of your choice. Atchley Funeral Home in charge.
