<P><B>GIBNEY, LAURENCE V., SR. - </B>age 83, of North Knoxville, died Saturday, January 11, 1997, at Holston Health Care Center. He was a member of Holy Ghost Catholic Church. A retired architecht for TVA. Member Knights of Columbus Council 645 and Monsignor Francis D. Grady Assembly and the American Institute of Architects. Preceded in death by wife, Catherine McGuire Gibney. Survivors: sons and daughters-in-law, Laurence V., Jr. (Larry) and Margaret Gibney, Knoxville, Thomas D. (Tom) and Merrily Gibney, Nashville; daughter, Katherine Gibney, Washington, D.C.; grandchildren, Thomas, Joseph and Elizabeth Gibney, Thomas and John Scott Gibney, and Kara Gibney; sister, Evelyn E. Gibney, Falls Church, Va.; brother and sister-in-law, Col. Raymond F. and June Gibney, Atlanta; several nieces and nephews. Funeral mass 10 a.m. Tuesday, Holy Ghost Catholic Church, Father John Dowling officiating. Interment Calvary Cemetery. In lieu of flowers, family requests memorials be made to Alzheimer&#39;s Area Chapter, 1924 Alcoa Hwy., Knoxville, TN 37920. Friends may call at their convenience at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
