<P><B>HAGANS, MR. FRANK MAYWOOD HAYES - </B>age 90, of Morristown, passed away Saturday, January 11, 1997, at Little Creek Sanitarium in Knoxville after a brief illness. Mr. Hagans is survived by wife, Mattie Lorino Hagans; stepdaughters, Rita Lorino Smith, Morristown, Deloris Lorino Smith, Knoxville, Frankie Lorino Moyers, Morristown; step-son, William John Lorino, Arlington, Va.; 11 grandchildren and 8 great-grandchildren; brother, Jerry Hagans of Van Wert, Ohio; several nieces and nephews; and great-nieces and nephews. Mr. Hagans was preceded in death by his first wife, Mary Keller Hagans. Mr. Hagans and his wife, Mattie, both widowed, were married November 16, 1975. Born August 28, 1906, in Piketon, Ohio, Mr. Hagans came to Morristown in the spring of 1962 from Columbus, Ohio, where he continued his  employment with Jeffery Chain Corporation until he retired in 1972. The family will receive friends at Stetzer Funeral Home Monday evening from 6:30-8 p.m. Funeral services will be held immediately following the receiving of friends. Graveside services will be held 11 a.m. Tuesday morning at Hamblen Memorial Gardens. Friends wishing to express sympathy may do so through memorial donations to ALPS or the American Heart Associaton. Stetzer Funeral Home in charge of arrangements.
<P>
<P><B>HERRELL, HELEN RUTH - </B>age 65, of Blaine, passed away Sat. Jan. 11, 1997, at Hillcrest North. She was a member of Highland Springs Baptist Church. Preceded in death by parents, Laura and Roscoe Shelton; brother, Eugene Shelton. Survived by husband, Lynn D. Herrell, Blaine; daughters, Rena Herrell, Knoxville, Janice Courtney; grandchildren, LaTonya and Jocelyn Mayes of New Market; sisters, Eula Tyler, Michigan, Leona Neal, Miss., Jerleen Range, Rutledge; brothers, Ray, Austin and Wade Shelton of Rutledge, Parlon W. Shelton of Clifton, Tenn.; several nieces, nephews, great-nieces and nephews. Funeral service 2 p.m. Wednesday, Fielden Chapel with Revs. Donnie Coffman and Lester Byrd officiating. Interment in Indian Ridge Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-9 p.m. Tuesday at Fielden Funeral Home, New Market.
<P>
<P><B>HOWARD, WILLIAM C.</B> <B>(BILL) - </B>age 57, of West Knoxville, died Saturday, January 11, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Park West Hospital. Member of Ooltewah Lodge #0741 F&AM. Served in the U.S. Air Force. Was ACFT dispatcher (Alert). Survivors: son, Casey Howard of Knoxville; step-sons, Bart Howard of Knoxville and Brad Howard of Dallas, Texas; Casey&#39;s mother, Deanna T. Howard of Charleston, S.C.; and many friends at Roger&#39;s Place. Graveside service and interment 2 p.m. Tuesday, Tennessee Veterans Cemetery, Dr. Eugene Fleming officiating. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Monday at Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>HUBBARD, WILLIAM - </B>age 68, passed away January 10, 1997, at Blount Memorial Hospital.  Retired from Institutional Jobbers.  Preceded in death by parents, Charles and Dolly Blew Hubbard.  Survivors:  wife, Betty J. Hubbard; sons; daughters; brothers and sisters. Graveside service 1 p.m. Tuesday, Sherwood Memorial Gardens.  In lieu of flowers make memorials to the Humane Society.  Family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Monday at Berry Funeral Home, Chapman Highway.
<P>
<P><B>KITTS, EVELYN JUSTINE (TOOTS) - </B>age 74, of Knoxville, passed away 4:30 a.m. Sunday, January 12, 1997, at Hillcrest Nursing Home. Preceded in death by parents, Albert T. and Maggie (Baker) Kitts; brother, James E. Kitts. Survivors: brother and sister-in-law, Max and Marie Kitts of Corryton; sister-in-law, Verna L. Kitts of Knoxville; niece and nephews, Susie and Joe Bob Hazelwood, Scott and David Kitts; aunt, Dula Baker of Maynardville. Graveside services and interment 1 p.m. Tuesday, Skaggs Cemetery, Rev. Mark Kitts officiating. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Monday, Cooke Mortuary, Maynardville.
