<head>
	<title>Locally managed mutual outpaces national funds</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper Business News">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<a href="/"><img src="../../images/flag.gif" alt="Knoxville News-Sentinel Online -- Business News" align=bottom border=0 width=595 height=176></a><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td align=left valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 12, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Locally managed mutual outpaces national funds</B></font><basefont size=6><!--SUBHEAD--></basefont></FONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		<FONT SIZE="+2">T</FONT>he IPS Millenium Fund, a no-load mutual fund managed from Knoxville, posted a 24.5 percent return in 1996 and grew its assets to $5.9 million.
<P>   The fund outperformed both the S&P 500 Index, up 20.3 percent, and the Lipper Growth & Income Fund Index, up 20.69 percent.
<P>   The fund&#39;s managers, Greg D&#39;Amico and Robert Loest, credit the $3.9 million in additional assets to the favorable national publicity the fund received throughout the year.
<P>   Fortune magazine, The Wall Street Journal, USA Today and CNNfn all highlighted the fund and its use of economic value-added analysis when choosing stocks to purchase. EVA is an economic model gaining in popularity that purports to determine whether a company is earning more than its cost of capital.
<P>   The fund is typically among the top five funds nationwide when the high-tech sector -- where about 40 percent of its assets are located -- is performing well, Loest said.
<P>   &#39;&#39;Usually only aggressive growth funds have a similar technology exposure, but we balance that with a significant investment in higher dividend sectors, which helps stabilize the fund without sacrificing exposure to the greatest growth engine of our lifetimes,&#39;&#39; Loest said.
<P>   Good performers for the fund last year were Intel, Sisco Systems, National Commerce Bancorporation and Rural/Metro, said Loest. Real estate investment trusts also moved up in the last quarter.
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
