<head>
	<title>Four UT athletic officials promoted</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 12, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td width=470><BASEFONT SIZE="6">
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Four UT athletic officials promoted</B></FONT><!--SUBHEAD--></BASEFONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		<FONT SIZE="+2">T</FONT>he University of Tennessee athletic department announced four staff promotions Saturday.
<P>   Men&#39;s athletic director Doug Dickey announced that Mike Hamilton and Gary Wyant have been promoted to associate athletic directors. John Stucky was made an assistant athletic director.
<P>   Women&#39;s athletic director Joan Cronan announced the elevation of Donna Thomas to associated athletic director for compliance and operation.
<P>   Under Dickey&#39;s realignment, Mitch Barnhart -- who became senior associate athletic director last July -- will have direct responsibilities for marketing and public relations and will be immediate supervisor of the Vols&#39; baseball, swimming and track programs.
<P>   Hamilton, an assistant AD under Barnhart since 1992, will be associate AD for development. Dickey said the 33-year-old Clemson graduate &#39;&#39;will have all responsibility for the annual donors program, including skyboxes and parking, and will continue to develop endowments for the athletic program.&#39;&#39;
<P>   Wyant will be associate AD for football operations. He will manage all direct support systems of the program.
<P>   Stucky will be assistant AD for physical development. Director of athletic fitness since 1994, he will be responsible for the physical training of the athletes and management of the staff of fulltime assistants and student workers. He was named Thursday at the SEC strength and conditioning coach of the year by his fellow coaches.
<P>   Cronan said Thomas, a UT graduate and four-year veteran of the Lady Vols&#39; staff, will continue to be responsible for compliance and for overseeing internal operations.
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
