<head>
	<title>Author to speak at Lee dinner</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 11, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Author to speak at Lee dinner</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">T</FONT>he annual Robert E. Lee-Stonewall Jackson Birthday Celebration dinner will be held Saturday, Jan. 18, at the Foundry on the World&#39;s Fair site.
<P>   The event, sponsored by the Knoxville chapter of the Sons of Confederate Veterans, is open to the public. Keynote speaker is Mauriel Joslyn, who has written two books on the War Between the States published this year.
<P>    She will speak on &#39;&#39;Women of the South.&#39;&#39;
<P>   Traditional Southern music, including &#39;&#39;Dixie,&#39;&#39; will be provided by keyboard artist Anne Jackson.
<P>   Cost is $19.50 for adults, $9.50 for children under 12. Reservations with payments must be received no later than Wednesday, Jan. 15. They can be mailed to Lee/Jackson Dinner, SCV Camp 87, P.O. Box 943, Knoxville, TN. 37902. Checks should be made payable to SCV Camp 87.
<P>  Semi-formal attire or period dress is requested. Doors will open at 6 p.m. for a social hour, followed by dinner at 7 p.m.
<P>    Anyone needing additional information may contact John Hitt, 689-4592; Dave Jones, 671-0341; or Earl Smith, 687-2732.
<P>    In Tennessee, Lee&#39;s birthday, Jan. 19, is an official State Day of Special Observance. Because Stonewall Jackson was also born in January, the Knoxville SCV chapter includes his name in the event.
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
