<P><B>COLE, EDGAR - </B>age 88, of Route 1, Rutledge, died Thursday evening, January 9, 1997, in Jefferson Memorial Hospital in Jefferson City following an extended illness. He was of the Baptist faith and was preceded in death by his parents, Caleb and Martha Oakley Cole; and a brother, Ray Cole; and a nephew, Billy Cole. Survivors: brother, Frank Cole of Rutledge; nephews, Johnny Cole of Rutledge and Charles Cole of Jefferson City; special niece, Johna Cole of Rutledge; several other nieces and nephews; special friend, Jimmy Clark of Rutledge. Funeral services will be held at 3:30 p.m. Sunday afternoon, January 12, 1997, from the Smith Funeral Home Chapel in Rutledge with Rev. Herbert Purkey, Sr. and Rev. Herbert Purkey, Jr. officiating. Interment to follow in the Grainger Memorial Gardens. The family will receive friends from 7-9 p.m. Saturday evening, January 11, 1997, at the funeral home. Arrangements by Smith Funeral Home, 123 Water Street, Rutledge, Tennessee 37861, Phone (423) 828-5555.
