<P><B>COX, JOHN A. - </B>age 78, of Knoxville, died Wednesday, January 8, 1997, at his home. Mr. Cox retired from Southern Railway in 1979 after 38 years of service. He was a combat veteran of WWII receiving a Purple Heart for wounds suffered in The Battle of The Bulge. Mr. Cox served in County Court from 1971-1976. He also served on the Election Commission in 1977. Mr. Cox was a Knox County School Board Member for 15 years, retiring in 1992. He was a trustee for the Juvenile Detention Center, chairman of the 39th. precinct voting district for 23 years from 1969-1992. An active member of Dante United Methodist Church. Preceded in death by parents, Mr. and Mrs. John A. Cox, Jr.; brothers, Carl, Ralph and Edward Cox. Mr. Cox is survived by his loving, devoted wife of 55 years, Margaret Whedbee Cox; sons and daughters-in-law, John Douglas and Susan Cox, Terry Lynn and Susan Cox; six grandchildren, Stephanie Cox Coiner and husband, Kevin, Chad and Amanda Cox, Courtney Cox and Heath Morgan, all of Knoxville, Cadet Justin D. Cox, West Point, N.Y.; one great-grandchild, Makenzie Coiner. Funeral service 11:30 a.m. Saturday at Stevens Chapel. Rev. John Brewster officiating. Interment Sherwood Memorial Gardens. Pallbearers: Chad Cox, Heath Morgan, Kevin Coiner, George Steele, Bud Lewis, Robert Province, Hal Worsham and David Clapp. Honorary pallbearers: Congressman John Duncan, Allen Morgan, Earl Hoffmeister, Ron Thomas, A.B. Bell, Bill Clabo, Lee Griswold, E.S. Bevins, Howard Ferguson and Alan Gill. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Dante United Methodist Church, 6700 Kern Road, Knoxville, Tenn. 37918. Arrangements by Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
