<P><B>GEIGER, WILLIAM A. - </B>age 81, of Knoxville, died Friday, January 10, 1997, at U.T. Hospital. Member of All Saints Catholic Church, former member of the Cathedral of the Sacred Heart of Jesus. He was a member of the 523rd Bomber Group, Army Air Group, during WWII. He retired from NASA as chief of air logistics. Member Delta Nu Alpha Fraternity and U.T. Alumni Association. Survivors: wife, Katherine B. Geiger; daughter and son-in-law, Gloria and Roy Neuenschwander, Knoxville; grandchildren, Andrea and Patrick Neuenschwander; brother and sister-in-law, Robert and Martha Geiger, Hendersonville, Tenn.; several nieces and nephews. Funeral mass 10 a.m.  Monday, January 13, 1997, at the Cathedral of the Sacred Heart of Jesus, Father Gregory L. Boisvert and Fr. Michael Cummins officiating. Interment will be in Highland Memorial Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Sunday at Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel.
