<P><B>GOAN, MR. THURMAN THEODORE, JR. - </B>age 49, of Charlotte, died Jan. 10, 1997, at Mercy South Hospital. Funeral service will be 1 p.m. Saturday, Jan. 11, 1997, at Holy Trinity Greek Orthodox Cathedral, Rev. Nick Triantafilou officiating. Interment will be 2 p.m. Sunday in Jarnagin Cemetery in Morristown. Mr. Goan, a native of Morristown, graduated from Morristown High School and the University of Tennessee in Knoxville. He was a member of the Holy Trinity Greek Orthodox Cathedral and a teacher with the Charlotte Mecklenburg Board of Education. Survivors include his wife, Mary B. Gaon; son, Nicholas Goan; and daughter, Miss Ellie Goan, all of Charlotte; mother, Mrs. Maxine Goan of Morristown; brother, Rick Goan of Dayton, Ohio. Memorials may be made to the Holy Trinity Greek Orthodox Cathedral, 600 E. Blvd. Charlotte, NC 28203. Hankins & Whittington is serving the family.
