<P>WESTFIELD, CARLOS EUGENE WAT<B>KINS - </B>of 2630 Wimpole Avenue, Apt. 37, entered into eternal rest, January 7th., 1997, at UT Medical Center. Preceded in death by grandparents, Thomas and Mary Elizabeth Westfield. Survivors: devoted mother, Lanita Watkins-Westfield; father, Thomas Eugene Westfield Jr.; sisters, Tiffanie Renee Westfield, Knoxville, Tabette Lena Westfield of Cleveland, Ohio; brothers, Thomas III and Samuel Tremayne Westfield of Cleveland, Ohio; grandparents, Curtis and Marian Watkins of Chattanooga, Tenn.; uncles, Michael Watkins, Atlanta, Curtis Watkins of Chattanooga, Theodore Westfield of Cleveland, Tenn.; aunts, Malory Barrett, Debra Bryant, Janet Whaley of Cleveland, Tenn.; special devoted friends to include, Calvin Eugene Davis, Frank Scruggs, Towana Woods, and a host of nieces, nephews and many friends. The family will receive friends Sunday at Jarnigan Chapel from 2-2:30 p.m. with funeral service to follow at 2:30 p.m., Rev. James Davis officiating. Interment to be held 10 a.m. Monday, Tennessee State Veterans Cemetery. The family will assemble at 1044 Groner Drive, Sunday, after the services at the home of Mrs. Bernice Hansand. Jarnigan & Son Mortuary in charge.
