	<title>Pair&#39;s murder charges sent to grand jury</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 10, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Pair&#39;s murder charges sent to grand jury</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">A</FONT> North Knox County woman and her boyfriend waived their rights to a preliminary hearing Thursday on charges they murdered her estranged husband.
<P>   A Knox County grand jury now will consider whether to indict Dana Louise Solomon, 21, and Thomas Edward Chambers, 19. Knox County General Sessions Court Judge Geoff Emery sent the charges on to the grand jury with the consent of defense lawyers and the prosecution.
<P>   Solomon and Chambers are accused of killing Clyde Milton Solomon III, 23, on Dec. 26 at the Black Oak Mobile Home Park, 3700 Rifle Range Road. Investigators allege the couple have admitted planning to lure Clyde Solomon to the trailer, which they shared, to commit murder.
<P>   Clyde Solomon went to the home to visit his toddler son. When he arrived, Solomon told him the boy was not present and that he should come back later in the afternoon, Knox County investigators allege.
<P>   When Clyde Solomon returned, his estranged wife stepped out and he went in the trailer. An argument broke out between Clyde Solomon and Chambers and Clyde Solomon was shot with a shotgun.
<P>   Solomon and Chambers each are being held in the Knox County Jail on $200,000 bond.
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
