	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Former News-Sentinel man, Masonic leader Chambers dies</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">M</FONT>asonic and funeral services for retired News-Sentinel employee James Paul Chambers will begin at 7 p.m. today at Oriental Lodge No. 453 F. & A.M.
<P>   Mr. Chambers, who retired from The News-Sentinel in 1974 after 45 years of service, died Monday at Baptist Hospital of East Tennessee. He was 88.
<P>   Mr. Chambers was a master mason and former worshipful master of Oriental Lodge No. 453. He was a member of French Broad Valley Baptist Church.
<P>   He is survived by wife of 64 years, Elizabeth Pauline Chambers; a daughter, Julia Chambers Lane; and several grandchildren and great-grandchildren.
<P>   Burial will be at 11 a.m. Saturday at Woodlawn Cemetery.
<P>
