<P><B>GUTRIDGE SR., THOMAS RAY - </B>age 76 of Maryville, passed away January 9, 1997, at Blount Memorial Hospital. He was a 35 year career employee of ALCOA where he received several awards for his achievements with the company. He was an active electrical contractor until he retired in 1995, was a member of Madison Avenue Baptist Church, Maryville, and was a veteran of World War II serving with the Marines in the Pacific Theater. He was preceded in death by his parents, Mary Sue and Ray Gutridge and brother, Dale Gutridge. Survivors include: Wife, Erma Carpenter Gutridge; daughter, Sondra Gutridge of Louisville; son and daughter-in-law, Tom and Cheryl Gutridge of Powell; son, Ronnie Gutridge; grandchildren, Eric Gutridge of Alcoa, Amanda Gutridge of Powell, Travis and Tanya Gutridge of Knoxville; brother, Gene Gutridge of Friendsville; sisters, Ella Sheets of Maryville, Nadine Henegar of Greenback, Frances Covert of Indianapolis, Phyllis Otterbein of Ohio; several nieces and nephews. Funeral services will be held at 8:00 p.m. Friday in McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home Chapel with Rev. Glenn Grubb officiating. Family and friends will meet at 11:00 a.m. Saturday at Grandview Cemetery for the interment service. The family will receive friends from 6-8:00 p.m. Friday at McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home, Maryville. Contributions may be made to the American Diabetes Association, 6906 Kingston Pike, Knoxville, TN 37919 or Habitat For Humanity, Blount County, 333 E. Broadway Avenue, Maryville, TN 37804.
<P>
<P><B>HART, VIRGIE FAYE (SMITH) - </B>age 86, of Knoxville, born July 16, 1910, in Roy, New Mexico, died Thursday, January 9, 1997, at Brakebill Nursing Home. Preceded in death by parents, Mabel and Jack Smith and husband, Elmo E. Hart, Sr. Survivors: daughter, Brenda Booker and her husband, Joe; daughter, Ruth Collins and her husband, Floyd; daughter, Ruby Allen; sons, Danny and Elmo E. Hart, Jr., Bill and Roy Howard; sisters, Marie Lunsford and Bertha Prince; brother, Bob Smith; several grandchildren; great-grandchildren; nieces and nephews. Family and friends will meet 9:45 a.m. Saturday at Asbury Cemetery for a 10 a.m. graveside service, Rev. Dewey Cooper officiating. The family will receve friends 5-7 p.m. Friday at Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
