<P><B>JONES, ESKER - </B>age 76, of South Knoxville, passed away January 8, 1996 at U.T. Medical Center. He was a member of Friendly Chapel Baptist Church, retired from Robertshaw and was a veteran of World War II. Preceded in death by brothers, Claude, Burl, Aliss Jones and sisters, Odessa Bolton, Evelyn Hatfield. Survivors: Daughter, Linda Galyon; sons, Lester and Lonas Jones; grandchildren, Wendy Smith, Shawn Jones; great-grandchildren, Travis, Trevor and Megan; brothers, Goldie Jones, Durl Jones; sisters, Myrie Hawkins, Zelma Norman; special friend, Louise McCarroll; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 2:30 p.m. Saturday, January 11, 1997, Berry Chapel with Rev. Fred McGill and Rev. Bill Acuff officiating. Interment to follow in Mt. Olive Cemetery. The family will receive friends from 7-9 p.m. Friday at Berry Funeral Home, Chapman Highway.
<P>
<P><B>LANKFORD, CUBIE LEE SUMMEY - </B>age 63, of Oak Grove Road, Madisonville, passed away 10 a.m. Wednesday, January 8, 1997, at UT Medical Center. Member of Mt. Zion Baptist Church and the W.M.U. Survivors: husband, James Henry Lankford; daughters and sons-in-law, Carolyn and Don Belcher, Wanda Stakely, Willa Mae Summey, Ann and Shawn Cross, Leasia Summey, all of Vonore, Connie and Virgil Duncan, Sweetwater; 16 grandchildren; one great-grandchild; three sisters; five brothers; devoted stepson and wife, Jerry and Dorothy Lankford, Maryville; two other stepsons and five step-daughters; several step-grandchildren; several nieces and nephews. Preceded in death by first husband, Fred Summey; daughter, Victoria Summey; two sisters. Funeral 11 a.m. Saturday, Mt. Zion Baptist Church, Rev. Gary E. Simmerly and Rev. Tommy Self officiating. Interment church cemetery. Family will receive friends 6-9 p.m. Friday at Biereley-Hale Funeral Home, Madisonville.
<P>
<P><B>MARSH, CHARLES FRANKLIN, SR. - </B>age 76 formally of Knoxville passed away Wednesday, January 8, 1997 in Lake Worth, Fla. He was born 8/24/1920 in Browntown, Tenn. He lived in Dayton, Ohio for 38 yrs years, most recently of Lake Worth, Fla. He was a former member of the Civilian Conservation Corps. He was a decorated veteran of WWII, serving from June 8, 1944 until January 6, 1946 in company E, 1st Platoon, 22nd infantry, 4th Division U.S. Army. Received the Purple Heart, Theater Ribbon with three Bronze Stars, Victory Medal WWII and the M1SS for Sharpshooting and expert gunmanship STMM. Retired driver, lastly in Eastern Express in Ohio. Longtime member Master&#39;s Masonic Lodge #0244 F&AM in Knoxville, Tenn. and the Antioch Temple A.A.O.N.M.S. of Dayton, Ohio. Survivors: He was the beloved husband of  Annie M. (Varnes) Marsh for 57 years and; the loving father of Cynthia J. (Marsh) Pryor, Glenna R. (Marsh) Stanhouse, Charles F. Jr, James E. Marsh; six grandchildren; and nine great-grandchildren. Funeral services 2:00 p.m. Sunday Rose Chapel Rev. David Smith officiating. Interment in Lynnhurst Cemetery with full military honors. Conducted by the Volunteer State Veterans Honor Guard. Masonic Services will be Saturday at 8:00 p.m. Rose Chapel conducted by Masters Masonic Lodge #0244 F&AM. The family will receive friends from 6-8:00 p.m. Saturday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel in Knoxville, Tenn.
<P>
<P><B>MATSON, SAMANTHA JO - </B>age 7, of 14436 Virtue Road, Lenoir City, passed away Thursday morning January 9, 1997 at her home. She was a member of Martel United Methodist Church. A second grade student at Highland Park Elementary School. Survivors: father, Dean Richards of Indiana; parents, Rachelle and David Bivens with whom she made her home; sister, Brandi Bivens of the home; grandparents, Don and Dianne Tipton, Jim and Paulette Bivens, all of Lenoir City; great grandparents, Haline Forrester of Knoxville; Paul and Doris Holloway of Lenoir City; several aunts and uncles. Funeral services 4 p.m. Saturday, Click Funeral Home Chapel, Rev. Larry Trotter officiating. Interment Lake View Cemetery. In lieu of flowers, donations may be made to the Highland Park School CDC Class. The family will receive friends from 6-8 p.m. Friday at Click Funeral Home, Lenoir City.
