<P><B>PATTON, FRANCES J. - </B>age 73, of Shelbyville, Indiana died January 8, 1997 at her residence. Born July 27, 1923 in Helena, AL. she lived most of her life in the Tennessee Valley. She moved to Shelbyville in April of 1996. She was employed by TVA for 33 years as a Construction Nurse at Sequoia Nuclear Plant in Chattanooga. She retired in 1984 as a rehabilitation supervisor with medical services. She was a member of Saint Luke United Methodist Church, Decatur, AL. She was the former Chairman of the Health Committee with the National Safety Council of Construction Section. She was a member of the American Nurses Association and the Tennessee Nurses Association. She was a member of the Soddy-Daisy, Tennessee Chapter 328 O.E.S. Preceded in death by: Parents Carl and Prue Kent Patton of Littleville, AL.; brother, Kent Patton. Survivors: Sister, Sue Patton Sparks, Shelbyville, IN.; brother, Dr. Thomas Patton, Cullman, AL.; three nieces, four nephews. Services will be held at Carmony-Ewing Broadway Funeral Home, Shelbyville, IN. Friday, Jan. 10, 1997, 10:00 a.m. with visitation beginning one hour before the service. A memorial service will be held at Colbert Memorial Chapel Tuscumbia, AL, Tuesday, Jan. 14, 1997, 11:00 a.m. with visitation beginning one hour before the service.  Burial in Colbert Memorial Gardens, Lt. Col. Michael Coburn officiating. Carmony-Ewing Funeral Homes in charge.
