<P>h3792_0110
<P><B>BABB, REV. HAROLD WAYNE - </B>age 78, of Oliver Springs, passed away Tuesday, January 7, 1997, at Oak Ridge Methodist Medical Center. He retired from Union Carbide Oak Ridge, also a retired Church of God minister. While in the professional world, Rev. Babb served his local church as a council member and Sunday School teacher. He also was active as a lay minister. Rev. Babb was involved in the ministry of the Lord Jesus Christ as both a lay minister and pastor for over 50 years. As pastor he served the congregation of the Grey Church of God, and later the Pigeon Forge Church of God, until retiring to the Oliver Springs, Tenn., area. Rev. Babb was preceded in death by his eldest daughter, Erma Jean Babb, who went on to meet the Lord in 1979. Survivors: wife, Helen Rogers Babb; children, Jerry, James, Richard and Larry Babb, Pamela Babb Gable and Stanley Babb; 13 grandchildren; five great-grandchildren; sister, June Fox; and brother, Dennis Babb. Funeral service 11 a.m. Friday, Oak Ridge Church of God, Rev. W.J. Brown and Rev. Joe C. Taylor officiating. Interment Oak Ridge Memorial Park. Pallbearers: Edward Babb, Walter Porter, Ron Flammang, Freddy Babb, Jim Babb, Michael Snow. Family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Thursday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>BLACKSTOCK, HOWARD C. - </B>age 75, of Knoxville, passed away Tuesday at Baptist Hospital. Member of Gayland Heights Baptist Church. Preceded in death by: parents, John R. and Martha Blackstock; son, Buddy Howard Blackstock; granddaughter, Faye Lee Ann Blackstock; brothers, Dewey and John R. Blackstock, Jr.; sister, Lucille McCroskey. Survivors: wife of 54 years, Virginia Blackstock; sons and daughters-in-law, Benny and Nancy Blackstock, Tom and Susan Blackstock; daughter, Martha Pedigo; grandchildren, Joshua Pedigo, Kayla Blackstock, Brad and Blake Price; brothers and sisters-in-law, Jim and Ruth Blackstock, Sam and Mary Ruth Blackstock; several nieces and nephews; special friends at Shannondale Health Care Center. Funeral service 8 p.m. Thursday at Lynnhurst-Greenwood Chapel, Rev. Troy Cody, Rev. Paul Haney, and Dr. Bob Blackstock officiating. Interment 11 a.m. Friday at Lynnhurst Cemetery. Nephews will serve as pallbearers. Memorial contributions may be made to Shannondale Health Care Center. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Thursday prior to the service at Lynnhurst-Greenwood Chapel of Berry Funeral Home, 2300 W. Adair Drive.
<P>
<P><B>BUTCHER, VERSA RICH - </B>age 81, of Fountain City, passed away Wednesday morning in NHC Fort Sanders. She was a member of First Baptist Church of Fountain City. She was the widow of Carl L. Butcher, Sr. Preceded in death by sister, Nishie Noe; and foster parents, Mr. and Mrs. H.C. Cantwell. Survived by: son and daughter-in-law, Carl L., Jr. and Kerissa Butcher of Knoxville; granddaughters, Melissa Swisher of Carboro, N.C., Leslie Butcher of Knoxville, and Angie Graves of Knoxville; grandson, Richard Alan Butcher of Ohio. Funeral arrangements are incomplete and will be announced later by Gentry-Griffey Chapel. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Alzheimer&#39;s Association, 1924 Alcoa Hwy., Knoxville, TN 37920. Friends may call at their convenience at Gentry-Griffey Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>CARNES, J.B. - </B>age 64, passed away Monday at his residence. Retired from South Central Bell. Member of Masters Lodge #244 F.& A.M. and The American Legion. Survivors: daughters, Tammi Mence, Clinton, Tenn., Tracey Temple, Richmond, Va.; grandchildren, Jennifer, Stephanie, and Christopher Mence, all of Clinton, Charlie, Canden, and Correy Temple, all of Richmond, Va.; sister, Francis Carr, Knoxville. Masonic memorial service at 8 p.m. Friday with funeral service immediately following at Lynnhurst-Greenwood Chapel with Rev. Roscoe Oxendine officiating. Interment 11 a.m. Saturday at Lynnhurst Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Friday prior to the service at the Lynnhurst-Greenwood Chapel of Berry Funeral Home, 2300 W. Adair Drive.
<P>
<P><B>CHAMBERS, JAMES PAUL - </B>age 88, of South Knoxville, passed away January 6, 1997, at Baptist Hospital. He was a Master Mason and former Worshipful Master of Oriental Lodge #453 F.& A.M., formerly Knoxville Lodge #718 F.& A.M.  Member of French Broad Valley Baptist Church, Kodak, Tenn. Retired from the Knoxville News Sentinel in 1974 after 45 years of service. Preceded in death by sons, James &#39;&#39;Granny&#39;&#39; Chambers and James Joe Chambers. Survivors: wife of 64 years, Elizabeth Pauline Chambers; daughter, Julia Chambers Lane; granddaughters, Denise Lane Smith, Robin Chambers Light, Carrie Jo Chambers; great-grandchildren, Lauren Womack, Jake Smith. Masonic services will be conducted by Oriental Lodge #453 F.& A.M. at 7 p.m. on Friday, January 10, followed by funeral service with the Rev. Charles Harkleroad officiating. Interment 11 a.m. Saturday, Woodlawn Cemetery. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the French Broad Valley Baptist Church, 2826 Kim Drive, Kodak, TN 37764. The family will receive friends following the services Friday in the chapel of Berry Funeral Home, Chapman Highway.
