<P><B>WOODS, GEORGIA POTTS - </B>age 74, of Dandridge, passed away 7:15 a.m. Wednesday,  January 8, 1997, at Jefferson Memorial Hospital following an extended illness. She was a member of the Swanns Chapel Baptist Church. Preceded in death by parents, Bill and Hattie Sisk Potts; sisters, Mary Lou Smith and Geneva Hance; brothers, Rev. James Potts and William Potts. Survivors: husband, William T. &#39;&#39;Bill&#39;&#39; Woods of Dandridge; daughters and sons-in-law, Darlene and Bill Satterfield, Mary and Ken Scott, all of Dandridge; sons and daughters-in-law, John and Jeanette Woods of Strawberry Plains, Curt and Charolette Woods, Ron and Clay Woods, all of Dandridge; grandchildren, J.J. Patterson, Cindy Cagle, Kim Scott, Wayne Woods, Chris Woods, Jon Woods, all of Dandridge, Crystal Woods of Miami, Fla., Julie Hutchins and Ginger Watson, both of Strawberry Plains; five great-grandchildren; sister, Mrs. Sudie Hall of Rochelle, Ill.; brothers, Alfred and Glenn Potts, both of Dandridge; sister-in-law, Mrs. Zelma Potts of Dandridge; half brother, Jess Conway of Newport; step-sisters, Clelda Carter of White Pine, Mary Elizabeth Chrisman of Dandridge, Joan Wood of Arkansas; several nieces and nephews. Funeral services Thursday, 8 p.m. at the Swanns Chapel Baptist Church with Rev. John Price, Dr. Clyde Tilley, Dr. Robert McCray and Rev. Ron Wine officiating.  Interment services Friday 11 a.m. at the Swanns Chapel Cemetery. Family will receive friends Thursday evening 6 to 8 p.m. prior to services at the church. Arrangements by Farrar Funeral Home, Dandridge.
<P>
<P><B>WORTHINGTON, JUDY - </B>of Fountain City, died Tuesday evening at St. Mary&#39;s Medical Center. She was an active member of St. Paul United Methodist Church for 44 years and a member of the Loyal Workers Sunday School Class. She was the widow of Gene Worthington, Sr. Survived by: son and daughter-in-law, Gene and Jeanie Worthington of Knoxville; grandsons and granddaughters-in-law, Greg and Lorraine Worthington, San Francisco, Calif., Mark and Susan Worthington, Knoxville; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 7:30 p.m. Friday, St. Paul United Methodist Church, Garden Drive, Rev. Carl Oaks officiating. Graveside services will be held at 11 a.m. Saturday at Lynnhurst Cemetery. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to St. Paul United Methodist Church, Garden Drive. The family will receive friends 6-7:30 p.m. Friday at St Paul United Methodist Church. Arrangements by Gentry-Griffey Chapel.
<P>
