<P><B>ADAMS, RAY B. - </B>age 70, of Knoxville, died 5 a.m. Monday, January 6, 1997, at the family home. Member of Washington Pike Methodist Church. Driver for Lay&#39;s Packing Company for over 41 years. Preceded in death by wife, Trula Marie Adams; parents, Buford and Grace Adams; sister, Betty Vanosdale. Survivors: wife, Marion L. Adams; daughter and son-in-law, Rachel and Mike King; stepdaughters and husbands,  Pam and Ben Lane, Maryland, Carol and Rickie Harris, Tammy and Jimmy Bounds; stepdaughter, Cathy Hall; son and daughter-in-law, Michael R. and Shelia Adams; stepsons and wives, Greg and Minnie Hall, Joey and Lee Hall, both of Texas, Tony and Libby Hall; 18 grandchildren and two great-grandchildren; brother and sister-in-law, Roy H. and Helen Adams, all of Knoxville. Funeral service will be 1 p.m. Wednesday, Stevens Chapel, Rev. Bob Zavattieri and Rev. Sam Jollay officiating. Interment will follow in Lynnhurst Cemetery. Pallbearers: Billy Harris, Scott Ritch, Brett Palmer, Joe King, Ralph Lamb, Junior Ammons. Arrangements by Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Ave. at Broadway.
<P>
<P><B>BABB, REV. HAROLD WAYNE - </B>age 78, of Oliver Springs, passed away Tuesday, January 7, 1997, at Oak Ridge Methodist Medical Center. He retired from Union Carbide Oak Ridge, also a retired Church of God minister. While in the professional world, Rev. Babb served his local church as a council member and Sunday School teacher. He also was active as a lay minister. Rev. Babb was involved in the ministry of the Lord Jesus Christ as both a lay minister and pastor for over 50 years. As pastor he served the congregation of the Grey Church of God, and later the Pigeon Forge Church of God, until retiring to the Oliver Springs, Tenn., area. Rev. Babb was preceded in death by his eldest daughter, Erma Jean Babb, who went on to meet the Lord in 1979. Survivors: wife, Helen Rogers Babb; children, Jerry, James, Richard and Larry Babb, Pamela Babb Gable and Stanley Babb; 13 grandchildren; five great-grandchildren; sister, June Fox; and brother, Dennis Babb. Funeral service 11 a.m. Friday, Oak Ridge Church of God, Rev. W.J. Brown and Rev. Joe C. Taylor officiating. Interment Oak Ridge Memorial Park. Pallbearers: Edward Babb, Walter Porter, Ron Flammang, Freddy Babb, Jim Babb, Michael Snow. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Thursday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>BLACKSTOCK, HOWARD C. - </B>age 75, of Knoxville, passed away Tuesday afternoon at Baptist Hospital. Funeral arrangements are incomplete and will be announced later by Lynnhurst-Greenwood Chapel of Berry Funeral Home, 2300 W. Adair Drive.
<P>
<P><B>BONASERA, EVELYN T. - </B>age 83, of Knoxville, passed away January 7, 1997, at St. Mary&#39;s Medical Center. Member of St. John&#39;s Newman Catholic Church. Survived by daughter and son-in-law, Joyce and C.E. Packer of Knoxville; grandson, Lance Packer of Atlanta; great-granddaughter, Jaclyn Packer of Knoxville; brother, R.L. Mitchell of Knoxville. Rosary 4 p.m. Wednesday at Weaver&#39;s Chapel, Father Patrick Brownell officiating. Graveside service 1 p.m. Thursday CST at Forrest Cemetery in Gadsden, Ala., with Father Kevin Cook officiating. Arrangements by Weaver Funeral Home.
<P>
<P><B>BROWN, IVA ROBERTS - </B>age 83, of Sevierville, died Tuesday, January 7, 1997, at Baptist Hosptial of East Tennessee. She was preceded in death by parents, Luther and Dicie Roberts; first husband, Elmer Watson; brother, Ray Roberts; sister, Leona Wilson. Survivors: husband, Hardie Brown; step-children, Wanda and Steve Patterson, Maryville, Charles and Pat Brown, Marietta, Ga.; several step-grandchildren; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 7 p.m. Thursday in the West Chapel of Atchley Funeral Home. Rev. Melvin Lonas, Rev. John Nations and Rev. Charles Brown officiating. Interment 11 a.m. Friday in Shiloh Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-7 p.m. Thursday at Atchley Funeral Home, Sevierville.
