<P><B>BURDEN, PEGGY WILSON HEADRICK - </B>age 54, of Knoxville, passed away January 5, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Medical Center. Member of Bethel Baptist Church, Pine Grove Rd., Knoxville. Preceded in death by her husband, Gabriel &#39;&#39;Don&#39;&#39; Burden; parents, George and Myrtle Wilson; brother, Benny Wilson; and brother-in-law, Danny Branch. Survivors: daughter and son-in-law, Candy and Paul Sellers; sons and daughters-in-law, Richard and Kelli Burden, Randall and Jennifer Burden; grandchildren, Sierra and Tori Sellers, Madison, Carolyn JoAnn and Crista Sky Burden; sister, Sarah Branch; sisters and brothers-in-law, Gladys and John Luttrell, Kathy and Don LaFollette; stepmother, Bobbie Wilson; special friend, Jack Reed; many nieces, nephews, cousins and friends.  Family and friends will meet 1:45 p.m. Wednesday at Pratt&#39;s Chapel Cemetery for a 2 p.m. graveside service and interment. Rev. Archie Elliott and Rev. Jack Oglesby officiating. Pallbearers: Scotty Runion, Brian Elliott, Dusty Kennedy, Frank and Jessie Sellers, Martin Headrick. A  special thanks to Dr. David Slutzker and Associates and the staff of Ft. Sanders Medical Center. Arrangements by McCarty Mortuary, 4004 Holston Drive.
