<P><B>COLEMAN, ELEANOR JEAN - </B>age 67, of Strawberry Plains, passed away Sunday, January 5, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Regional Medical Center. Retired from Electric Service Company. Survived by husband, Howard G. Coleman, Jr.; daughter, Linda Carver; grandchildren, Cara and Josh Carver; parents, Thomas C. and Eleanor Bigler; sister, Barbara Long; several nieces and nephews. Family and friends will meet 10:15 a.m. Wednesday at McCarty Mortuary and proceed to Caledonia Cemetery for an 11 a.m. graveside service with Rev. Robert McCray officiating. Arrangements by McCarty Mortuary, 4004 Holston Drive.
<P>
<P><B>CORUM, MRS. RUBY MYNATT - </B>age 80, of Johnson City, died Monday, January 6, 1997, in Pine Ridge Health Care Center following a brief illness. Mrs. Corum was a native of Knoxville, and had been a resident of Johnson City since 1955. She was a daughter of the late Leroy Graves and Nancy Jane Burnett Mynatt. Mrs. Corum was retired from Massengill&#39;s Specialty Shop, Johnson City. She was a Methodist. Mrs. Corum was preceded in death by her husband, W.A. &#39;&#39;Bob&#39;&#39; Corum in 1966, and one brother. Survivors include two daughters, Janie Lewis of Johnson City and Elaine Pealer of Watauga, Tenn.; one brother, Raymond Mynatt of Knoxville; two sisters,  Mildred Moore of Johnson City and Helen Dance of Knoxville; three grandchildren; one great-grandchild; several nieces and nephews. Funeral services will be conducted at 8:30 p.m. Wednesday, January 8, 1997, from Appalachian-Hartman Funeral Home. Graveside committal services will be held at 10 a.m. Thursday, January 9, 1997, in Roselawn Memory Gardens, Johnson City. The family will receive friends 6:30-8:30 p.m. Wednesday in the funeral home chapel. Appalachian-Hartman Funeral Home, 800 E. Watauga Ave., Johnson City, Tenn., is in charge of arrangements (423) 928-6111.
<P>
<P><B>COWDEN, JAMES E. - </B>age 57, of Knoxville, passed away January 7, 1997, at Baptist Hospital. He was a retired U.S. Air Force Staff S.S.G.T. He was manager of Weigel&#39;s #18 for nine years. Preceded in death by parents, Eugene and Cora Mae Cowden; and sister, Barbara King. Survivors: loving wife, Elizabeth; and precious daughter, Megan (Pumpkin) Cowden; step-children, Teresa, David and Gary Winningham; sisters, Ann (Nah) Hicks, Helen M. Pruett and Nancy Graybeal; several nieces and nephews and great-nieces and nephews, aunts and uncles and cousins; numerous friends, with special recognition to Ann Adkinsson. Funeral service 7:30 p.m. Thursday, Mynatt&#39;s Chapel, Rev. Charles Lynch officiating. Interment will be at Tennessee State Veterans Cemetery Friday. Full military honors to be provided by East Tennessee Veterans Honor Guard. Family will receive friends 6-7:30 p.m. Thursday at Mynatt&#39;s.
<P>
<P><B>DAVIS, LEETHA VIOLA - </B>of North Knoxville, died Monday, January 6, 1997. She was a member of First Baptist Church of Knoxville and the former Bell Ave. Baptist Church. The widow of Carl F. Davis, Sr., she is survived by son and daughter-in-law, Carl and Gladys Davis of Knoxville; grandchildren, David and Alice Davis, Danny Davis; great-grandchildren, Molly, Zackary and Amy Davis. Funeral service 8 p.m. Wednesday, Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel with Rev. Dave Ward officiating. Family and friends will meet at Strawberry Plains Cemetery Thursday for an 11 a.m. interment service. Nephews will serve as pallbearers. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>DeLANEY, RUBY AKARD - </B>age 83, of Knoxville, died Saturday, January 4, 1997, at her home. Member of Second United Methodist Church and former member of Deaderick Avenue Baptist Churcb. She was retired from the Insurance Department of Valley Fidelity Bank/First Tennessee with over 30 years service. She was the oldest member of Omni Neighborhood Association. She was preceded in death by husband, Charles E. DeLaney. Survivors: nieces, Gail Copeland of Cookeville, Tenn., Barbara Drotos of Cheyenne, Wyo.; great-nieces, Greta Wallace of Charlotte, N.C., Beverly Drotos of Cheyenne, Wyo.; great-nephews, Jimmy Copeland of Columbia, Tenn., Greg Copeland; Fort Mill, S.C., Dan Drotos of Richmond, Va. Funeral services 2 p.m. Wednesday, Rose Broadway Chapel, Rev. J. Russell (Rusty) Taylor officiating. Interment Lynnhurst Cemetery. Family will receive friends 12:30-2 p.m. Wednesday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P> 
<P>DREW, MRS. KITTY &#39;&#39;CLIXIE&#39;&#39; HEM<B>PHILL - </B>age 87, of Knoxville, passed away Saturday, January 4, 1997, at Brakebill Nursing Home. Member of Metropolitan Missionary Baptist Church. Preceded in death by parents; husband, Herman Thomas; daughter, Katherine Wayman; sons, Wilbur and William; brothers, Sidney and William Hemphill; sisters, Mary Scruggs and Louise Armstead; great-grandson, Charles. Survivors: loving daughter, Barbara (Melvin, Sr.) Porter; sons, Herman (Reba) and Charles &#39;&#39;Pete&#39;&#39; (Joyce) Drew; devoted granddaughters, Katie Brown, Stephanie (Victor, Sr.) King, Angie Brooks (Shane), all of Knoxville, Yvonne, Yvette F. (Vanderbilt), Alcoa, Annetta Drew, North Carolina, Thomasena Drew, Knoxville; grandsons, Herman III, Melvin (Teresa) Porter, Randall (Patricia) Thomas, Robert, Nathaniel; devoted and loving niece, Della Oliver; great-grandchildren, Pamela Geater; faithful and devoted great-grandson, Willie &#39;&#39;King&#39;&#39; Williams, Clinton Brown; 28 grandchildren; 45 great-grandchildren and nine great-great-grandchildren; nephews, Warren Hemphill and James (Gert) Hemphill, Nashville; and a host of nieces, nephews, cousins and friends. Friends may call at the home of her granddaughter, Mrs. Stephanie King, 2204 Parkview Ave. The family will receive friends 1-1:30 p.m. Thursday, January 9, 1997, at Jarnigan&#39;s Chapel. Funeral service to follow at 1:30 p.m., Rev. Joe Colquitt officiating. Interment Holly Hills Memorial Park. Arrangements by Jarnigan and Son Mortuary.
