<P><B>KING, SYLVIA WHALEY - </B>age 92, widow of E.T. King, Sevier County&#39;s First County Judge and long-time Sevierville City Recorder, passed away 9 p.m. Monday, January 6, 1997. She was preceded in death by parents, Pinkney and Julia Whaley; brothers, Charlie and Vernon Whaley; sisters, Lillard King and Hazel Carr. She was born and grew up in the Greenbrier Section of Sevier County which is now part of the Great Smoky Mountains National Park of which the Whaley&#39;s where one of the original settlers. She was a member of First Baptist Church in Sevierville for over 58 years. Survivors: son and daughter-in-law, Carroll and Faye King; daughter and son-in-law, Shirley and Robert DeLozier; grandchildren, Dan and Connie King, Patti Rozzell and husband, Victor, Pam DeLozier; great-grandchildren, Blair, Crystal and Summer King, Justin and Jessica Rozzell; sisters, Mildred Gibson of Sevierville, Grace Pierce of Lenoir City; special appreciation to devoted caregivers at Markhill Village where Sylvia had been a resident for over 31/2 years; nephews, Jerry Pierce, Norman Whaley; nieces, Debra McCarter, Jan West, Linda Frances, Phyllis Megson, Peggy Clark; sisters-in-law, Lillian and Lucille Whaley. Funeral service 7 p.m. Wednesday in the West Chapel of Atchley Funeral Home, Dr. Rich Liner and Rev. Dillard Mynatt officiating. Interment 11 a.m. Thursday in Shiloh Cemetery. Pallbearers will be Carroll King&#39;s Sunday School Class of First Baptist Church. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to First Baptist Church, Sevierville, Building Fund. The family will receive friends 5:30-7 p.m. Wednesday at Atchley Funeral Home, Sevierville.
