<P><B>SENN, RONALD LEE - </B>age 66, of Oak Ridge, died Monday, Jan. 6 at Methodist Medical Center of Oak Ridge. Mr. Senn was born May 31, 1930, in Geary, Okla., to Elwin Lyle and Helen May Reynolds Senn. Mr. Senn was a professional engineer and staff member in the engineering technology division at the Oak Ridge National Laboratories from where he retired July 31, 1994, after 38 years of service. Mr. Senn was also a retired fighter pilot for the United States Air Force. He was a member and deacon at the First Baptist Church of Oak Ridge. Mr. Senn was a longtime contact teleministries volunteer and former board member. He also served two terms a president of the Foot Hill Craft Guild, Inc. Mr. Senn was also a member of the Oak Ridge Masonic Lodge #492. Mr. Senn is survived by his loving wife of 43 years, Mrs. Dorothy S. Senn of Oak Ridge; three sons, Mark Ronald Senn and his wife, Susan of Oak Ridge, David Lawrence Sean of Oak Ridge and Stephen Lyle Senn of Nashville; three grandchildren, Samantha Senn of Oak Ridge, Rebecca Senn and Jeremy Senn of Nashville. Funeral services will be held Friday, Jan. 10 at 2 p.m. at First Baptist Church in Oak Ridge. Rev. Larry Dipboye will officiate the service. The family will receive friends Thurs. evening from 6-8 at McCarty-Martin Oak Ridge Funeral Home. Interment will follow the service at Oak Ridge Memorial Park. The family requests that any memorials be in the form of donations to the First Baptist Church Organ Fund &/or Contact Teleministries.
