<head>
	<title>City seeks ad campaign to attract more visitors</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper Business News">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<a href="/"><img src="../../images/flag.gif" alt="Knoxville News-Sentinel Online -- Business News" align=bottom border=0 width=595 height=176></a><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td align=left valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 08, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>City seeks ad campaign to attract more visitors</B></font><basefont size=6><!--SUBHEAD--></basefont></FONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I>By Eleni Chamis, News-Sentinel business writer</I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		<FONT SIZE="+2">T</FONT>he Tombras Group is developing a marketing campaign for the Knoxville Convention and Visitors Bureau to convince more groups to hold meetings here, as well as to convince more tourists to spend the night, eat and shop here.
<P>   But first, they have to stop in Knoxville.
<P>   &#39;&#39;We need to be more than one of the many gateways to the Smokies,&#39;&#39; said Steve Richardson, a Tombras account supervisor who is overseeing the campaign for the bureau. &#39;&#39;We&#39;re more than that. We need to be something more than Big Orange Country. . . . We&#39;re more than a nice stopover place for people traveling along the interstates.&#39;&#39;
<P>   It&#39;s been 15 years since the bureau hired an advertising agency to develop a marketing communications plan, said Mike Wilds, executive director of the Knoxville Convention and Visitors Bureau.
<P>   The plan could include all types of advertising, from newspapers, trade publications and the Internet to television and radio ads.
<P>   &#39;&#39;We felt like prior to Tombras starting their creative processes, it would be good if some community leaders had the opportunity to share with them their views on Knoxville and how they feel about what is there to attract people to Knoxville and how Knoxville should be positioned,&#39;&#39; said Wilds.
<P>   About 25 business and community leaders attended two focus group sessions last month conducted by Tombras.
<P>   
<P>   &#39;&#39;The product in part is how the community sees itself,&#39;&#39; said Richardson. &#39;&#39;We got them all in the same room to probe ideas and opinions of how they saw Knox County&#39;s best selling points.&#39;&#39;
<P>   Many of the group&#39;s comments focused on what they saw as Knox County&#39;s strength as a &#39;&#39;hub&#39;&#39; for the region, and on a renewed spirit for marketing the county as a destination.
<P>   &#39;&#39;We&#39;re at a crossroads with expanding air service and the convergence of interstates,&#39;&#39; Richardson said. &#39;&#39;We&#39;re at a crossroads for nature and technology with a large number of area attractions, venues, and events. We&#39;re the hub in the middle of all that.&#39;&#39;
<P>   The core of the program needs to focus on getting tourists to stay in Knox County, he added.
<P>    &#39;&#39;We want them to spend the night here, eat in our restaurants, and shop with our merchants,&#39;&#39; he added. &#39;&#39;For them to go to the mountains one day is fine but we want them to come back here to spend the night.&#39;&#39;
<P>   In addition, the county may have to limit its access to larger-scale conventions because of its lack of adequate facilities, but will continue to target smaller meeting groups such as military reunions and religious organizations, as well as target families and other leisure travelers.
<P>   A preliminary plan will be submitted to Wilds by the end of January. Most of the plan will be funded by the hotel/motel tax.
<P>   The bureau also plans to seek further funding from the state, and through promotional programs and cooperative ventures. 
<P>   The Tombras Group was unanimously selected after a recommendation from the Knox County Tourist Commission&#39;s advertising subcommittee. Five other agencies were interviewed.
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
