<P>
<P><B>MURRAY, ADA (MAMIE) - </B>age 94, of Loudon, went home to be with the Lord 9:15 p.m. Sunday, January 5, 1997, at Loudon Health Care Center. Awaiting her heavenly arrival is her husband, George Murray; parents, Rev. Frank and Fannie Stephens Keller; and four beloved children, Dennis, J.R. and D.M. Murray, Marie Tilley. Survivors left to celebrate her life, devoted daughter, Frankie M. Shubert, Loudon; daughter-in law Lena Murray of Loudon; eight grandchildren; 18 great-grandchildren; five great-great-grandchildren. The family wishes to thank the staff of Loudon Health Care Center for the wonderful care and love given to our mother and grandmother. Funeral services 2 p.m. Tuesday, Loudon Funeral Home Chapel, Rev. Bernard Courtney officiating. Interment Oak Grove Cemetery, Madisonville. Pallbearers: grandsons, Bud Tilley, Charles, Ted, Ryan and Jonathan Sitzlar, Chris Moses and Wayne Gordon. The family will receive friends 12 noon-2 p.m. Tuesday, Loudon Funeral Home.
<P>
<P><B>OLIVER, LOUIS ALVA - </B>age 89, of Kimberlin Heights, died 7:52 p.m. Friday, Jan. 3, 1997, at Knoxville Convalescent Home. He was born Sept. 25, 1907, son of Henry Douglas and Ida Elizabeth Oliver. Preceded in death by his dear wife, Lucy Ann Ebnother Oliver; parents; brothers, John, William, Elmer and Henry Oliver; sisters, Paralee Hood, Louvenia Dearmond, Carrie McMurray, Matlida Jansen, Minnie Bell Oliver and Myrtle Oliver. Survivors: son and daughter-in-law, Gerald and Margie Oliver; grandson, Kevin Oliver; brother, Theodore R. Oliver; sister, Ruth E. Crisp; and brother-in-law, Harry G. Crisp; niece and husband, Harriet and Rene Jordon; nephew, Henry Oliver. Graveside service and interment 11 a.m. Tuesday at Calvary Cemetery, Rev. Rocky Johnson officiating. The body may be viewed before and during the service. Please omit flowers. Memorials may be made to the American Cancer Society. Atchley Funeral Home, Sevierville, in charge.
<P>
<P><B>PEARSON, GEORGE EDWARD (ED) - </B>age 83, of Knoxville, died 11 a.m. Sunday, January 5, 1997, at Mariner Health of Norris. Member of Inskip Baptist Church, retired from ORNL. Preceded in death by first wife, Rosie Brooks Pearson; and son, George Pearson. Survivors: wife, Margaret Pearson of Knoxville; daughter and son-in-law, Rhonda and Mike Barlow, Cookeville; son and daughter-in-law, Wayne and Greta Pearson, Knoxville; grandson, Andy Barlow, Cookeville; step-daughter and husband, Sandy and Charles Smith of Knoxville; sister and brother-in-law, Bessie and Clinton Moore, Bells, Tenn.; sisters, Hester Buford, Bells, Tenn., Katherine Talarico, Cohaset, Mass., Violet Hebrinik, Bethel Island, Calif.; brothers and sisters-in-law, Lem and Blondel Pearson, Bells, Tenn., Jessie and Hazel Pearson, Toone, Tenn.; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 2:30 p.m. Tuesday at Stevens Mortuary Chapel, Rev. Ernest Condee, Rev. Roberts Sanders officiating. Interment Greenwood Cemetery. Arrangements by Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
<P>
<P><B>RODDY, THAD WILLIAM - </B>age 15, of Friendsville, died Friday, January 3, 1997, at the University of Minnesota Children&#39;s Hospital in Minneapolis. He was a member of First Cumberland Presbyterian Church, a sophomore at William Blount High School, and was a member of the William Blount High School football team. Thad was preceded in death by his grandparents, Frank and Julia Roddy, and Earl and Vera Cross; grandfather, Eddie Teffeteller; great-grandmothers, Augusta Delozier and Martha Davies. Survivors include mother and stepfather, Jean and Dan Teffeteller of Friendsville; father and stepmother, Bill and Glynda Roddy of Elkhart, Texas; sister and brother-in-law, Lynn and Tracy Brooks of Knoxville; sisters, Robin Delozier, Tina Roddy, both of Maryville, Randi Roddy of Friendsville; brothers, Tommy Roddy of Maryville, Pete Teffeteller of Kodak; grandmothers, Louise Teffeteller, Carrie Horton; special grandmother, Virginia Delozier; brother-in-law, Jim Delozier of Maryville; nephews, Nicholas Delozier, Christopher Roddy; nieces, Sarah Delozier, Emily Brooks; several aunts, uncles and cousins; special friends, Bethany Morton, Allison Roberts, Robert Miller, Sara Beth Loveday, Mandy McBath, Mrs. Helen Webb, Michelle Bishop. Funeral services will be held at 5 p.m. Wednesday in the William Blount Gymnasium with Rev. Ronald Longmire and Pastor Mark Grubb officiating. Friends will meet at 2 p.m. Thursday at Carpenter&#39;s Cemetery for the interment service. The family will receive friends at the school following the service. McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home, Maryville, in charge.
<P>
<P><B>SHARP, ELSIE FREDA - </B>age 96, of Knoxville, passed away Saturday, January 4, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Hospital. She was a member of the Seventh-day Adventist Church. Preceded in death by husband, Robert H. Sharp; infant son, James E. Sharp; daughters, Maude E. Sharp and Frances Sharp Glenn. Survivors: son, Robert H. Sharp, Jr.; daughters, Allie M. Sharp, both of Knoxville, and Charlotte S. Webb, Maryville; daughter and son-in-law, Geneva and Lealand Cody, Springhill, Fla.; granddaughters and husbands, Donna Dixon, Cheryl and David Garner, Felecia and David McClanahan; grandsons and wives, Anthony Sharp, Scott and Marlene Webb, Robert III and Cindy Sharp; 12 great-grandchildren; sister, Ada Elizabeth Holman, Blaine, Tenn. Funeral service 8 p.m. Tuesday, Rose Chapel, Pastor John Cooper officiating. Family and friends will meet at Woodlawn Cemetery at 10:45 a.m. Wednesday for graveside and interment services at 11 a.m. Pallbearers: David Garner, David McClanahan, Scott Webb, Anthony Sharp, Robert H. Sharp III, Charles Brown. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Seventh-day Adventist Church, 3611 Kingston Pk., Knoxville, TN 37919. The family will receive friends 7-8 p.m. Tuesday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
