<P><B>SHARP, ROSA - </B>age 89, died Monday, January 6, 1997, at Church Hill Life Care Center. She was born in Anderson County, Tenn. She had resided in Nashville for several years and moved to Kingsport six years ago. She was preceded in death by her husband, Charlie Sharp; and parents, Francis and Martha Ridenour. Survivors: one daughter, Mrs. Bruce (Lois) Moore, Kingsport; three sons, Donald Sharp, Hoenwold, Tenn., Vasco Sharp, Westpoint, Tenn., and Lewis Sharp, White Bluff, Tenn.; one brother, Robert Ridenour, Andersonville, Tenn. Calling hours will be 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at Oak Hill Funeral Home, Kingsport. Funeral services will be conducted at 8 p.m. Wednesday in the funeral home chapel with Rev. Jerry Northam officiating. Graveside services will be conducted at 11:30 a.m. Thursday at the National Veterans Cemetery in Knoxville, Tenn. Oak Hill Funeral Home is in charge of local arrangements.
