<P><B>SMITH, MILTON R. - </B>age 84, of 3237 Fountain Park Blvd., passed away January 5, 1997, at U.T. Hospital. He retired from Standard Coffee Co. of New Orleans after 35 years. A Baptist and member of Kingston Union Lodge #38 F&AM Survived by daughters and sons-in-law, Janice S. and Vern R. Basham, Sherry J. and Bobby W. Hicks of Knoxville; son, Sidney R. Smith of Ft. Myers, Fla.; stepdaughters and sons-in-law, Norma Jean and Pete Campbell, Linda and Howard Armstrong, and Patricia Johnson of Knoxville; special friend, Kenny Goans. He will be greatly missed by ten grandchildren and 23 great-grandchildren. Family and friends will meet at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel Wednesday by 9:30 a.m. and will proceed to Greenwood Cemetery for a 10 a.m. graveside service with Rev. Rodney Burnette officiating and a solo by Kathy Hicks. Pallbearers: Bill Knight, Jeff Johnson, Steve Hicks and Roark Basham. Honorary pallbearers: Grady Hughes, Bobby White and J.B. Tawzer. The family will receive friends 6:30-8:30 p.m. Tuesday, followed by a Masonic memorial service by Kingston Union Lodge #38 F&AM at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
