<P><B>STAMPS, FLORENE FOUST - </B>age 77, of Lake City, passed away Monday, January 6, 1997, at Fort Sanders Regional Medical Center, Knoxville. She was a member  of Main Street Baptist Church, Lake City. Preceded in death by parents, Henry Clay and Litha Jane Davis Foust; son-in-law, Jerry Smiddy. Born August 8, 1919 in Anderson County. Survivrs: husband of 56 years, Stuart R. Stamps, Lake City; daughters, Elaine Smiddy, Norris, Jo Anne Swann and husband, Charles, Andersonville, Judy Bates and husband, Gary, Norris; grandchildren, Kimberly Butler and husband, Kevin, Lansing, Mich., Lesley Swann, Norcross, Georgia, Krista Bates, Norris, Adam Bates; sisters, Catherine Glandon, Kingston, Margaret Fox Best and husband, Walter, Clinton, Jean Hunt and husband, Curtis, Oak Ridge; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 8 p.m. Tuesday, January 7, at Main Street Baptist Church with the Rev. Don Martin and Dr. Ray Jones officiating. Interment 11 a.m. Wednesday in Woodhaven Memorial Gardens. Memorials may be made to Main Street Baptist Church, P.O. Box 405, Lake City, Tennessee 37769. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Tuesday at Main Street Baptist CHurch, Lake City. Cox Funeral Home, Lake City, in charge of arrangements.
