<P><B>STYLES, MARY LEE - </B>age 82, of North Knoxville, died Saturday evening, January 4, 1997, at St. Mary&#39;s Regional Medical Center. She was a longtime member of Oakwood Baptist Church and the Ruth Sunday School Class. She retired from Palm Beach Company with almost 50 years service. Member of Amalgamated Clothing Workers Union. She was preceded in death by sisters, Cumie Greene, Lucy Kooch, Berdell Henson; and brother, Carter B. Styles, Sr. Survivors: sister-in-law, Mrs. Iva Styles of Knoxville; brother-in-law, E.P. (Ras) Henson of Asheville, N.C.; special nephew, Adam Hilton; and several other nephews and nieces; special friends, Dorene Lay and Jane Kerr, both of Knoxville. Funeral service 12 noon Tuesday, Rose Broadway Chapel, Rev. Larry Young officiating. Interment Trentville Cemetery. Pallbearers: Carter Styles, Denny Styles, Marshall Kooch, Jerry Kooch, Tony Kooch and Shawn Kooch. Honorary pallbearers: members of the Ruth Sunday School Class, Oakwood Baptist Church. Arrangements by Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
