<P><B>THORNTON, LLOYD LAWSON - </B>age 85, of Maryville, died Monday, January 6, 1997, at Blount Memorial Hospital. He was an active member of Broadway United Methodist Church. Employed at ALCOA from 1941-75, he served in management positions in the personnel department. He was educational coordinator at Blount National Bank from 1975-86. Survivors include wife, Dorothy Pardue Thornton; sons, Lloyd L. Thornton, Jr. and wife, Linda of Indianapolis, Ind., John C. Thornton and wife, Eileen of Chattanooga; daughter, Anne Thornton Reynolds and husband, Randy of Marietta, Ga.; grandchildren, Emily and Mark Reynolds, Dori, Johnny, Ryan, Katie and Sam Thornton; brother and sister-in-law, Cecil and Gertrude Thornton of Harlan, Ky.; sisters-in-law, Hazel Thornton of Newport, Lucy Thornton of Gastonia, N.C. Funeral services will be held at 2 p.m. Wednesday at Broadway United Methodist Church with Rev. Robert A. Hayes officiating. The interment will follow in Grandview Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6:30-8 p.m. Tuesday at McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home and from 1-2 p.m. Wednesday at the church. The family suggests that memorials be made to Broadway United Methodist Church, 309 E. Broadway, Maryville, TN 37804. McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home, Maryville, in charge.
