<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="10">
    <tr>
        <td valign="top" width="150"><i>January 06, 1997</i> </td>
        <td width="470"><font size="6"><b>Knox Briefs<!--SUBHEAD--></b></font><h3>Murder
        suspect jailed after hospital release</h3>
        <p>A 16-year-old murder suspect who was shot after he
        allegedly robbed a fellow gang member was released from a
        hospital Sunday and booked into the Knox County Jail. </p>
        <p>Melvin ''Little Melvin'' Davis was being held Sunday
        evening in the downtown jail in lieu of $70,000 bond on
        charges of aggravated robbery and aggravated assault.
        Davis had been hospitalized at Baptist Hospital of East
        Tennessee. </p>
        <p>Davis, also known as Melvin Tate, is a member of the
        East Side gang, whose members hail from East Knoxville,
        police have said. He is accused in the May 18 shooting
        death of Brittany Shenice Daniels, 5. </p>
        <p>Brittany was shot as she played on a sidewalk in
        Lonsdale Homes housing project when a group of East Side
        gang members drove up to the curb and opened fire,
        according to police. </p>
        <p>Davis turned shooting victim on Christmas Eve, one day
        after he allegedly robbed William ''Junebug'' Martin of
        $200 in the Walter P. Taylor Homes housing project,
        police said. Martin allegedly shot Davis but claimed
        Davis threatened him with a gun first. Police declined to
        charge Martin. </p>
        <p>Martin now is charged with attempted murder, however,
        after he allegedly shot another of Davis' friends,
        Jeremiah Davis, in a parking lot in the Austin Homes
        housing project Dec. 29. </p>
        <h3>Man driving stolen car faces cocaine charge </h3>
        <p>Police have arrested an East Knoxville man who
        allegedly has been dealing drugs out of a stolen car he
        insisted he bought from a 15-year-old boy, authorities
        said. </p>
        <p>Knoxville Police Department Patrol Officer Derek
        Weller charged Elmora Quince, 36, with possession of
        cocaine and marijuana for resale, driving on a revoked
        license and theft after an investigation at the Rama Inn,
        1500 Cherry St., where Quince had been staying. </p>
        <p>Weller said authorities believe Quince had been
        selling both powder and crack cocaine, as well as
        marijuana, from a stolen Toyota Camry. The Camry also
        bore a stolen license plate, Weller said. When Weller
        stopped Quince in the Camry outside the Rama Inn Saturday
        night, he said he discovered cocaine, marijuana and a
        large amount of cash. </p>
        <p>Quince told Weller he bought the stolen car from a
        15-year-old boy, but Quince insisted he did not know the
        boy or ask him for any documents to verify ownership of
        the car, Weller said. </p>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

