<P><B>BAILEY, CHARLES C. - </B>age 87, went to be with the Lord Friday, January 3, 1997. Member of West Lonsdale Baptist Church. Retired fireman of Knoxville City Fire Dept. after 25 years of service. Preceded in death by wife, Ellen Roach Bailey. Survivors: son, Robert E. Bailey Sr. of Andersonville, Tenn.; daughter and son-in-law, Nancy and Dr. Ray Gibson of Glasgow, Ky.; son and daughter-in-law, Bill and Joni Bailey Brabson of Knoxville; grandchildren, Kim Smith, Robert Bailey Jr., Elanda Mason, Rachel Gibson, Shannon Mills, Charles Brabson, Clifford Brabson, Amanda Brabson and Susan Brabson; nine great-grandchildren; sister, Ruby Greer. Funeral service 2 p.m. Monday, West Lonsdale Baptist Church, Rev. Bruce Robinson officiating, assisted by Bill Brabson. Body will lie in state one hour before service. Interment Woodlawn Cemetery. Pallbearers: Mike Smith, Greg Mason, Steve Bailey, Bob Bailey Jr., Bob Bailey III, Clifford Brabson, Jack Mills. Arrangements by Mynatt&#39;s.
<P>
<P><B>BOWLES, GERTRUDE G. - </B>age 98, of Knoxville, passed away Saturday, January 4, 1997, at Brakebill Nursing Home. She was of the Methodist faith. Preceded in death by husband, R.L. Bowles; children, Roy Eugene Bowles, Helen Grace Ogden, Nancy Ann Bowles. Survivors: son, Clarence Bowles; grandchildren, Gerard Bowles, Woodruff, S.C., Robert Stanley Ogden, Clarence E. Bowles, Jr., Lawrence E. Bowles, all of Knoxville; three great-grandchildren. Family and friends will meet at the West Adair entrance to Lynnhurst Cemetery at 12:45 p.m. Tuesday for graveside and interment service at 1 p.m., Dr. James A. Daugherty officiating. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Monday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
