<P><B>JOHNSON, JESS - </B>age 79, of Harriman, passed away Saturday, January 4, 1997, at Methodist Medical Center in Oak Ridge. Chairman deacon of Bazeltown Baptist Church. Former chaplain of the Roane County Honor Guard. Worked for Union Carbide. Member of Chapter 24 DVA Kingston, Harriman Junction Lodge 103 F&AM, Alcoa Consistory #175, Order of Eastern Star of Crystal Star 57 and Five Star Jubilee Singers. Johnson was named district commander of the second district for the American Legion at their state convention held July 4-6, 1969, at Chattanooga&#39;s Hotel. He served in the U.S. Army during World War II, seeing action in North Africa and Italy. He was wounded in action in the Italian Theatre. He was former commander of Post 232 at Harriman. Survivors: wife, Augusta Faye Johnson of Harriman; sister, Pearl Scott of Harriman; adopted son, Jess Julian Lester Johnson of Connecticut; adopted daughter, Dewanda Jean Lester Johnson of Connecticut; step-daughter, Mamie Jackson of Connecticut; step-son, James Lester of Connecticut; step-grandson, Jeffery Lester of Oxford, Ohio; special nieces, Vanda Johnson of Knoxville, Norman De&#39;Armond of Harriman; god granddaughter, Ashlei De&#39;Armond of Harriman; sisters-in-law, Barbara Johnson of Rockwood, Nellie Swafford of Kingsport; sister-in-law and brother-in-law, Kathryn and Rubin Hunter of Kingsport; brothers-in-law and sisters-in-law, Jack and Ruby Jean Boyd of Harriman, Mr. and Mrs. Arthur Boyd of Dayton, Ohio; brother-in-law, Charles Boyd of Dayton, Ohio; nieces and nephews, Mr. and Mrs. Ronald Morrison of Cleveland, Ohio; Lillie and Charles Douglas of Harriman; nieces, Helen Buttram of Cleveland, Ohio, Minnie Buttram of Cleveland, Ohio; nephews, Ralph Buttram of Cleveland, Ohio, David Buttram of Harriman, Winfred Johnson of Athens, Tenn., Thomas Johnson of Middletown, Conn.; a host of other grandnieces and grandnephews, relatives and friends. Fuenral 2 p.m. Tuesday at Bazeltown Baptist Church where the body will lie in state for one hour before services, Rev. Rue Eskridge officiating. Interment in Roane Memorial Gardens with full military honors by Roane County Honor Guard. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Monday at Kyker Funeral Home in Harriman with Masonic service to follow visitation.
