<P><B>WHITE, GLENDA SMITH - </B>age 53, of Knoxville, passed away Saturday, January 4, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Medical Center. She was a member of Brickyard Baptist Church. Preceded in death by parents, Glenn and Mildred Smith. Survived by husband, Hubert White; son and daughter-in-law, Rev. Anthony and Florine White; daughter, Jody L. White; grandson, Anthony Lee White; step-granddaughters, Anitrea, Jenia and Amanda Dalton; sister and brother-in-law, Luetta and Vaughn Smith. She will be sorely missed by a host of family and friends. Funeral service 1 p.m. Monday, Brickyard Baptist Church, Rev. Anthony White, Rev. Bud Lane and Rev. Gary Day officiating. Interment Bookwalter Cemetery. Pallbearers: Scott Hodges, Brian Welch, Jason Holbert, Hubert White, Jamie Webb, Willie White and Rev. Gary Day. The body will lie in state at the church one hour before services. Arrangements by Mynatt&#39;s.
