<P><B>YOHEY, WALTER A. JR. - </B>age 60, died Friday, January 3, 1997, at University of Tennessee Medical Center. Mr. Yohey was a graduate of the University of Tennessee, a retired AF officer and a self-employed businessman. He is survived by his wife, Inge of Farragut, Tenn.; sisters, Marie Drulis and husband, Francis of Warminster, Pa., and Mary Jane Hukalowics of St. Petersburg, Fla.; sister-in-law, Annelie Lienemann and husband, Klaus of Munich, Germany. Funeral Mass will be held Monday, January 6, 1997, at St. John Neumann Catholic Church, 225 Jamestown Blvd., Farragut, Tenn., at 12 noon with Father Patrick Brownell officiating. Arrangements by Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>YOUNG, JAMES NELSON - </B>age 69, of Merced, Calif., formerly of Rutledge, passed away Wednesday, January 1, 1997. He was preceded in death by parents, Pryor and Annie Young; sister, Ruby Donaldson; brothers, Ray and Holly. Survived by daughter, Larita Lindsey of New Market; brothers, J.E. of Indiana, Carroll of Virginia and Curtis of Bean Station; aunts and uncles, Mattie and Elijah Young of Knoxville, Hester Norton of Blaine, Rose Cabbage of Rutledge, and Carl Antrican of Knoxville; several nieces and nephews. Funeral arrangements are incomplete and will be announced by Smith Funeral Home in Rutledge.
<P>
<P>CONLEY L. CASSIDY
<P>I Have a Place in Heaven
<P>Please don&#39;t sing sad songs for me,
<P>Forget your grief and fears,
<P>For I am in a perfect place,
<P>Away from pain and tears...
<P>Sadly missed by wife, Ellen;
<P>sons and daughters-in-law,
<P>Steve and Cindy, Billy and Linda,
<P>Clyde and Shelia, and Wayne;
<P>brothers, Jarvis and Harvey;
<P>and grandchildren
<P>
<P>VIRGINIA (JENNY) PHILLIPS
<P>You have gone to be with Jesus and are in a better place. You are sadly missed with each passing day. Happy Birthday Mom.
<P>Love, Eugene, Cindy, Derek,
<P>Jeremy, Little Jenny
