		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Gala to kick off local fund-raiser</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">K</FONT>noxville College will host a black-tie gala from 9 p.m. to 1 a.m. Friday, Jan. 10, at The Foundry at World&#39;s Fair Park to kick off this year&#39;s local broadcast of The College Fund/UNCF annual telethon.
<P>   The theme is &#39;&#39;A Salute to Historically Black Colleges and Universities and Neighbors.&#39;&#39; Neighbors includes the University of Tennessee, Maryville College and Carson-Newman College.
<P>   Graduates, former students, teachers, staff and friends are invited to attend. A $25 donation entitles each supporter to an evening of music, dancing and food. For reservations or more information, call the Knoxville College Office of Institutional Advancement at 524-6842.
