<P><B>CROSS, MR. GEORGE WASHINGTON - </B>age 75, of 906 South Second St., Elizabethton, died Saturday, January 4, 1997, at his residence following an extended illness. Mr. Cross was a native of Sullivan County and had lived in Carter County since 1946. He was a son of the late Sam Lee and Venia Frances Fox Cross. He was a retired plasterer in construction. Mr. Cross was a World War II Army veteran. He was a member of Dashiell Masonic Lodge #238 F&AM, the R.D. Keller Chapter #214 R.A.M., the B.E. Wooten Council #119 R&SM, the Carter Commandery #37 K.T. and Jericho Shrine Temple. He was of the Baptist faith. Survivors include his wife, Ruby Tester Cross of the home; son and daughter-in-law, Rick and Laura Cross of Johnson City; daughter, Tammy L. Cross, Knoxville; sister, Reba Rasnick, Bluff City; granddaughter, Jennifer K. Cross, Johnson City; several nieces and nephews. Funeral services will be held 8 p.m. Monday in the Sunset Chapel of Hathaway-Percy Funeral Home with Rev. Bruce Hendrich officiating. A Masonic service will follow by Dashiell Masonic Lodge #238. Graveside service and interment will be held at 11 a.m. Tuesday in Happy Valley Memorial Park. Military honors wlil be accorded by Capt. Lynn H. Folsom, V.F.W. Post #2166. Active pallbearers will be Ralph Fletcher, Bill Yontz, Arthur Holsclaw, David Holsclaw, Junior McAninch, Glen Tester and Jack Tester. Honorary pallbearers are Johnny Williams, Steven Williams, Johnny VanHuss, Dwight King, Lewis Rasnick, Jake Carr and Buford McAmis. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Monday at the funeral home. Friends may call at the residence anytime. Hathaway-Percy Funeral Home, Sunset Chapel, is in charge of arrangements.
