<P><B>DeBLOIS, RUTH ELIZABETH - </B>age 80, passed away Friday, December 27, 1996, in Ft. Lauderdale, Fla., after an extended illness. Born in Toronto, Ontario, Canada, on March 14, 1916, and moved with her parents and brothers from Wheaton, Ill., in 1932 to Ft. Lauderdale, Fla. Miss DeBlois graduated from Ft. Lauderdale&#39;s &#39;&#39;Flying L&#39;&#39; Central High School in 1935, and attended Stetson College in Florida. She is survived by her loving brothers and sisters-in-law, William A. and Dorothy DeBlois of Knoxville, Tenn., and Thomas M. and Helen DeBlois of Toronto, Ontario, Canada; nephews, William A. DeBlois of San Antonio, Texas, Charles M. DeBlois of Wheaton, Ill., and Stephen E. DeBlois of Titusville, Fla.; and nieces, Lynn E. Lawrence of Mississauga, Ontario, Canada, and Janet Ellinor of Limerick, Ireland; as well as several grandnieces and grandnephews. She was preceded in death by her parents, Thomas Melville and Ruth Elizabeth DeBlois. Miss DeBlois was employed as a devoted receptionist and assistant by a dentist and numerous physicians in the Ft. Lauderdale area. She received the &#39;&#39;Licensed Practical Nurse&#39;&#39; designation which she maintained until her retirement. Miss DeBlois was a member of Church by the Sea in Ft. Lauderdale for many years and was a friend and loved by many people. She was active in hand crafts and was treasured by her family as she always remembered anniversaries and birthdays with cards. A memorial service will be held at Church by the Sea, Ft. Lauderdale, Fla., Feb. 22, 1997. Interment has taken place at Lauderdale Memorial Park. Memorial contributions may be made to Church by the Sea, 1705 S. Ocean Dr., Ft. Lauderdale, FL 33316. Arrangements by Fairchild Funeral Home, Ft. Lauderdale, (954) 763-4489.
