<P><B>GOLDEN, JAMES RICHARD - </B>age 95, of Holston Hills, passed away quietly from this life on New Years Day 1997. He was a member of First Presbyterian Church, an active member of Holston Hills Country Club, an avid golfer, a fisherman, a strong Republican, and grew up in Atlanta. He was advertising manager at the Knoxville Journal for 19 years and while there, during WWII, he met and later married Kathryn Sherer, who was heading the local Women&#39;s Army Corp. He later became advertising manager for JFG Coffee for 35 years until he retired at age 92. Survivors: wife, Kathryn Sherer Golden of Holston Hills; daughter and son-in-law, Carolyn Golden Lowe and Nathen Ted Lowe of Spokane, Wash.; son, James R. Golden of Knoxville; grandchildren, Elizabeth, Matthew and Carrie Lowe, Spokane, Melissa Golden Stedina, Knoxville. Funeral service will be following the Sunday Morning Service at the First Baptist Church, 510 W. Main St., with Dr. David Hull officiating. The interment will be in Columbia, S.C. In lieu of flowers, contributions may be made to the Knoxville Convalescent Center, Bachman Home for Children, or the United Jewish Appeal. Arrangements by McCarty Mortuary, 4004 Holston Drive.
