<P><B>HODGES, THERON HASKELL - </B>age 88, of Prince St., Sevierville, died January 4, 1997, after an extended illness. He was a member of First Baptist Church, Sevierville, where he served as deacon for many years. He was preceded in death by his father, Harry G. Hodges; mother, Lillie Mae Bales Hodges; sister, Pauline; and brothers, John and Edward, all of Boyds Creek. He is survived by his wife of 63 years, Mary Kate Howell Hodges; 3 nephews and several cousins. Mr. Hodges was a graduate of Carson-Newman College and did graduate work at George Peabody College. He spent his entire adult life in educational work having taught at Union Valley, Knob Creek and White&#39;s Elementary Schools and also at Sevier County High School. He was elected superintendent of Sevier County Schools at the age of 25 and served six terms, four without opposition. He served as Resource-Use Director for the Tennessee Department of Education and the T.V.A. and was public relations chairman for the Tennessee Teacher&#39;s Retirement System. He later served as director of the State Teacher&#39;s Retirement System for many years. He also served as a member of the board of trustees of Carson-Newman College and the board of directors of Sevier Medical Center. In earlier years he was president of the Sevierville Lions Club, Worshipful Master of Mountain Star Lodge No 197 Free and Accepted Masons, and was a member of Mountain View Chapter 163 Royal Arch Masons. He was a Scottish Rite Mason and also a Shriner. The funeral service will be 7:30 p.m. Monday evening, January 6, 1997, at Atchley&#39;s West Chapel with Dr. Grant Jones and Dr. Rich Liner officiating. The family will receive friends 6-7:30 p.m. Monday evening, January 6, 1997. Interment will be at Boyds Creek Cemetery on Tuesday morning at 10 a.m. Honorary pallbearers: Charles Blalock, Clifford Davis, Rudolph Douglass, Kenneth Rawlings, Jim Atchley, Herbert McCuiston, Jack Sherwood, Ben Headrick, Gordon Bales, Floyd Bales, Carl Ownby, John Fox, Edward Watson, Henry Hodges, Robert E. Dorsey, Phil McMahan, Edward Tipton, Kenneth Norton, Doyle Jones and members of the Sevier County Teacher&#39;s Association. Active pallbearers: John Hodges, Charles Ownby, Teddy Ingle, Paul Manis, Jerry Baxter and Tyler Trotter. The family requests that in lieu of flowers, donations be made to the Alzheimer&#39;s Association, Eastern Tennessee Chapter, 1924 Alcoa Hwy., Knoxville, TN 37920.
