<P><B>MINEFIELD, LAURA DIANE (HARDIN) - </B>age 36, of Knoxville, departed this life Thursday, January 2, 1997, at U.T. Medical Center. Preceded in death by her father, Jimmy M. Hardin, Sr. Survivors: devoted husband, Cassius A. Minefield, Sr.; sons, Cassius A. Jr. and Taurean S. Minefield; mother, Wanda A. Hardin; sisters, Janice and Wanda Hardin; brothers, Jimmy Jr., Anthony and Gregory (Bonita) Hardin; grandmother, Elizabeth Minefield, Montgomery, Ala.; mother and father-in-law, Rev. Walter and Carolyn Walls; uncle, Olden (Betty) Smith, Audrey C. Fine, Washington, D.C.; brothers-in-law, Virgil, Kendell and Henry C. Minefield; several nieces, nephews, other relatives and friends. The family will receive friends 7-7:30 p.m. Monday, January 6, 1997, at Unity Mortuary Chapel with funeral to follow, Dr. Jerry Blackman officiating. Interment will be 10 a.m. Tuesday, January 7, 1997, at Tennessee State Veterans Cemetery. Arrangements by Unity Mortuary.
