<P><B>RHYNE, CHARLES T., JR. - </B>age 74, of Newport, died Friday morning in Baptist Hospital of Cocke County after being in declining health for the past few years. Mr. Rhyne was a graduate of North Carolina State College. Following graduation, he returned to Newport and entered the family business, Rhyne Lumber Co., with his father. He was former chairman of the board of National Bank of Newport, was serving as vice-chairman at the time of his death, was on the Newport Utilities Board and the board of directors of Newport Federal Savings and Loan Association. He served as president and CEO of Rhyne Lumber Co., president of Wood Products Co., Inc., Newport Manufacturing Co., Newport Builders and R & W Properties. He was a member of the First United Methodist Church of Newport where he served on the board of trustees. He was active in civic affairs in Newport and Cocke County. He was involved in local and state politics, serving as chairman of the Cocke County Democratic Party. Member Newport Kiwanis Club. He is survived by his wife, Frances S. Rhyne, Newport; son, Charles T. Rhyne, III, Hilton Head, N.C.; daughters, Sally Pierce and Terry Mullins, both of Brentwood, Tenn.; sister, Mrs. Bill (Patsy) Williams of Newport; six grandchildren. Funeral services will be held at 4 p.m. Monday at the First United Methodist Church of Newport with the Rev. Dr. Charles Starks and the Rev. Dr. Castro Smith officiating. Burial will be in Union Cemetery. The family will receive friends the funeral home 6-8 p.m. Sunday. For those wishing to give memorials, please do so to the First United Methodist Church of Newport. Manes, Newport, in charge.
