	<title>ET lawyer named to appeals court</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 04, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>ET lawyer named to appeals court</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I>By Tom Humphrey, News-Sentinel Nashville bureau</I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">N</FONT>ASHVILLE -- Monroe County lawyer James Curwood Witt Jr., son of a judge and grandson of a prosecutor, was appointed to a new seat on the state Criminal Court of Appeals by Gov. Don Sundquist on Friday.
<P>    Witt&#39;s appointment completes the naming of three new Court of Criminal Appeals judges -- one for each grand division of the state -- that were authorized by the state Legislature last year.
<P>    The state&#39;s Judicial Selection Commission had sent Sundquist three nominees on Sept. 20. The governor picked Witt over Paula Voss, an assistant public defender in Knoxville, and Thomas Wright, a federal public defender in Greeneville.
<P>    &#39;&#39;Judge Witt has shown his commitment to fairness throughout his career,&#39;&#39; Sundquist said in a statement. &#39;&#39;His work with young people will bring an important perspective to the bench.&#39;&#39;
<P>    Witt, 47, is a graduate of Hiwassee College, Madisonville; Tennessee Wesleyan College, Athens; and the University of Tennessee College of Law. He has been in private practice at Madisonville since 1973 and served three years as Monroe County&#39;s juvenile judge.
<P>    He has served as president of the Monroe County Bar Association and the Boys and Girls Clubs of the Monroe area. He has also served as a member of the Tennessee Conference of Juvenile Court Judges, the Tennessee Judicial Council and the Tennessee Juvenile Justice Advisory Group.
<P>    He has four children and is a member of First United Methodist Church of Madisonville.
<P>    Witt&#39;s father was a circuit court judge in Monroe County, while his grandfather, Beecher Witt, was a district attorney general.
<P>    &#39;&#39;It is an honor that Gov. Sundquist has chosen me to fill this position,&#39;&#39; said Witt in a statement released by the governor&#39;s office. &#39;&#39;I look forward to joining my colleagues on the Court of Criminal Appeals to increase the efficiency of the appeals process in this state.&#39;&#39;
<P>    The three new court seats were created in response to reports that the appeals court workload had increased to a level where cases could be delayed.
<P>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<hr size=5>

