<P><B></B>
<P><B>BARNES, JAMES RAY - </B>age 34, of Knoxville, passed away Tuesday, December 31, 1996, at U.T. Hospital. Member of the Baptist faith. Preceded in death by a brother, William Edward Barnes. Survivors: parents, Horace and Helen Barnes; son, Adam Barnes; sister, Judy Barnes; brothers and sisters-in-law, Horace (Hoss) and Yvonne Barnes, Jr., and Robert and Tracy Barnes; beloved nephews and niece, Robbie, Wesley, Casey, Hector and Jackie; many aunts, uncles, cousins and friends. Family and friends will meet at McCarty Mortuary 9:45 a.m. Saturday and proceed to Ailordale Baptist Church Cemetery, Maynardville, for graveside services and interment at 11 a.m. Rev. Fred Goodson will officiate. Pallbearers: David White, Mike Day, Steve Day, Terry Fields, Danny Kinser and Johnny Swaggerty. Arrangements by McCarty Mortuary, 4004 Holston Drive.
<P>
<P><B>BEELER, PAULINE W. (POLLY) - </B>age 70, of 8900 Tazewell Pike, Corryton. We celebrate with her as she has gone to be with her heavenly father on Jan. 2, 1997. She was a very loved member of Corryton Baptist Church. Retired from Hillcrest Nursing Home. Greeting her there are her father and step-mother, Fate and Lela Graves; mother, Essie Foust; brothers, Kenny, Bill and Daryle Graves. Waiting to join her: her loving husband of 51 years, Delbert Clayton Beeler; along with him, her 6 devoted children, Linda Luttrell, Judy Cooper, Herschel Beeler, Teresa Flatford, Kyle Beeler and Clay Beeler; daughters-in-law and sons-in-law, Dean Luttrell, Clayton Cooper, Rose Beeler, Denny Flatford, Ginny Beeler and Deana Beeler. Polly&#39;s joy was her 14 grandchildren and 7 great-grandchildren. Greatly loved by her sisters, Shirley Skeen and Arlene Daniel; sister and brother-in-law, Patsy and Jimmy Lett; brothers and sisters-in-law, David and Jo Graves, Ronnie and Sharon Graves, all of Corryton; aunt, Helen Carmen; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 2 p.m. Saturday, Graveston Baptist Church, Rev. Johnny Beeler, Rev. Mark Kitts officiating. Interment Graveston Cemetery. The body will lie in state from 1-2 p.m. at the church. Music will be performed by Mike Harless and Judy Beeler. Pallbearers: Herschel, Kyle and Clay Beeler, Dean Luttrell, Richard and Chris Cooper, Tony Beeler. Arrangements by Mynatt&#39;s.
<P>
<P><B>BERRY, RUTH TILLERY - </B>of South Knoxville, passed away January 2, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Hospital. Member of Lake Hills Presbyterian Church. Employed with Mayo Seed Company for over 30 years as a bookkeeper. Member of the Tennessee Watercolor Society. Volunteer 4-H leader for 25 years. Avid genealogist. Preceded in death by husband of 50 years, Walter Houston Berry; sisters, Hazel Tillery, Jessie Paul, Alice Walker, Nancy Daughterty, Marie Tauscher; brother, Lloyd Tillery. Survivors: daughters and sons-in-law, Sherry and Marshall Saylors, Bowie, Md., Rebecca and Ronald Lee, Nashville; grandchildren, Mary, Marcia and Will Saylors, Caitlin Lee. Funeral service 2 p.m. Saturday, Lake Hills Presbyterian Church, Rev. James McTyre officiating. Interment Mt. Olive Cemetery. Memorials may be made to Lake Hills Presbyterian Church, 3805 Maloney Rd., Knoxville, TN 37920. Arrangements by Berry Funeral Home, Chapman Highway.
<P>
<P><B>BRYANT, EVERETT C. - </B>age 78, of Cleveland, passed away in a local hospital Thursday evening. He was affectionately called &#39;&#39;Pompie.&#39;&#39; Born March 16, 1918, in Claiborne County, he lived in Knoxville before making Cleveland his home in 1938. He was the son of the late Andrew Johnson and Rosa Bartlett Bryant, and was preceded in detah by his three brothers, S.I. Bryant, Hubert Bryant and Herbert Bryant, all of Cleveland. He was a longtime member of the First Baptist Church. He was the owner of Bryant Construction Company and later retired from Brown Stove Works as a purchasing agent. He served his country as a lieutenant in the U.S. Army Air Corps during World War II. He held membership in the Cleveland Jaycees, Kiwanis Club and the Cleveland Masonic Lodge No. 134. Survivors include his wife of 52 years, L&#39;Ene Biggs Bryant of Cleveland; daughters, Becky Osborne and Nanci Williams, both of Cleveland, and Carol Brock and husband, Leland of Hixson; seven grandchildren, Melissa Bigham Reuter and husband, Jason, Chrystie Bigham, Kelly Bigham, and Amy Osborne Waddle and husband, Jeff, all of Cleveland, Chad Williams and wife, Pam of Athens, Ga., Bryant Brock and Jonathan Brock, both of Hixson; one great-granddaughter, Rebecca Reuter of Cleveland; two sisters, Lois Caughron and Anita Bridges, and husband, Leamon of Knoxville; several nieces and nephews. Funeral services will be held 2 p.m. Saturday in the chapel of the Grissom Funeral Home with the Rev. Rob Peters and the Rev. Allan Lockerman officiating. Interment will follow in the Hilcrest Memorial Gardens with Chad Williams, Bryant Brock, Jonathan Brock, Jason Reuter, Jeff Waddle and Chris Wright serving as pallbearers. Honorary pallbearers are members of the Manly Sunday School Class, nephews, and Dr. Steve Williams. The family will receive friends 5-8 p.m. Friday at the Grissom Funeral Home and Saturday from 12 noon until time of service. Memorials may be made to the First Baptist Church Building Fund, Cleveland, TN or to the American Heart Association.
<P>
<P><B>CHANEY, DIXIE ALLEN - </B>age 80, of Sevierville, passed away Friday, January 3, 1997, at Sevier Medical Center. She was a member of the First Baptist Church of Sevierville for 69 years. She was preceded in death by her parents, John Russell and Carrie Free Allen; three sisters and five brothers. Survivors: husband of 61 years, Hugh Chaney; daughter and son-in-law, Carrie and Robert Murphy, Sevierville; son and daughter-in-law, Hulet and Joyce Chaney, Columbia, Tenn.; grandchildren, Rob Murphy, Kingsport, Tenn., Elizabeth Clark, Woolwine, Va., Darla Spire, Marietta, Ga., Jim Chaney, Columbia, Tenn.; four great-grandchildren; sister, Irene Ailey, Sevierville; brother, Rev. James D. Allen, Greeneville, Tenn.; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 7 p.m. Saturday in the East Chapel of Atchley Funeral Home, Dr. Rich Liner and Rev. Gordon Greenwell officiating. Interment 2 p.m. Sunday in Allen Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-7 p.m. Saturday at Atchley Funeral Home.
<P>
<P><B>DEVINE, JAKE - </B>age 81, of 2741 Hwy. 411 North, Madisonville, passed away 4:35 a.m. Friday, January 3, 1997, at U.T. Hospital. Member of Upper Shady Grove Baptist Church. Survivors: wife, Frances Melson Devine; daughters and sons-in-law, Geneva and Garland Best, Glena and Richard Aguirre, Ivy and Jack Harrill, Esther (Fuzzy) and Ray Cain, all of Madisonville, Jo and Gene Ogle, Riceville, Geraldine and Scott Dunn, Kathy Devine, both of Maryville; sons and daughters-in-law, Beechard and Edna Devine, Marie Devine, Larry and Brenda Devine, all of Madisonville, Rev. Leon and Donna Devine, Etowah, James and Nancy Devine, Greenback, Ronnie and Jackie Devine, Maryville; 20 grandchildren; 14 great-grandchildren; sisters, Lucy Pressley, Maryville, Ella Nichols, Vonore; brothers, Pete McMahan, Vonore, Austin Devine, Phillipines, Rose McMahan, Loudon; several nieces and nephews. Preceded in death by first wife, Dorothy Millsaps Devine; son, Ted Devine; and brother, Fred Devine. Funeral 8 p.m. Saturday, Biereley-Hale Chapel, Rev. Tyson Matoy officiating. Interment 2 p.m. Sunday, Haven Hill Memorial Gardens. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Saturday at Biereley-Hale Funeral Home, Madisonville.
<P>
<P><B>DODRILL, LOIS H. - </B>age 59, of Knoxville, went to be with the Lord Friday morning. Survivors: sister, Sue Lee of Louisville, Ky.; niece, Susan S. Lee of St. Louis, Mo. Family and friends will meet for a graveside service 12 noon Tuesday, Tennessee State Veterans Cemetery, Chaplain Jim Wilson officiating. Friends may call at their convenience Sunday and Monday at Mynatt&#39;s.
<P>
<P><B>FUGATE, ANNE MARY - </B>age 93, of Ewing, Va., was born May 4, 1903, and passed away January 3, 1997, at the Claiborne  County Hospital. She was a member of Morley Memorial Methodist Church. She was preceded in death by her husband, Hollis H. Fugate; one daughter, Mildred Ramsey. She is survived by her daughter, Nancy Brooks of Tazewell, Tenn.; daughter and son-in-law, Frankie and Harold Rutherford of Knoxville; son-in-law, Ryland Ramsey of Sneedville, Tenn.; four grandchildren; seven great-grandchildren. The family will receive friends 5-7 p.m. Sunday, January 5, 1997, with funeral services to follow at 7 p.m. in the Claiborne Funeral Home Chapel with the Rev. Eddie Overholt and Rev. Michael Buckles officiating. Graveside services 10 a.m. Monday in the Green Hills Cemetery. Claiborne Funeral Home in charge of arrangements.
<P>
<P><B>GODFREY, ELSIE CLARK - </B>age 90, of Knoxville, passed away Thursday, January 2, 1997, at St. Mary&#39;s Medical Center. She was a charter member of Tennessee Avenue Baptist Church. Preceded in death by husband, Edgar Lee Godfrey; parents, Frank and Emma Clark; daughters, Lois Elizabeth and Phyllis Jean Godfrey, Linda Ann Wood Gregory; sisters, Verna Perkins, Ollie Webb and Alice Tanner. Survivors: daughters, Doris Godfrey Whittle, Mary Lee Godfrey O&#39;Connor; sons and daughters-in-law, Carl E. and Ann Godfrey, Kenneth F. and Oneida Godfrey; 13 grandchildren; several great-grandchildren and great-great-grandchildren. Family and friends will meet at the main entrance to Greenwood Cemetery at 12:45 p.m. Saturday for graveside and interment services at 1 p.m. with Rev. Ralph Guthrie officiating. Arrangements by Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>GOLDEN, JAMES RICHARD - </B>age 95, of Holston Hills, passed away quietly from this life on New Years Day 1997. He was a member of First Presbyterian Church, an active member of Holston Hills Country Club, an avid golfer, a fisherman, a strong Republican, and grew up in Atlanta. He was advertising manager at the Knoxville Journal for 19 years and while there, during WWII, he met and later married Kathryn Sherer, who was heading the local Women&#39;s Army Corp. He later became advertising manager for JFG Coffee for 35 years until he retired at age 92. Survivors: wife, Kathryn Sherer Golden of Holston Hills; daughter and son-in-law, Carolyn Golden Lowe and Nathen Ted Lowe of Spokane, Wash.; son, James R. Golden of Knoxville; grandchildren, Elizabeth, Matthew and Cari Lowe, Spokane, Melissa Golden Stedina, Knoxville. Funeral service will be following the Sunday Morning Service at the First Baptist Church, 510 W. Main St., with Dr. David Hull officiating. The interment will be in Columbia, S.C. In lieu of flowers, contributions may be made to the Knoxville Convalescent Center, Buchman Home for Children, or the United Jewish Appeal. Arrangements by McCarty Mortuary, 4004 Holston Drive.
<P>
<P><B>GOODMAN, NANCY ANGEL - </B>of Talbott, Tenn., peacefully passed away Friday, January 3 after an extended illness at the Knoxville home of her daughter, Mrs. Cissie Pitts. She was 62 years of age. Mrs. Goodman was a partner in Remax Between the Lakes in Jefferson City. She was past regional vice president of the Tennessee Association of Realtors, and had served as chairman of the board, president and and director of the Morristown Board of Realtors. Mrs. Goodman had also been awarded a Lifetime Membership in the Million Dollar Club. She was the daughter of the late Kermit and Jane Angel of Knoxville. She was preceded in death by her husband of 47 years, J. Frank Goodman, Sr., who passed away December 12, 1996. Mrs. Goodman is survived by her daughter and son-in-law, Cissie and Monty Pitts; and daughter, Nan Goodman of Knoxville; sons, Gary T. Goodman, Frank Goodman, Jr. and his fiancee, Debora Reese, all of Talbott; grandchildren, Brad Goodman, Michael Goodman, Kendra Barnett, Tara Brewer, John G. Shepherd and Sandy Goodman; brother-in-law and sister-in-law, Thomas G. and Mary Goodman; niece, Cindy Goodman. Funeral services will be held 2 p.m. Sunday, January 5 at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel with Father Gene Smitherman officiating. Interment will be with her husband in Lynnhurst Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Saturday, January 4 at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P>HEINZ, MRS. NINA BELL WOLFEN<B>BARGER - </B>age 80, of Shannondale Health Care Center, Knoxville, passed away 4:30 p.m. Thursday, January 2, 1997, at Baptist Hospital of East Tennessee. Member of Macedonia United Methodist Church and the Loyalty Sunday School Class. Preceded in death by husband, Harry Louis Heinz, Jr. Survivors: son and daughter-in-law, Harry L. and Mickey Heinz, Cross Hill, S.C.; daughter, Patricia Heinz Thompson; daughter-in-law, Sandy McMurray; six grandchildren; one great-grandchild; sister, Lorene Lee, all of Knoxville; and many friends and staff of Shannondale Health Care Center. Family and friends will meet at the main entrance to Lynnhurst Cemetery at 1:15 p.m. Sunday for a 1:30 p.m. graveside service and interment, Rev. Larry Best officiating. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to Macedonia United Methodist Church. Friends may call at their convenience at Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
<P>
<P><B>HURST, HELEN - </B>age 70, of Knoxville, passed away at Ft. Sanders Regional Medical Center. She was a member of the Church of God. Survivors: son, Freddie Sexton; daughters, Wanda Cline, Betty Blair; several step-children, grandchildren and great-grandchildren. Family and friends will meet at 2:45 p.m. Sunday at Bell&#39;s Campground Cemetery for a 3 p.m. graveside service, Rev. Harley Tapp officiating. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Saturday at McCarty Mortuary, 4004 Holston Drive.
<P>
<P><B>IRICK, CATHERINE SUFFRIDGE - </B>age 84, of Knoxville, passed away Jan. 1, 1997. Member of Washington Pike United Methodist Church. Preceded in death by husband, Carl L. Irick; and son, Ronnie Irick. Survivors: sons and daughters-in-law, Carl L. (Buddy) and June W. Irick of Hendersonville, Tenn., William A. (Bill) and Teri Irick of Mason, Ohio; daughter and son-in-law, Cathy and Jon Bell of Powell; nine grandchildren; two great-grandchildren. Service 1 p.m. Saturday, Mynatt&#39;s Chapel, Rev. James Dougherty officiating. Interment Greenwood Cemetery. In lieu of flowers, donations may be made to the Alzheimer&#39;s Association, 1924 Alcoa Hwy., Knoxville, TN 37920. The family will receive friends 12 noon - 1 p.m. Saturday at Mynatt&#39;s.
<P>
<P><B>JACKSON, ARMETHINE HALL (ARMY) - </B>of 3807 Middlebrook Pike, Apt. 510, departed this life Friday, January 3, 1997, at Ft. Sanders Medical Center. The family will be at the home of Rev. Willie Hall, 4114 Holston Dr. Funeral arrangements are incomplete and will be announced later by Unity Mortuary.
<P>
<P><B>KERWIN, JOHN JOSEPH, SR. (JACK) - </B>age 76, of North Knoxville, passed away Friday, January 3, 1997. Member of Holy Ghost Catholic Church. Born St. Louis, Mo., May 25, 1920. Owner of East Tennessee Adjustment Company for 38 years. Army veteran of World War II. Secretary/treasurer of American Legion, Fountain City Post #126. Survivors: wife of 43 years, Dorothy H. Johnson Kerwin; sons and daughters-in-law, John and Merilee Kerwin, Michael and Jerri Kerwin; daughter and son-in-law, Mary and Mike Moreland; daughters, Kathy Kerwin and Connie Kerwin; grandchildren, Benjamin and Julia Kerwin, Kelly and Olivia Kerwin, all of Knoxville; sister, Mary Densem of Grants Pass, Ore.; special friend, Rodney Satterfield of Corryton. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Sunday, January 5th at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel with Rosary immediately following, Rev. Xavier Mankel officiating. Funeral Mass 1 p.m. Monday, January 6th, Holy Ghost Catholic Church, Rev. Phillip Thoni and Dr. James McCluskey officiating. Interment Woodlawn Cemetery. In lieu of flowers, please make donations to Jack Kerwin Memorial Fund, St. Joseph&#39;s School. Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel in charge.
<P>
<P><B>LOVE, MRS. HELEN CARR - </B>of Virginia Beach, Va., formerly of Maynardville and Nashville, died December 19, 1996, in Virginia Beach, Va. She was the daughter of the late Dr. John Harvey Carr and Ida Snoderly Carr of Maynardville. Member of Virginia Beach Christian Church. Survivors: husband, Clifford Love, Jr.; son and daughter-in-law, Clifford Love III and Suzanne S. Love, M.D.; grandchildren, David Clifford Love and Michael Isaiah Love, all of Virginia Beach, Va.; sister, Louise C. Brogan; brother, retired Major John H. Carr, both of Knoxville; sister-in-law, Mrs. Willard O. (Alvilva) Carr of Maynardville; seven nephews and one niece. Memorial service 11 a.m. Saturday, January 4, 1997, at Smithwood Baptist Church, Dr. C. Glenn Sullivan and Rev. Roscoe Harless officiating. Family will receive friends immediately after the memorial service. Memorials may be made to Carr Cemetery Maintenance Association, c/o Ralph Monroe, Treasurer, Box 309, Maynardville, TN 37807 and the Maynardville Baptist Church, Box 850, Maynardville, TN 37807. Arrangements by Stevens Mortuary, Oglewood Avenue at Broadway.
<P>
<P><B>LOY, ALBERTA COOMER - </B>of Halls, passed away Jan. 2, 1997, at U.T. Hospital. Member of Salem Baptist Church and former Sunday School teacher. Retired Knox County teacher after 35 years service and member Knox County Teachers Credit Union. Preceded in death by husband, Millard Loy; and parents, Will and Bessie Coomer. Survivors: daughters and sons-in-law, Janice and Dale Walker of Corryton, Susan and Chuck Brantley of Knoxville; grandchildren, Denise Walker of Nashville, Shelley Walker of Corryton, Claire and Graham Brantley of Knoxville; sisters and brothers-in-law, Ruth and Earl Haynes, Bessie Lee and Leonard Cook; sister, Madge Cain; sister-in-law, Hazel Loy of Knoxville; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 8 p.m. Saturday, Mynatt&#39;s Chapel, Rev. John Holland officiating. Family and friends will meet at 1:30 p.m. Sunday at Mynatt&#39;s and proceed to Greenwood Cemetery for interment at 2 p.m. Pallbearers: Bud Ford, David Boles, Buddy Daniels, Don Smith, Harold Wayland, Allen Wayland and David Sharp. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Saturday at Mynatt&#39;s.
<P>
<P><B>MAYES, JAMES W. - </B>age 90, of Maryville, died Friday, January 3, 1997, at his home. He was a member of Green Meadow United Methodist Church, an active member of the Alcoa Kiwanis, retired from ALCOA with over 42 years of service, member of the ALCOA 25 Year Service Club, a Scottish Rite Mason, member of the Masonic Lodge No. 719 F&AM, past patron of Prudence Chapter No. 270 Order of the Eastern Star. Mr. Mayes was preceded in death by his parents, J.W. Mayes and Araminta Tidd Mayes. Survivors include wife, Gladys &#39;&#39;Pat&#39;&#39; Mayes; son, James W. Mayes, Jr. of Maryville; stepson, Louie E. LeRoy of Athens, Tenn.; step-daughter, Patsy L. Slagle of Garland, Texas; grandchildren, Darrell Mayes of Birmingham, Wayne Mayes of Lenoir, N.C., Kevin B. Mayes of Fredericksburg, Va., Karen Mayes Johnson of Powell, Tenn.; great-grandchildren, Alicia Mayes, Kaitlin Mayes, Samantha Mayes, Matthew Mayes, Brandon Johnson, Brittany Johnson; step-grandson, James W. LeRoy; brother, Paul S. Mayes of Knoxville; niece, Sandra Kimmel of Gatlinburg, Tenn. Funeral services will be held at 5 p.m. Sunday in McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home Chapel with Rev. Martha Yeomans officiating. Family and friends will meet at 10 a.m. Monday at Grandview Cemetery for the interment service. The family will receive friends 4-5 p.m. Sunday at McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home, Maryville. Those who wish may make memorials to Green Meadow United Methodist Church, 1600 Louisville Rd., Alcoa, TN 37701.
<P>
<P><B>McCAMMON, AGNES SAYNE - </B>age 87, of South Knox County, passed away January 3, 1997, at Brakebill Nursing Home. She was a member of Stock Creek Baptist Church. Preceded in death by husband, Walter A. McCammon; brother, Manuel Sayne. Survivors: son, James T. McCammon, Knoxville; daughter and son-in-law, Dorothy M. and Joseph C. Collins of Fayetteville, Tenn.; granddaughter, Claudia Collins Morgan, Havelock, N.C.; sister, Mrs. Jack (Ruby) Godfrey, Maryville; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service 4 p.m. Sunday, Berry Chapel, with Rev. Dana Fachman and Rev. C.D. Hagaman officiating. Graveside service and interment 2 p.m. Monday at McCammon Family Cemetery. The family will receive friends 2-4 p.m. Sunday at Berry Funeral Home, Chapman Highway.
<P>
<P><B>McMAHAN, CLEO H. - </B>age 82, of Sevierville, died Thursday, January 2, 1997, at his home. He was a member and deacon of Richardson&#39;s Cove Baptist Church. He was preceded in death by his parents, Berry and Miley Jane McMahan; brothers, Ted and Mitchell McMahan; daughter-in-law, Bernice McMahan; son-in-law, James A. (Bud) Messer; grandson, Michael Harrison McMahan. Survivors: wife, Exa Valentine McMahan; children, Harry McMahan and wife, Miriam, Merle Messer, Don McMahan and wife, Sandra, James C. (Jim) McMahan and wife, Portia, Judy Manis and husband, Norman; grandchildren, Elaine Mauter and husband, Bill, Leslie Atchley and husband, Ricky B., Ted McMahan and wife, Norva, Elizabeth McCarter and husband, David H., Lynn McMahan and wife, Peggy, Lisa Roach and husband, Chuck, Tracy Schappacher and husband, Wayne, Christy McMahan, Jimmy McMahan and wife, Brandy, Cecily Bradshaw; great-grandchildren, Christopher, Michael, Zack, Mitchell, Sarah, Matthew, Rebecca, Jessica; sisters, Leona Pendley and Ruth Ramsey; sisters-in-law, Gladys McMahan and Henrietta Hendrickson. Funeral service 8 p.m. Saturday in the West Chapel of Atchley Funeral Home, Rev. Edward Parton and Rev. Melvin Carr officiating. Interment 1 p.m. Sunday in Smoky Mountain Memory Gardens. Serving as honorary pallbearers will be Blaine (K.O.) McMahan, Oscar Dunn, Paul Henderson, Thurman Cates, Conley Mack Marshall, Ted Ogle, Gerald Bales, Chuck Thomas and Timmy McGill. Memorials may be made to Richardson&#39;s Cove Baptist Church, % Janella Justus, 3152 Pittman Center Rd., Sevierville, TN 37876. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Saturday at Atchley Funeral Home, Sevierville.
<P>
<P><B>MILLER, HELEN RUTH LOWERY - </B>age 66, of South Knoxville, went to meet our Lord Friday, January 3, 1997. Retired from East Tennessee Baptist Hospital. Preceded in death by husband, Charles Miller, Sr.; parents, William and Esther Lowery; brother, Frank Lowery. Survivors: daughter and son-in-law, Elizabeth and Jimmy Carter; son and daughter-in-law, Charles and Jane Miller; five grandchildren; three great-grandchildren; brothers, Wayne, George and Eddie Lowery; sisters, Barbara Love, Mary Hawkins, Dorothy Osborne, Becky Gosnell; brother-in-law, Ottis Beals; special friends, Emma Clark, Jearl Arwood, Phil Groos, Faye Irwin. Funeral 7:30 p.m. Saturday, Atlantic Avenue Baptist Church, Rev. David Rush and Rev. Phil Groos officiating. Special music by Vickie Rush. Graveside service 2 p.m. Sunday, Knob Creek Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-7:30 p.m. Saturday, Atlantic Avenue Baptist Church. Berry Funeral Home, Chapman Highway.
