<P><B>MOORE, ELBERT (RED) - </B>age 77, of Sweetwater, passed away Thursday, January 2, 1997, at Sweetwater Hospital. He was preceded in death by his parents, Robert and Suvilla Moore; brothers, Cas Moore, Ernest Moore, Garrison Moore; sisters, Charity Wicker, Jessee Lee Moore; and son-in-law, James Irving Render. He was a member of Paint Rock Baptist Church, VFW Gold Post 5156, UAW Local 594 and a veteran of World War II. Survivors: wife, Alice Ruth Moore; daughters and son-in-law, Nelma and Lynn Williams, Fonda Render, Marietta (Mary) Moore; sons and daughters-in-law, Ronald and Taffy Moore, Philip and Tracy Moore; sisters, Ellen Bettis, Nora Brown; brothers and sisters-in-law, Clifford and Callie Moore, Emitt and Blanche Moore, Robin Moore; ten grandchildren; seven great-grandchildren; several nieces and nephews. The body is at Kyker Funeral Home, Sweetwater, where the family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Saturday. Funeral services 2 p.m. Sunday in Kyker&#39;s Chapel with Rev. Joe Roysden officiating. Interment to follow at West View Cemetery. Military honors provided by VFW Gold Post 5156.
