<P><B>NELSON, M. JEFF - </B>age 18, of Blockhouse Valley Rd., Clinton, Tenn., passed away Thursday, January 2, 1997, at Harriman City Hospital due to an auto accident. He was the son of Mike and Aline Garner Nelson of Clinton. He was of the Baptist faith. He was self-employed doing horse shoeing. He was preceded in death by grandmother, Wanda Garner. He is survived by parents and sister, Beverly Hogan of Clinton, Tenn.; beloved girlfriend, Angela Loy of  Clinton; grandparents, Rev. Archie and Ruby Nelson of Clinton, and James Garner of Clinton; nephew, McKenzie Hogan of Clinton; niece, Sara Hogan of Clinton; several aunts and uncles and many friends. Funeral services will be conducted at 8:30 p.m. Saturday, January 4, 1997, at the Holley-Gamble Funeral Home Chapel with Rev. Gary Smith officiating. Graveside services will be conducted at 2 p.m. Sunday, January 5, 1997, at Farmers Grove Cemetery, Clinton, Tenn. The family will receive friends 7-8:30 p.m. Saturday, January 4, 1997, at Holley-Gamble Funeral Home Chapel, Clinton.
