<P><B>WESTGATE, CHARLES JOSEPH, JR. - </B>age 69, of 740 W. Meadecrest Drive, Knoxville, died Thursday morning, January 2, 1997, in the Ft. Sanders Park West Medical Center in Knoxville. He was born in White Plains, N.Y. on October 24, 1927, a son of the late Charles Joseph and Ethel Frances Lewis Westgate. He was a member of the Cornerstone Church of Waynesboro, a Navy veteran, having served in both World War II and the Korean Conflict, and was a 1955 graduate of the Philadelphia College of Pharmacy and Science. Employed as a pharmacist for 36 years, he worked with the Standard Drug Co. for 23 of those years, after which he retired. Mr. Westgate was a member of the International Fellowship of Christian Businessmen, of which he also served on the board of directors. In addition to his parents, he was preceded in death by his wife, Mary Elizabeth Peden Westgate on June 19, 1987. Survivors include his son, Major Charles Joseph Westgate, III of Dayton, Ohio; daughters, Charlene Westgate of Chandler, Ariz., Deborah Gray of Knoxville, Cynthia Simmons of Stuarts Draft, and Pamela Westgate of Roanoke; sister, Ethel Kistler of Allentown, Pa.; grandchildren, Michael and Jason Gray of Knoxville, Christian Snider and Joseph Westgate, both of Chandler, Ariz., Tyler and Kirby Elizabeth Simmons of Stuarts Draft; special friends, Libby Layman and Jesse and Midge Kester. A service will be conducted at 3 p.m. Sunday in the Waynesboro Chapel of Etter-Reynolds Funeral Service by the Rev. Greg Mayo. Burial will follow in Barren Ridge Church of the Brethern Cemetery. Active pallbearers: Mike Zirkle, Lanny Campbell, Kendall Layman, Tony Viglione, Myron Jones, Jesse Kester, Barry Tomey and David Showers. Honorary pallbearers will be members of the Shenandoah Valley Chapter of the International Fellowship of Christian Businessmen. The family will receive friends 7-8 p.m. Saturday in the Waynesboro Chapel of Etter-Reynolds Funeral Service. Memorial contributions may be made to the Cornerstone Church Building Fund, 403 W. Main St., Waynesboro, VA 22980.
