		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		<h3>Kentucky will spend $24 million on stadium</h3> 
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>     The University of Kentucky has begun soliciting bids for a $24 million expansion and renovation of Commonwealth Stadium, despite record low attendance this past season at the 23-year-old stadium.
<P>    The expansion, which most likely will be done before the 1998 season, will increase capacity from 57,800 to between 63,000 and 66,000, athletic director <B>C.M. Newton </B>said Thursday.
<P>    &#39;&#39;We think it&#39;s in our best interest financially to do this, or we wouldn&#39;t do it,&#39;&#39; Newton told The Courier-Journal. &#39;&#39;And that&#39;s what our studies showed.&#39;&#39;
<P>    UK was left with more than 100,000 empty seats last football season -- the lowest attendance since Commonwealth Stadium opened in 1973. School officials, however, are confident they can fill seats in the future.
<P>    The anticipated construction will include luxury suites in the corners of the stadium, new and renovated restrooms, concession-area renovation and expansion and the addition of a &#39;&#39;Wildcat stadium store.&#39;&#39;
<P>    Newton said the work will be done in phases, beginning with renovations before the 1997 season. If all goes as planned, it will end with construction of 20 to 40 luxury boxes and permanent end-zone seating -- replacing metal bleachers -- before the 1998 season.
<P>
<P><h3>College football</h3>
<P>
<P><B></B><B>Tony Daniels,</B> a defensive end at Texas Tech, said that he was making himself available for the NFL draft. He is the second Red Raiders&#39; junior to make that decision, joining star tailback <B>Byron Hanspard</B>. Texas Tech opens next season at Tennessee.
<P>* Another junior declaring for the NFL draft: Virginia defensive back <B>Ronde Barber,</B> who made 15 interceptions in three seasons.
<P>* <B>Bill Bleil,</B> Western Carolina&#39;s offensive coordinator and offensive line coach, was hired as the school&#39;s head coach, replacing <B>Steve Hodgin,</B> who was fired Nov. 18 after seven seasons (and a 31-45 record) as the Catamounts&#39; head coach.
<P>* The NCAA has accepted Clemson&#39;s penalties in the case of defensive end <B>Trevor Pryce </B>illegally using a university long-distance credit card. Pryce, an All-ACC player, had to sit out two games and Clemson froze coach <B>Tommy West&#39;s </B>salary for a year because he waited almost a month before reporting the violation. 
<P>* The U.S. Military Academy is nearing a decision whether or not to join Conference USA in football.
<P>* Kansas City&#39;s <B>Marty Schottenheimer </B>(South) and the Washington Redskins&#39; <B>Norv Turner </B>(North) will be coaches in the Senior Bowl at Mobile, Ala., a Jan. 18 matchup of senior college  players looking to become pros.
<P>* Alabama confirmed that <B>Ellis Johnson </B>and <B>Neil Callaway </B>will join the Crimson Tide&#39;s coaching staff as defensive coordinator and offensive line coach, respectively.
<P>
<P><h3>Hockey</h3>
<P>
<P>* <B>Mark Messier, Mario Lemieux </B>and <B>Paul Coffey,</B> with 32 years of All-Star Game experience among them, were selected to the Eastern Conference team for the game Jan. 18 at San Jose.
<P>* The NHL suspended Hartford Whalers center <B>Keith Primeau </B>for two games for slashing Washington&#39;s <B>Joe Juneau</B>.
<P>
<P><h3>Basketball</h3>
<P>
<P>* No. 12 Hiwassee lost to No. 1-ranked Central Florida 109-77 in the McDonald&#39;s Classic women&#39;s tournament at Ocala, Fla. <B>Cindy Ainsworth </B>had 20 to lead Hiwassee (13-1).
<P>
<P><h3>Tennis</h3>
<P>
<P>* <B>Jim Courier </B>posted his seventh consecutive victory over  <B>Thomas Muster,</B> beating the top-seeded Austrian 6-3, 7-5 in the quarterfinals of the Qatar Open. Courier will face <B>Sergi Bruguera </B>of Spain in in a semifinal today.
<P>* <B>Wayne Ferreira </B>and <B>Amanda Coetzer </B>of South Africa, 3-0 in Group B play, will face the U.S. team of <B>Justin Gimelstob </B>and <B>Chanda Rubin </B>in today&#39;s Hopman Cup final in Perth, Autralia. Gimelstob and Rubin beat Australia 2-1 to top Group A with a 3-0 record.
<P>
<P><h3>Baseball</h3>
<P>
<P>* The Colorado Rockies gave pitcher <B>Kevin Ritz,</B> their biggest winner with 17 victories in 1996, a lucrative new contract.
<P>* American League umpire <B>Vic Voltaggio </B>has retired after 20 years in the league and will be replaced by <B>Gary Cederstrom,</B> who has umpired professionally for 18 seasons -- the last eight as a fill-in in the majors.
<P>
<P><h3>Miscellany</h3>
<P>
<P>* Former Pittsburgh Steelers running back <B>Rocky Bleier </B>has hocked his Super Bowl rings and filed for bankruptcy. His former wife has little sympathy. <B>Aleta Whitaker </B>said in a counter-suit that Bleier just wants to avoid paying her $837,948 from the sale of their suburban Pittsburgh home.
