<P>
<P><B></B>
<P><B>ASBURY, GEORGE RICHARD - </B>age 78, of LaFollette, passed away Tuesday, Dec. 31, 1996, at the LaFollette Medical Center. He attended Fincastle United Methodist Church, member of Caryville Lodge #665 F&AM and Caryville O.E.S. #415. Mr. Asbury served as Deputy County Trustee from 1958 until 1974, and trustee from 1974 until 1990. Preceded in death by parents, Wesley and Lou Miller Asbury of Caryville; sister, Winnie (Sis) Massengill; and brothers, Raymond, Homer, Roy, Condrey, Maynard, Robert and Henry &#39;&#39;Fuzz&#39;&#39; Asbury. Survivors: wife, Maxene Graves Asbury; daughter, Leann Asbury; several nieces and nephews; and a host of friends. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Friday, Jan. 3 at Cross Funeral Home with funeral services to follow, Rev. David Lawrence officiating. Interment 10 a.m. Saturday, Jan. 4, at Woodlawn Cemetery with Masonic services by Caryville Lodge #665. Arrangements by Cross Funeral Home.
<P>
<P><B>BAKER, JAMES (JIM) ROBERT - </B>age 66, of Corryton, passed away December 31, 1996, at his home. Member of Marantha Baptist Church. Preceded in death by: father, Nero E. Baker; brother, John A. Baker; stepsons, John Leroy Stellate (Jackie Baker). He was a retired heavy equipment operator with 30 years service with Operating Engineers Local 917. Survivors: wife, Marie Baker; son and daughter-in-law, Mike and Le Anna Baker; daughter, Karen Baker; mother, Jewel Baker; sisters and brothers-in-law, Mary and Howard Phillips, Teena and Hurchel York; brother and sister-in-law, Fran and Marion Baker; stepchildren, Chris and Beth Matthews; grandchildren, Jacob and Crystal Baker; mother and father-in-law, Mary and C.L. Creswell; sisters and brothers-in-law, Jo Ann and Larry Kiser, Linda and Larry Creswell, Carolyn and Kenneth Lacy, Shirley and Mike Mynatt; sisters-in-law, Darlene Creswell and Rhonda Lowery. Funeral services 1 p.m. Friday, McCarty&#39;s Evergreen Chapel, Rev. Kenneth Lacy and Rev. Roger Lee will officiate. Interment to follow in Mt. Herman Methodist Church Cemetery. Arrangements by McCarty&#39;s Evergreen Chapel, 7426 Asheville Highway.
<P>
<P><B>BAKER, ERNEST GLENN &#39;&#39;RED&#39;&#39; - </B>age 66, of Clinton, Tenn., passed away January 2, 1997, at Oak Ridge Methodist Medical Center after suffering a heart attack on December 21, 1996. Mr. Baker was born August 10, 1930, in Harlan County, Ky., to Elijah A. and Mae Hensley Baker. Preceded in death by parents and brothers, Drexel Baker, Manchester, Tenn., and Rev. Kenneth Baker, Lincoln, Neb. Graduated Clinton High School 1949. Attended Tennessee Wesleyan College. Veteran of U.S. Army Battery A, 191st Field Artillery Battalion, 101 Airborne Division, Korean War. Retired from U.S. Dept. of Energy 1987 after 30 years service. At the time of retirement, Mr. Baker was assigned to the Office of Scientific and Technical Information as a tecnical information specialist. Member of St. Mark&#39;s United Methodist Church, Clinton. Member of board of directors for Clinton Recreation Commission. Past officer and former coach of Clinton Girls&#39; Softball, Inc. Mr. Baker enjoyed sports activities throughout his life. He played high school and college football, was an avid bowler and played golf. Survivors: daughter, Penny D. Baker and her mother, Joyce L. Baker, Clinton; brother, Leslie A. Baker, Sr. and his wife, Glessie, Maryville, Tenn.; sisters-in-law, Alice F. Baker, Manchester, Tenn., and Anne Baker, Lincoln, Neb.; several nieces and nephews. Funeral services will be held 8:30 p.m. Friday, Jan. 3, 1997, in the Holley-Gamble Chapel with Rev. Bill Rowland officiating. Graveside service will be 10 a.m. Saturday, Jan. 4, 1997, in Sunset Cemetery, Clinton, with full military honors. The family will receive friends 7-8:30 p.m. just prior to the funeral service at Holley-Gamble Chapel. In lieu of flowers, the family respectfully requests any memorials be made to the American Heart Association, P.O. Box 6014, Oak Ridge, TN 37831 or any charity of the donor&#39;s choice.
