<P><B>WINTER, LADONA TEDDER - </B>age 63, of Dunbar, W. Va., died Sunday, Dec. 29, 1996, after a long illness. She was a native of Kingsport, Tenn. Survivors: brother, Maynard Tedder of Harper&#39;s Ferry, W. Va.; sister, June Tedder Armstrong, Kingsport; half brother, Tony Mowdy; half sister, Carol Ann Mowdy Grizzell, Surgoynsville, Tenn. Funeral services were held 1 p.m. Thursday, Jan. 2, 1997, at Keller Funeral Home, Dunbar, W. Va. Burial in Grandview Memorial Park, Dunbar.
<P>
<P><B>WOODALL, HENRY &#39;&#39;H.P.&#39;&#39; - </B>age 85, of South Knoxville, passed away January 1, 1997, at Knoxville Health Care Center. Active member of Immanuel Baptist Church, a veteran of World War II, and a member of Woodward Lodge #0737 F&AM. He retired with 45 years of service from Life Insurance Company of Georgia. Survivors: wife, Mary Louise Johnson Woodall, Knoxville; son and daughter-in-law, Gerald and Martha Woodall, Georgia; daughter and son-in-law, Mary Ann and Ed McCoy, Virginia; four grandchildren; four great-grandchildren; sister, Sudie Vaughn, Georgia. Funeral service 7 p.m. Friday, Berry Chapel, with Rev. Doug McPherson and Dr. Gene Fleming officiating. Music will be provided by Tim Purvis. Graveside service and interment 11 a.m. Saturday at Woodlawn Cemetery. The family will receive friends 5-7 p.m. Friday at Berry Funeral Home, Chapman Highway.
<P>
<P><B>WORKMAN, RAYMOND E. - </B>age 75, of Morristown, passed away Tuesday, December 31, 1996, at Morristown-Hamblen Hospital. He was a deputy with the Hamblen County Sheriff&#39;s Department. He was a veteran of World War II and a member of Lowland Missionary Baptist Church. Survivors include his wife, Ethel Almeda Walton Workman; sons, Clifford Paschel Workman of Marion, Ind., Jimmy Workman and David Workman of Knoxville; step-children, Linda Greene and George Cochran of Morristown, and Jimmy Cochran of Newport; grandchildren, Tim Workman, Letitia Workman and Crystal Burton; two great-grandchildren and 11 step-grandchildren; sisters, Ruby Owens of Rutledge and Frances Wilson of Knoxville; step-brother, Ernest Wilson of Bulls Gap; several nieces and nephews. Funeral service will be 11 a.m. Friday, January 3, 1997, at Westside Chapel with Rev. Murrel Ison and Rev. Thomas Holt officiating. Interment will be in the Jefferson Memorial Gardens. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Thursday at Westside Chapel. Westside Chapel Funeral Home in charge of arrangements.
<P>
