<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td align=left valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 03, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Business briefs</B></font><basefont size=6><!--SUBHEAD--></basefont></FONT><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		<h3>Ingram Group relocates Knox office</h3>
<P>
<P>   The Ingram Group has relocated its Knoxville offices to the first floor of 610 S. Gay Street, which formerly housed Fidelity Federal Savings and Loan, now a part of Union Planters Bank of East Tennessee
<P>   Susan Richardson Williams, who joined the group in September after serving two years in Gov. Don Sundquist&#39;s cabinet, said the group has added clients and more than doubled its Knoxville staff, necessitating additional space.
<P>   It previously had shared space in the Arcade Building with Venture Alliance, in which Ingram Group founder Tom Ingram is a principal.
<P>   The Ingram Group, with offices in Knoxville and Nashville, specializes in corporate strategy, public relations and government relations.
<P>   In addition to Williams, the Knoxville office is staffed by Carol Evans, former assistant athletics director for marketing for the Lady Vols; James Pratt, press secretary to former U.S. Sen. James Sasser, and George Korda, former city of Knoxville information director.
<P>
<P><h3>First American buys bank</h3>
<P>
<P>   First American Corp. has completed its acquisition of Hartsville Bancshares for approximately $13.4 million.
<P>    Hartsville Bancshares is a $100 million institution operating as CommunityFIRST Bank with five branches in the greater Nashville metropolitan area. 
<P>    This acquisition gives First American a total of 71 branches in Middle Tennessee.
<P>   First American is consolidating CommunityFIRST Bank operations into First American National Bank and changing the name to First American.
<P>   First American acquired all of the outstanding shares of Hartsville Bancshares in a tax-free exchange of First American&#39;s common stock.  First American issued approximately 175,000 shares in conjunction with this merger which represents 7.1 First American shares for each share of Hartsville Bancshares common stock.
<P>
<P><h3>Company completes acquisition of Georgia subsidiary</h3>
<P>
<P>   CHATTANOOGA -- Dixie Yarns Inc. said Thursday it has completed the acquisition of Danube Carpet Mills Inc. for $18.2 million.
<P>   Danube, headquartered in Fort Oglethorpe, Ga., manufactures and sells carpet for the manufactured and modular housing, recreational vehicle and van conversion industries and yarn for the carpet industry.
<P>   It is a subsidiary of Shelter Components Corporation Inc.
<P>   Dixie Yarns manufactures floor covering and textile products for specialty markets. The textile products include yarns, knit fabrics and apparel.
<P>
<P><h3>Names in the news</h3>
<P>
<P>   Betsy Foxx, formerly director of human resources at Kings Foodservice, has been named director of marketing that the Alcoa wholesale food distributor. <B>Susan Scalzo</B>, formerly of Charlotte, N.C., has been named human resources manager. . . .
<P>
