<head>
	<title>Same address: Jenkins to take over Quillen&#39;s Kingsport office</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 02, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>Same address: Jenkins to take over Quillen&#39;s Kingsport office</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I>By The Associated Press</I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">K</FONT>INGSPORT -- Most people in the 1st District know how to get to the congressman&#39;s office. Now, the new congressman will be finding his way there.
<P>    Bill Jenkins will move into the same Kingsport office that retiring Rep. Jimmy Quillen used for three decades.
<P>    &#39;&#39;People kept telling me they knew how to get there,&#39;&#39; Jenkins said.
<P>    The move will officially occur when Jenkins takes the oath of office Tuesday, Jan. 7.
<P>    Jenkins, a former Tennessee Valley Authority board member and most recently a Circuit Court judge in Rogersville, said he decided to make Quillen&#39;s quarters in the Kingsport Post Office his own after consulting with constituents.
<P>    &#39;&#39;We are going to remain in the Kingsport office at least on a temporary basis,&#39;&#39; said Jenkins, a Republican from Rogersville.
<P>    &#39;&#39;We may make it permanent. After talking to the General Services Administration, we found that for cost and space, we would be better off staying in the Kingsport office.&#39;&#39;
<P>    He said the public&#39;s familiarity with the Kingsport office was also a deciding factor in his plans to make Kingsport the location of his district office.
<P>    He said he is looking at opening a second field office in one of the counties in the western end of the district.
<P>    &#39;&#39;We know there are some counties that will be willing to make some space available to us for a rotating office,&#39;&#39; Jenkins said.
<P>    Jenkins has also named Bill Snodgrass, a former consultant with the state Department of Education and a one-time adjunct faculty member at East Tennessee State University, as the director of his field office.
<P>    &#39;&#39;Our goal for the field office is to continue the excellent work done by Congressman Quillen&#39;s staff,&#39;&#39; Jenkins said.
<P>    Jenkins said Snodgrass&#39; &#39;&#39;exemplary professional credentials and experience make him an excellent choice&#39;&#39; to serve as his field representative.
<P><font size=2><strong><p>Copyright 1997 by the Associated Press. All Rights Reserved. Unauthorized use is probihited. </p></strong></font>
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
