<P><B>LAY, MR. ELMER - </B>age 78, of 415 W. Wheeler St., Rockwood, passed away Monday, December 30th at the Methodist Medical Center, Oak Ridge. He was a member of the First Baptist Church, Rockwood, retired utilities operator with Oak Ridge, Y-12 with 25 years service, U.S. Army veteran of World War II and member of the American Legion. Survived by his wife, Bea Lay, Rockwood; son, Larry Lay, Morristown, Tenn.; daughter, Mary Jo Foust, Glen Allen, Va.; five grandchildren, Jack, Lisa and Jason Lay, Wendy Yager, Shane Foust; three great-grandchildren, Robbie, Amie and Hunter Yager; brothers, John Lay, Oak Ridge, J.D. Lay, Carl Lay, Oneida, Tenn.; sister, Helen Poe, Jonesville, Va. Funeral services will be conducted Thursday, January 2nd. 8 p.m. from the chapel of Evans Mortuary with Rev. James Hutson officiating. Graveside services and interment will be held Friday at 11 a.m. in the Oak Grove Cemetery with full military honors by the Roane County Military Memorial Honor Guard. The family will receive friends Thursday 6-8 p.m. at the Evans Mortuary. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the First Baptist Church Life Center or nursery. Evans Mortuary of Rockwood in charge of services.
