<P><B>LEE, JESSE CLYDE, SR. - </B>age 87, of Knoxville, passed away Tuesday morning, December 31, 1996, at St. Mary&#39;s Hospital. He retired from Fraker Sales Company after 30 years service. He was of the Baptist faith. Preceded in death by his son, James Franklin Lee; and sister, Trula Lawrence. Survivors: wife, Carrie Artis Lee; daughters and sons-in-law, Betty and Ronnie Beets, Jane and Glenn Johnson; sons and daughters-in-law, Howard and Gunde Lee, Charles and Sue Lee, Jesse Lee, Jr., Wayne and Mary Lee; many grandchildren and great-grandchildren; brother, Bill Lee; sisters, Anna Bell Bush and Lilly Davis, all of Knoxville. Funeral service 10 a.m. Friday, Rose Chapel, Rev. Louis Branch officiating. Interment in Bookwalter Cemetery. Pallbearers: grandsons, Robert, Jeff, Ronnie, Greg, Scott Lee and Bryan Johnson. Honorary pallbearers: Ronnie Beets and Robbie Spurlock. The family will receive friends 7-9 p.m. Thursday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
