<head>
	<title>State&#39;s prepaid college tuition program draws interest</title>
	<meta name="keywords" content="Knoxville Tennessee Newspaper, Detours, Entertianment, Music, Arts">
	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="NewsView Connections32 with WebDesk">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center><a href="/"><IMG SRC="../../images/flag.gif" ALT="A Knoxville News-Sentinel Online product" border=0></a></center><BR clear=all>
<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=10>
	<tr>
	<td valign=top width=150>
		<i>January 01, 1997</i> 
	</td>
	<td align=left width=470>
            <basefont size=6>
		<FONT SIZE="6"><B>State&#39;s prepaid college tuition program draws interest</B></font><!--SUBHEAD--><P>
		<FONT size="2"><I></I></FONT><P>
		<FONT SIZE="3"><I></I></FONT><BR>
		</basefont><FONT SIZE="+2">N</FONT>ASHVILLE -- About 1,000 families have signed up for Tennessee&#39;s new prepaid college tuition program, and its marketing efforts have not yet begun.
<P>    The state&#39;s new Baccalaureate Education System Trust, or BEST, opens this spring. The program lets Tennesseans pay college tuition costs years ahead of time and at today&#39;s rates.
<P>    &#39;&#39;I think you can call it unrestrained enthusiasm. I get asked about it two or three times a day,&#39;&#39; said state Treasurer Steve Adams, who will direct BEST.
<P>    At least 22 states have started some form of the college savings plan.
<P>    Earlier this year, Congress provided an attractive tax incentive for them.
<P>    Parents, grandparents or friends can buy tuition credits at today&#39;s rates for future students, even while they are infants. The money goes into what amounts to a state-administered mutual fund.
<P>    State money managers, accustomed to handling huge pension investments, usually produce a return on the funds greater than the growth of college tuition rates.
<P>    Tennessee pension fund investments have grown at a rate of almost 10 percent over the past decade while tuition rates have increased about 5 percent.
<P>    &#39;&#39;I hope that the fact that the state is managing this fund gives people some confidence that this is not a fly-by-night scheme, but something that is going to be around for a long time. It gives people a chance at a child&#39;s early age to identify and plan for the opportunities for kids to go to college,&#39;&#39; Adams said.
<P>    Congress settled a long legal dispute this year by allowing gains on the investment to be deferred until a student uses the credits. The student, not the purchaser, becomes liable for the tax in a presumably low tax bracket. In private investment funds that might be used for the same purpose, gains are taxed annually to the purchaser, reducing appreciation of the fund.
<P>    Tennessee tuition credits will be priced at about $22.50 each at the start, with 100 credits producing the annual average tuition at state universities, community colleges and technical schools. Tennessee purchasers can buy up to 1,500 credits in case the student decides to attend a more expensive private school or use them for graduate work. The credits can be used at any accredited school anywhere in the country.
<P>    The Legislature approved the prepaid tuition plan last spring, and an oversight committee approved its operating rules in mid-December.
<P>    Officials are working on a marketing plan to launch sales by April.
<P>
<P>
	</td>
	</tr>
</table>
<hr size=5>

