<P>
<P>
<P><B></B>
<P><B>AXMACHER, NANCY MAY BEASLEY SEAGRAVES - </B>of Knoxville, died December 30, 1996, at St. Mary&#39;s Hospital. She was preceded in death by her husband, O.C. Axmacher. Survivors: children, Dewayne Seagraves of Conyers, Ga., Joan Fleming and Janice Leath, both of Knoxville, Judy Burton of Orlando, Fla. and Michael Seagraves of Tallahassee, Fla.; 21 grandchildren and 22 great-grandchildren. Family and friends will meet at Greenwood Cemetery, Thursday, for a 10 a.m. graveside service with Dr. Doug Slagle officiating. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the Knox Humane Society or Ijams Nature Center. Friends may call at their convenience at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>BRADLEY, EDNA MILLS - </B>age 78, of Lenoir City and Cleveland, passed away Monday evening December 30, 1996, in Chattanooga. She was a member of the First Church of The Nazarene in Lenoir City. Preceded in death by husband, Rev. John Lois Bradley; brothers and sisters, Sanford Hope Mills, Hommel Mills, Willie Mills Pickell-Hyde, Bart Lindsey Mills, Robert Godbey Mills, Ada Frances Mills. Survivors: daughters and sons-in-law, Gaytha &#39;&#39;Gaye&#39;&#39; Bradley Ogle and Steve of Cleveland, Joyce Bradley Robertson and William &#39;&#39;Bill&#39;&#39; of Smithville; son and daughter-in-law, John Edward Bradley and Pam of Riverdale, Ga.; several grandchildren; great-grandchildren; nieces and nephews; sister, Ollie Rhea Mills McReynolds of Lenoir City. The family will receive friends from 3-4 p.m. Thursday followed by funeral services at 4 p.m. in the Click Funeral Home Chapel. Rev. Joe Brown and Rev. Ronald McCormick officiating. Interment Woodlawn Cemetery. Click Funeral Home, Lenoir City, in charge.
<P>
<P><B>BURLESON, THOMAS M. - </B>age 90, of West Knoxville, died Tuesday, December 31, 1996, at U.T. Hospital. Member of Rocky Hill Baptist Church. Preceded in death by first wife, Gladys Elizabeth Medlin Burleson. Survivors: wife, Omma Hankins Smith Burleson of Knoxville; sons and daughters-in-law, Howard and Joann Burleson, David and Nancy Burleson, Jack and Bunny Burleson, all of Knoxville; step-daughter, Rosemary Bdeir of Amman, Jordan; step-son, Don Smith of Okechobee, Fla.; grandchildren, Cindy and Andra Lettieri, Gary Burleson, Sherron Burleson, Susan Adkins, Patty Burleson and Pam Stewart; half brothers and sisters-in-law, John and Thelma Burleson of Knoxville, Paul and Iris Burleson of St. Louis, Mo.; half sister, Nora Cheatham Erby of Texas. Funeral service 4 p.m. Thursday at Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel. Family and friends will meet 10:45 a.m. Friday at Highland Memorial Cemetery for an 11 a.m. graveside service and interment with Rev. Philip Nations and Rev. John Burleson officiating. Active pallbearers: Donavon Stewart, Gary Burleson, Jim Adkins, Walter Harrington, Tyson Burleson and Jimmy Merritt. Honorary pallbearers will be Eveready Sunday School Class at Rocky Hill Baptist Church. The family will receive friends 2-4 p.m. Thursday at Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>CARDIN, HUMPHREY (HUMP) - </B>age 79, resident of Parkside Nursing Home, Ft. Oglethorpe, Ga., formerly of 11 Maple Way, Ringgold, Ga., and Mt. Vernon, Tenn., passed away 7 p.m. Monday, December 30, 1996, at Parkside Nursing Home. Member of Mt. Vernon Baptist Church. Survivors: niece, Reba Lee, Ringgold, Ga.; several other nieces and nephews. Graveside service and interment 2 p.m. Wednesday, Eleazar Cemetery, Rev. Beecher Miller officiating. Family will receive friends 12:30-1:30 p.m. Wednesday at Biereley-Hale Funeral Home, Madisonville.
<P>
<P><B>COOKE, JULIA JACKSON - </B>age 36, of Maryville, died Tuesday, December 31, 1996, at her home. She was a member of Faith Baptist Church, graduated from Heritage High School in 1978, graduated from the University of North Florida, was a system analyst for Blue Cross and Blue Shield of Florida, was a volunteer for the American Cancer Society Breast Cancer Division of Duvall County, Florida for 10 years, was a Purple Belt Tae Kwon Do. She was preceded in death by her father, Walter H. Jackson, Sr. Survivors inlcude husband, Doug Cooke; mother, Jo Ann Chambers Jackson of Knoxville; brother, Walter Jackson, Jr. of Knoxville; special friend, Pam Snoderly of Maryville; daughter-in-law of Joe and Lyda Cooke of Maryville. Funeral services will be held 8 p.m. Wednesday in McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home Chapel with Rev. Herman Helton officiating. The entombment will be 1 p.m. Thursday in Sherwood Mausoleum. Family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at McCammon-Ammons Funeral Home, Maryville.
<P>
<P><B>CREEKMORE, ROBERT VANGILDER, SR. - </B>age 64, of Plantation, Fla., died December 29, 1996, at Haywood Regional Medical Center in Clyde, N.C. He was the son of the late Robert Elmond and Evelyn Vangilder Creekmore. He was born and educated in Knoxville, graduating from the University of Tennessee in 1954. He was a veteran of the United States Army. Following his Army service, he embarked on a 35 year business career, during which he served as a marketing representative and executive for the IBM Corporation, the First National Bank of Atlanta and American Express. He was regional vice president for American Express at the time of his retirement in 1989. He was a member of Sigma Alpha Epsilon Fraternity and Ft. Lauderdale County Club, where he served as a member of the board of directors until shortly before his death. He is survived by his wife, Donna Rankin Creekmore of Plantation; son and daughter-in-law, Robert V. &#39;&#39;Rip&#39;&#39; Creekmore, Jr. and Joann of Kannapolis, N.C.; sisters, Eleanor Dickinson and Louise Senatore, both of San Francisco; 7 nieces and nephews. Funeral service will be 10 a.m. Thursday, January 2 at St. John&#39;s Cathedral, The Rev. Canon John C. Ross officiating. Interment Highland Memorial Cemetery. Memorials may be made to the Humane Society or American Heart Association. Family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel.
