<P><B>SANDERS, SARAH ALEXANDER - </B>age 66, of Jefferson City, passed away 4 p.m. Monday, December 30, 1996, at her residence after an extended illness. Mrs. Sanders attended grade school and high school in Marrowbone, Ky. Graduated from Western Kentucky University in Bowling Green. Mrs. Sanders received her master&#39;s degree from the University of Tennessee. Taught home economics in high schools in Kentucky and Florida and at Indiana University and Carson-Newman College. Served as president of Tennessee Home Economics Association. Mrs. Sanders was an elder at the First Presbyterian Church of Jefferson City  and a member of the Holston Presbytery Council and as chairman of the Holston Presbytery Camp Committee. Preceded in death by husband, Earl D. Sanders; parents, William Ledman and Georgia Pace Alexander; brother, Justin Alexander. Survived by: daughter, Major Martha Sanders of Belcamp, Md.; son and daughter-in-law, business owner John and Dr. Lynda Sanders of Lexington, Ky.; daughter and son-in-law, Betsy and Dr. Bill Childress of San Antonio, Texas; son and daughter-in-law, Professor George and Suzanne Sanders of Bradenton, Fla.; grandchildren, Katie and Holly Sanders, Justin Childress, Zachary Sutton and Abigail Sanders; sisters, Daisy B. Alexander of Marrowbone, Ky. and Betsy Rounds of Hanover, Md.; brother, James Ledman Alexander of Burksville, Ky.; several; nieces and nephews; special friends, Betty Finley, Dr. Barbara McDougal and Angie France; many friends too numerous to mention. Funeral service 6:30 p.m. Thursday, Jan. 2, 1997, at First Presbyterian Church of Jefferson City with Dr. Robert Reno and Rev. Roger Raby officiating. Interment will be held Friday, Jan. 3, 1997, in Marrowbone, Ky. Family will receive friends following the funeral service in the Fellowship Hall of First Presbyterian Church. Family requests that in lieu of flowers, memorial donations be made to First Presbyterian Church, 712 Church St, Jefferson City, TN 37760, to Holston Pres