<P>
<P><B>SMITH, PEARL ETHEL - </B>age 81, of Knoxville, passed away December 29, 1996, at Northhaven Health Care. Survived by grandsons, Kenneth and Jonathan Fitzpatrick; granddaughter, Stephannie Fitzpatrick; great-granddaughter, Brittney Fitzpatrick, all of Knoxville; brothers, Bill, Fred and John Rogers, all of Ohio, Jess Rogers of Tazewell and Jim Rogers of Florida; sisters, Roxie Byrd of Knoxville and Helen Walker of Ohio. Funeral service 11 a.m. Thursday at Weaver&#39;s Chapel, Rev. Terry Gaylor officiating. Interment in New Gray Cemetery. Pallbearers: Steve and Billy Rogers, Phillip and Gregg Nicely, Larry Adams and John Fitzpatrick. Family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday at Weaver Funeral Home.
<P>
<P><B>STRICKLAND, CHARLIE - </B>age 81, of Knoxville, died Monday, December 30, 1996, at Ft. Sanders Hospital. He was a retired employee of Associated Transport, Inc., and was awarded an expert drivers citation for several years of no accident record. He was a member of Teamsters Local 519. An avid bowler, he possessed several trophies and awards. He was preceded in death by his wife, Elizabeth Strickland. He leaves to mourn his passing: a sister, Mrs. Cleo Morris; brother, Walt Strickland; two nieces, Pat Blalock and Marie Buffington, both of Acworth, Ga.; a host of other relatives and friends to include a very special friend and co-worker, Elmer P. Griffin and Rev. Thomas Cook. Funeral services will be 2 p.m. Wednesday in the Holly Hills South Chapel. Entombment will follow in Holly Hills Memorial Park. The family will receive friends 1-2 p.m. Wednesday at Holly Hills South Funeral Home (573-7300).
<P>
<P><B>SWANN, ELEANOR H. - </B>of North Knoxville, died Sunday, December 29, 1996. She was a member of First Lutheran Church. Survived by her husband, Hugh Swann, Jr.; daughter and son-in-law, Karen and Jeff Schoenfield; son, Thomas Swann of Colorado; five grandchildren; mother, Mrs. Evelyn Maas of Michigan. Funeral service 8 p.m. Thursday in Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel with Pastor John P. Schulz officiating. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to First Lutheran Church, 1207 N. Broadway, Knoxville, TN 37917. The family will receive friends 6:30-8 p.m. Thursday at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>THOMAS, ANNE HENEGAR - </B>age 99, of Knoxville, died December 29, 1996, at Little Creek Sanitarium. She was a member of the Church Street United Methodist Church. She was preceded in death by husband, Matthew G. Thomas; and son, Matthew G. Thomas, Jr. She was the daughter of the late Mr. and Mrs. Edward Henegar and the great-great-granddaughter of Charles and Margaret White McClung. Her late husband, Matt G. Thomas, was president of Appalachian Textile Mill and a founder and secretary/treasurer of Cherokee Textile Mill. Survivors: daughter and son-in-law, Mary T. and William E. Fleury; daughter, Barbara T. Henslee of Knoxville; grandchildren, Anne F. Curtis, Chattanooga, Tenn., Barbara F. Burrows, Houston, Texas, John S. Foster, Atlanta, Ga., Chadwick Brown Conroy and Thomas Garrett Brown of Knoxville; great-grandchildren, Polly F. Curtis, San Francisco, Calif., and Benjamin B. Curtis, Elizabeth Conroy, Chase Conroy and Mary Chad Conroy, all of Knoxville; sister-in-law, Mrs. Martin J. Henegar of Knoxville; seven nieces; two nephews; 13 great-nieces and nephews; and several great-great-nieces and nephews. Family and friends will meet at the main entrance to Highland Memorial Cemetery at 10:45 a.m. Thursday for an 11 a.m. graveside service, Rev. William Fowler officiating. Memorials may be made to the Holston United Methodist Home for Children, P.O. Box 188, Greeneville, TN 37743 or to Church Street United Methodist Church or to Little Creek Santiarium. Arrangements by Rose Mortuary Mann Heritage Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>TODD, ASHFORD, JR. - </B>of Chattanooga. Graveside services will be held 11:30 a.m. Thursday at Greenwood Cemetery, Knoxville, with the Rev. Julian Spitzer officiating. Memorial contributions may be made to Sr. Neighbors or a favorite charity.
<P>
<P><B>WILLIAMS, MATTIE MALISSIE - </B>age 94, of Route 1, Blaine, passed away 6:30 p.m. Sunday evening, December 29, 1996, at Ridgeview Terrace Nursing Home in Rutledge. She was a member of the New Corinth Baptist Church and was preceded in death by her husband, Hubert Williams; daughter, Edith Cranfield; son, J.T. Williams; and two sisters. Survivors include her daughters, Iva Daniel and Reda Morgan; sons, Hubert Junior Williams and Paul &#39;&#39;Hunkie&#39;&#39; Williams; son and daughter-in-law, Curtis and Edna Williams, all of Blaine; grandchildren, Barbara Myers, Erma Lou Greene, Wayne Morgan, Brenda Lawson, Sgt. FC Michael Williams, and Eddie and Donna Williams; many great-grandchildren and great-great-grandchildren; sister, Luellia Daniel; several nieces and nephews. Funeral services will be held at 8 p.m. Wednesday evening, January 1, 1997, from the Smith Funeral Home Chapel in Rutledge with Rev. Lee Wayne Grubb and Rev. Fred Chandler officiating. Graveside services and interment will be 11 a.m. Thursday morning, January 2, 1997, in the New Corinth Cemetery. The family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Wednesday evening prior to services at the funeral home. Friends may call at the home of Curtis Williams. Arrangements by Smith Funeral Home, 123 Water Street, Rutledge, Tennessee 37861, Phone (423) 828-5555.
<P>
<P><B>TALLENT, GLORIA BERRIER - </B>age 47, of Knoxville, Tenn., departed this life to be with her heavenly father on December 28, 1996, at 7:30 p.m. She left from the University of Tennessee Medical Center to be with the Lord after a long illness with lupus and cancer. Attended West Lonsdale Baptist Church and was a former faithful employee of Abstract Title, Inc. She is survived by devoted husband, Joseph W. Tallent, local contractor; beloved parents, Elmer and Mildred Berrier; aunt, Nettie Mingie; sisters and brothers-in-law, Robert and Toni Johnson of South Carolina, Robert and Jill Keck, Gene and Judy Sayne, all of Knoxville; and sister, Linda Raby of North Carolina; brothers-in-law and sisters-in-law, David and Carolyn Tallent, Steve and Shirley Tallent, Linda Tallent, Janie and A.J. Daniels, Dorothy and Fred Lawhorn, Knoxville, Tenn., Carolyn and Vaughn Davis, Maryville, Tenn., Raymond and Ethel Tallent of Macon, Ga.; nieces and nephews, Robin and Kellie Keck of Knoxville, Charles and Cheryl Johnson, and Chris Johnson of South Carolina, Kim Gazaway and family of Georgia, Tammy Rowe and family of North Carolina, John Raby and family, and Jeffrey Raby of Knoxville, Scott and Whitney Tallent, Debbie and Angie Daniels, Jeff and Aaron Lawhorn, Ray and Amanda Tallent, all of Knoxville, Mike Davis, Donnie Davis, Carol Ann Early, all of Maryville, Tenn., and Raymond E. Tallent, Jr. of Ohio; many friends, aunts, uncles, and cousins including Jerry and Carolyn Cunningham. Pallbearers: Robert Keck, Gene Sayne and Jerry Cunningham, Chris Johnson, Scott Tallent and Aaron Lawhorn. Honorary pallbearers: Robert Johnson, David Tallent and Steve Tallent. Funeral services January 1, 1997, at 11 a.m. at Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel with the Rev. Bruce Robinson officiating. Interment will follow at Lynnhurst Cemetery. In lieu of flowers, memorials may be made to the Lupus Foundation of America, Kidney Foundation of East Tennessee or American Cancer Society. The family expresses their gratitude and thanks for all the support, assistance and loving care shown over the years from the family and many friends. Special thanks is especially extended to the 8th floor nurses and staff of the University of Tennessee Medical Center. Thanks is also expressed to the personnel and friends at Martin Mill Dialysis Clinic. Arrangements by Rose Mortuary Broadway Chapel.
<P>
<P><B>YOUNG, HERBERT HAMILTON - </B>age 73, of Kingston, passed away Monday, December 30, 1996, at Methodist Medical Center. He was a member of Bethel Presbyterian Church, Union Lodge 38, F&AM, Scottish Rite and Eastern Star Chapter 405, Kingston. Survivors: wife, Jean Young of Kingston; daughters, Amy Ravotti of Comer, Ga.; sons, David Young of Crawford, Ga. and Scott Young of Kingston; sisters, Katherine Eldridge of Kingston; eight grandchildren; one great-grandchild. The body is at Kyker Funeral Home, Kingston, where the family will receive friends 6-8 p.m. Thursday, Jan. 2, 1997. Funeral 8 p.m. Thursday in Kyker Chapel, the Rev. Richard Hettrick officiating, followed by a Masonic Memorial Service conducted by Union Lodge 38 F&AM. Burial 10 a.m. Friday, Kingston Memorial Gardens. Family suggests memorial donations to Bethel Presbyterian Church, American Lung Asociation or charity of your choice.
